{"_id":"0dwdpRZI9Me3Wljl","name":"The Canine Tigers","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5SUVPP90FXXlg7gs","name":"The Canine Tigers - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Canine Tigers","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the village dogs, turned into monsters \nby the desire of one of the children. Once the tiger’s ferocity \ntakes over, we can no longer be controlled.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","positive":"We are the village dogs, turned into monsters \nby the desire of one of the children. Once the tiger’s ferocity \ntakes over, we can no longer be controlled.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Canine Tigers","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"cQjORsQ2uA651AsW","name":"Gift - Fierce as a Tiger","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Canine Tigers","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>When a Canine Tiger suffers \na Wound, it goes mad with rage and its Opposition Level \nrises to Hard 7. At the mercy of anger, the Tiger will attack \nthe closest target without distinguishing between allies and \nenemies.\nNorman Henkle \nThe Powerful Wizard Who \nMakes Wishes Come True</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Canine Tigers","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AkGap2Ft8NdfwTSs","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Canine Tigers","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are the village dogs, turned into monsters \nby the desire of one of the children. Once the tiger’s ferocity \ntakes over, we can no longer be controlled.\nGift - Fierce as a Tiger: When a Canine Tiger suffers \na Wound, it goes mad with rage and its Opposition Level \nrises to Hard 7. At the mercy of anger, the Tiger will attack \nthe closest target without distinguishing between allies and \nenemies.\nNorman Henkle \nThe Powerful Wizard Who \nMakes Wishes Come True</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","owner":"The Canine Tigers","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-canine-tigers-242","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":242,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are the village dogs, turned into monsters \nby the desire of one of the children. Once the tiger’s ferocity \ntakes over, we can no longer be controlled.\nGift - Fierce as a Tiger: When a Canine Tiger suffers \na Wound, it goes mad with rage and its Opposition Level \nrises to Hard 7. At the mercy of anger, the Tiger will attack \nthe closest target without distinguishing between allies and \nenemies.\nNorman Henkle \nThe Powerful Wizard Who \nMakes Wishes Come True</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1tB1Rszsp13XIDSK","name":"Alizée the Fugitive","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Rp27krF7r8o0P5jM","name":"Alizée the Fugitive - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alizée the Fugitive","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out \nof love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability \nsometimes scares me.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152.","positive":"I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out \nof love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability \nsometimes scares me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Alizée the Fugitive","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1KScU5RI2aTItaeI","name":"Gift - Spiritualist","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alizée the Fugitive","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Alizée can see and communicate with \nspirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past \ntwenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit \nenergy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can \nobtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she \nhas perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove \na Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.\nThe Underground Pit</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Alizée the Fugitive","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XSTtKBX9CZCplzjz","name":"Gift - Mass of Restless Spirits","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alizée the Fugitive","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The pit accumulates \nspiritual energy thanks to the passage of the comet Morituris. \nAt the beginning of each Scene, there are 2 Grudge Tokens \nin the pit. An NPC with the Gift Spirit, Alizée with the Gift \nSpiritualist, or a Hunter with a Descriptor associated with \nmagic or spirits, can use their action to add or remove 1 \nToken from the mass. If at midnight on December 31st there \nare 3 Tokens in the pit, all the accumulated energy will cause \na powerful explosion capable of wiping out half of Paris. \nThe passage of the comet will add 1 Token at the stroke of \nmidnight. There can never be more than 4 Grudge Tokens on \nthis Gift.\nThreat - Grudge of the Dead</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Alizée the Fugitive","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YZpCxl2kj1exRH5e","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alizée the Fugitive","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out \nof love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability \nsometimes scares me.\nAgenda: Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don’t need \nto fear the Church’s punishment.\nGift - Spiritualist: Alizée can see and communicate with \nspirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past \ntwenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit \nenergy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can \nobtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she \nhas perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove \na Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.\nThe Underground Pit\nDescriptor: A huge pit where the corpses of all those who \ncannot afford a burial are thrown. Crowds of restless spirits \nthrong among the inert bodies, invisible to mundane eyes.\nGift - Mass of Restless Spirits: The pit accumulates \nspiritual energy thanks to the passage of the comet Morituris. \nAt the beginning of each Scene, there are 2 Grudge Tokens \nin the pit. An NPC with the Gift Spirit, Alizée with the Gift \nSpiritualist, or a Hunter with a Descriptor associated with \nmagic or spirits, can use their action to add or remove 1 \nToken from the mass. If at midnight on December 31st there \nare 3 Tokens in the pit, all the accumulated energy will cause \na powerful explosion capable of wiping out half of Paris. \nThe passage of the comet will add 1 Token at the stroke of \nmidnight. There can never be more than 4 Grudge Tokens on \nthis Gift.\nThreat - Grudge of the Dead\nDescriptor: We are the spirits of those who are dead and \nforgotten by all. We hate the living and their life energy, and we \nattack anyone who dares to approach the underground pit.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152.","owner":"Alizée the Fugitive","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-aliz-e-the-fugitive-152","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":152,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out \nof love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability \nsometimes scares me.\nAgenda: Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don’t need \nto fear the Church’s punishment.\nGift - Spiritualist: Alizée can see and communicate with \nspirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past \ntwenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit \nenergy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can \nobtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she \nhas perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove \na Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.\nThe Underground Pit\nDescriptor: A huge pit where the corpses of all those who \ncannot afford a burial are thrown. Crowds of restless spirits \nthrong among the inert bodies, invisible to mundane eyes.\nGift - Mass of Restless Spirits: The pit accumulates \nspiritual energy thanks to the passage of the comet Morituris. \nAt the beginning of each Scene, there are 2 Grudge Tokens \nin the pit. An NPC with the Gift Spirit, Alizée with the Gift \nSpiritualist, or a Hunter with a Descriptor associated with \nmagic or spirits, can use their action to add or remove 1 \nToken from the mass. If at midnight on December 31st there \nare 3 Tokens in the pit, all the accumulated energy will cause \na powerful explosion capable of wiping out half of Paris. \nThe passage of the comet will add 1 Token at the stroke of \nmidnight. There can never be more than 4 Grudge Tokens on \nthis Gift.\nThreat - Grudge of the Dead\nDescriptor: We are the spirits of those who are dead and \nforgotten by all. We hate the living and their life energy, and we \nattack anyone who dares to approach the underground pit.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don’t need \nto fear the Church’s punishment.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2AObYqf2o4217R19","name":"The White Rabbit","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"CC4WlZOwSYiHnSes","name":"The White Rabbit - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The White Rabbit","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I’m a little white rabbit wandering around the \nCure Rooms and I have a message holder tied around my neck. \nI fear those I do not know.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 173.","positive":"I’m a little white rabbit wandering around the \nCure Rooms and I have a message holder tied around my neck. \nI fear those I do not know.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The White Rabbit","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wiQcshOaXKV3qrGw","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The White Rabbit","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: I’m a little white rabbit wandering around the \nCure Rooms and I have a message holder tied around my neck. \nI fear those I do not know.\nGift - Messenger: By capturing a White Rabbit it is \npossible to take the message it carries. Roll a die.\n1-2: It’s not always convenient to knock on a door with your \nhand. \n3-4: Knocking on a door is the bare minimum to be \nexpected of a respectable person. \n5-6: When you arrive at a door, it is polite to ask if anyone \nis home.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 173.","owner":"The White Rabbit","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-the-white-rabbit-173","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":173,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: I’m a little white rabbit wandering around the \nCure Rooms and I have a message holder tied around my neck. \nI fear those I do not know.\nGift - Messenger: By capturing a White Rabbit it is \npossible to take the message it carries. Roll a die.\n1-2: It’s not always convenient to knock on a door with your \nhand. \n3-4: Knocking on a door is the bare minimum to be \nexpected of a respectable person. \n5-6: When you arrive at a door, it is polite to ask if anyone \nis home.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2OpJ1kDZBZGhmUnT","name":"Christian","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"qCkDaU4aW3wdJzCz","name":"Christian - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Christian","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a former soldier, called the Relentless \nby all because of my cold determination. I act without any \nqualms when it comes to executing an order.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","positive":"I am a former soldier, called the Relentless \nby all because of my cold determination. I act without any \nqualms when it comes to executing an order.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Christian","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bi5GTIJgKP32HkgS","name":"Gift - The Relentless","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Christian","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>When he is carrying out an order, \nChristian is immune to any effect that affects his behavior, \nsuch as fear or charm. The soldier increases his Opposition \nLevel by 1 when he tries to eliminate an obstacle that stands \nbetween him and the subject of an order he must carry out.\nEnar</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Christian","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PVoxrgSMaAt3I78v","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Christian","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former soldier, called the Relentless \nby all because of my cold determination. I act without any \nqualms when it comes to executing an order.\nAgenda: Help Andersen in memory of the old days and a \nmilitary life I can’t forget / Eliminate Enar to prove I am the \nbetter man.\nGift - The Relentless: When he is carrying out an order, \nChristian is immune to any effect that affects his behavior, \nsuch as fear or charm. The soldier increases his Opposition \nLevel by 1 when he tries to eliminate an obstacle that stands \nbetween him and the subject of an order he must carry out.\nEnar</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","owner":"Christian","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-christian-162","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":162,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former soldier, called the Relentless \nby all because of my cold determination. I act without any \nqualms when it comes to executing an order.\nAgenda: Help Andersen in memory of the old days and a \nmilitary life I can’t forget / Eliminate Enar to prove I am the \nbetter man.\nGift - The Relentless: When he is carrying out an order, \nChristian is immune to any effect that affects his behavior, \nsuch as fear or charm. The soldier increases his Opposition \nLevel by 1 when he tries to eliminate an obstacle that stands \nbetween him and the subject of an order he must carry out.\nEnar</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Help Andersen in memory of the old days and a \nmilitary life I can’t forget / Eliminate Enar to prove I am the \nbetter man.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2Yvmk1D5MZwrxQSu","name":"Lorenzo Scannapecore the Plague Doctor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"zcrAPBmOi0RKAwTB","name":"Lorenzo Scannapecore the Plague Doctor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lorenzo Scannapecore the Plague Doctor","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to \ndetail is obsessive.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152.","positive":"I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to \ndetail is obsessive.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Lorenzo Scannapecore the Plague Doctor","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dwcKQFxklR0Ay3t6","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lorenzo Scannapecore the Plague Doctor","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to \ndetail is obsessive.\nAgenda: Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée \nfrom prying eyes.\nAlizée the Fugitive</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152.","owner":"Lorenzo Scannapecore the Plague Doctor","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-lorenzo-scannapecore-the-plague-doctor-152","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":152,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to \ndetail is obsessive.\nAgenda: Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée \nfrom prying eyes.\nAlizée the Fugitive</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée \nfrom prying eyes.\nAlizée the Fugitive","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"30GSHeK0NSJ2q03y","name":"Sea Fairy","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"FCvFlvtH96ICKgxs","name":"Sea Fairy - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sea Fairy","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to \nperform true miracles. My entire existence is tied to the sea and \nleaving it would destroy me.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","positive":"I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to \nperform true miracles. My entire existence is tied to the sea and \nleaving it would destroy me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Sea Fairy","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PvlBAOQFdDSH9pNx","name":"Gift - Sea Magic","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sea Fairy","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Sea Fairy can always use one of \nthe following effects. 1. Water of Life: A target recovers 1 \nWound and, if they have been dead for no more than a day, \nthey can even come back to life. 2. The Fury of the Sea: \nThe water of the sea engulfs everything, sweeping away all \nthreats. Those who are within 30 feet must pass a Defense</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Sea Fairy","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kURlJmi9ZuaU9mo7","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sea Fairy","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to \nperform true miracles. My entire existence is tied to the sea and \nleaving it would destroy me.\nAgenda: I am sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept \nhim alive in favor of blind hatred. I would like to do something \nfor him, but I cannot go to the mainland to stop his fury or find \nhis beloved.\nSpecial Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer): I have \nheard of Marina and know her reputation. She uses her powers \nonly to enrich herself at the expense of others. I will never agree \nto help her unless she first shows me that she is also capable of \ngood deeds.\nGift – Sea Magic: The Sea Fairy can always use one of \nthe following effects. 1. Water of Life: A target recovers 1 \nWound and, if they have been dead for no more than a day, \nthey can even come back to life. 2. The Fury of the Sea: \nThe water of the sea engulfs everything, sweeping away all \nthreats. Those who are within 30 feet must pass a Defense</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","owner":"Sea Fairy","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-sea-fairy-164","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":164,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to \nperform true miracles. My entire existence is tied to the sea and \nleaving it would destroy me.\nAgenda: I am sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept \nhim alive in favor of blind hatred. I would like to do something \nfor him, but I cannot go to the mainland to stop his fury or find \nhis beloved.\nSpecial Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer): I have \nheard of Marina and know her reputation. She uses her powers \nonly to enrich herself at the expense of others. I will never agree \nto help her unless she first shows me that she is also capable of \ngood deeds.\nGift – Sea Magic: The Sea Fairy can always use one of \nthe following effects. 1. Water of Life: A target recovers 1 \nWound and, if they have been dead for no more than a day, \nthey can even come back to life. 2. The Fury of the Sea: \nThe water of the sea engulfs everything, sweeping away all \nthreats. Those who are within 30 feet must pass a Defense</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I am sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept \nhim alive in favor of blind hatred. I would like to do something \nfor him, but I cannot go to the mainland to stop his fury or find \nhis beloved.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"49YOUFn3ZbhgPFIU","name":"Hans","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"2pryG4yGoya7phtG","name":"Hans - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hans","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a former soldier, once one \nof the company’s best marksmen. I never miss \nmy mark and always have a loaded weapon \nhidden under my heavy overcoat.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","positive":"I am a former soldier, once one \nof the company’s best marksmen. I never miss \nmy mark and always have a loaded weapon \nhidden under my heavy overcoat.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Hans","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"GP69kOroC8imLhep","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hans","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former soldier, once one \nof the company’s best marksmen. I never miss \nmy mark and always have a loaded weapon \nhidden under my heavy overcoat.\nAgenda: Convince Nils to keep our \nsecret or remove him.\nGift - Gunslinger: Hans owns a \npair of prized experimental pistols, \nwhich he bought from an inventor</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","owner":"Hans","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-hans-164","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":164,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former soldier, once one \nof the company’s best marksmen. I never miss \nmy mark and always have a loaded weapon \nhidden under my heavy overcoat.\nAgenda: Convince Nils to keep our \nsecret or remove him.\nGift - Gunslinger: Hans owns a \npair of prized experimental pistols, \nwhich he bought from an inventor</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Convince Nils to keep our \nsecret or remove him.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"4AE8YZgLqPxd02Uc","name":"Angry Little Girl","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"e9pcksd7ENXMe3V3","name":"Angry Little Girl - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Angry Little Girl","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I survived the adults’ madness and now I \nstruggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this \ncruel world.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 188.","positive":"I survived the adults’ madness and now I \nstruggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this \ncruel world.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Angry Little Girl","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"t824E7rPGaQYhETR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Angry Little Girl","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I survived the adults’ madness and now I \nstruggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this \ncruel world.\nAgenda: Find a safe place to stay or a group of people \nready to accept and protect me.\nEnd of Scene: after one or more encounters (at the \ndiscretion of the Storyteller) the Hunters come across \nthe crown of the Fairies (THIRD SCENE OPTION A - \nThe Crown of the Fairies) or the Hulder (THIRD SCENE \nOPTION B - The Hulder and the white dress).\nTHIRD SCENE OPTION A – \nThe Crown of the Fairies\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Sherazade smiles at a young \nnobleman among her audience who has risen from his chair \nto get a better look at her. She winks at him and says: “Sit \ndown my little guest, now the best is coming. ” \n“The swamps are shrouded in thin veils of a ghostly mist. All \nis silent. The moon appears to crack and bleed into the sky, \nand the faint stars die out one by one as you travel deeper \ninto this nocturnal realm. There is a light in the distance, a \nglow that is reflected in the swamps and still water. This light \ncomes from a small golden crown, and all around, many \nsilhouettes dance as if enthralled by its light. Fairies look like \npale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in \nthe air as if adrift in an invisible current. They are dreamlike, \nethereal, but their bodies meet, touch and brush against each \nother or, sometimes, through each other. Their eyes are shut</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 188.","owner":"Angry Little Girl","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-angry-little-girl-188","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":188,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I survived the adults’ madness and now I \nstruggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this \ncruel world.\nAgenda: Find a safe place to stay or a group of people \nready to accept and protect me.\nEnd of Scene: after one or more encounters (at the \ndiscretion of the Storyteller) the Hunters come across \nthe crown of the Fairies (THIRD SCENE OPTION A - \nThe Crown of the Fairies) or the Hulder (THIRD SCENE \nOPTION B - The Hulder and the white dress).\nTHIRD SCENE OPTION A – \nThe Crown of the Fairies\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Sherazade smiles at a young \nnobleman among her audience who has risen from his chair \nto get a better look at her. She winks at him and says: “Sit \ndown my little guest, now the best is coming. ” \n“The swamps are shrouded in thin veils of a ghostly mist. All \nis silent. The moon appears to crack and bleed into the sky, \nand the faint stars die out one by one as you travel deeper \ninto this nocturnal realm. There is a light in the distance, a \nglow that is reflected in the swamps and still water. This light \ncomes from a small golden crown, and all around, many \nsilhouettes dance as if enthralled by its light. Fairies look like \npale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in \nthe air as if adrift in an invisible current. They are dreamlike, \nethereal, but their bodies meet, touch and brush against each \nother or, sometimes, through each other. Their eyes are shut</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Find a safe place to stay or a group of people \nready to accept and protect me.\nEnd of Scene: after one or more encounters (at the \ndiscretion of the Storyteller) the Hunters come across \nthe crown of the Fairies (THIRD SCENE OPTION A - \nThe Crown of the Fairies) or the Hulder (THIRD SCENE \nOPTION B - The Hulder and the white dress).\nTHIRD SCENE OPTION A – \nThe Crown of the Fairies\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Sherazade smiles at a young \nnobleman among her audience who has risen from his chair \nto get a better look at her. She winks at him and says: “Sit \ndown my little guest, now the best is coming. ” \n“The swamps are shrouded in thin veils of a ghostly mist. All \nis silent. The moon appears to crack and bleed into the sky, \nand the faint stars die out one by one as you travel deeper \ninto this nocturnal realm. There is a light in the distance, a \nglow that is reflected in the swamps and still water. This light \ncomes from a small golden crown, and all around, many \nsilhouettes dance as if enthralled by its light. Fairies look like \npale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in \nthe air as if adrift in an invisible current. They are dreamlike, \nethereal, but their bodies meet, touch and brush against each \nother or, sometimes, through each other. Their eyes are shut","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"52lW9h1hsjKzdHHO","name":"Dose the Giant in Love","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"H58zx0AwEyBMmiX4","name":"Dose the Giant in Love - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>My body has become pure metal and only the \npower of love can bring me back to flesh and blood. I fight \nand destroy anything that can threaten my sweet OZena.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","positive":"My body has become pure metal and only the \npower of love can bring me back to flesh and blood. I fight \nand destroy anything that can threaten my sweet OZena.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"cSKrRR9wqPxQ3uqr","name":"Gift - Of Steel and Love","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Dose is made of pure metal and \ncannot suffer any kind of physical Wound. The only way to \nget him to return to flesh and blood for a few moments is \nto make his heart beat with love. Seeing OZena in danger \nor well disposed towards him will change him back for \none Exchange. Seeing OZena, Dose can’t help but declare \nhis love as he fights, making his infatuation for the young \nassassin clear.\nThe Canine Tigers</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wkyDDfZzhXyKrQrH","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: My body has become pure metal and only the \npower of love can bring me back to flesh and blood. I fight \nand destroy anything that can threaten my sweet OZena.\nAgenda: I am in love with OZena and I want her to loyally \nserve Henkle once more. I know that imprisonment in the \nhands of the enemy may have made her reluctant to trust us. \nI have to save her, whether she wants it or not.\nGift - Of Steel and Love: Dose is made of pure metal and \ncannot suffer any kind of physical Wound. The only way to \nget him to return to flesh and blood for a few moments is \nto make his heart beat with love. Seeing OZena in danger \nor well disposed towards him will change him back for \none Exchange. Seeing OZena, Dose can’t help but declare \nhis love as he fights, making his infatuation for the young \nassassin clear.\nThe Canine Tigers</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","owner":"Dose the Giant in Love","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-dose-the-giant-in-love-242","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":242,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: My body has become pure metal and only the \npower of love can bring me back to flesh and blood. I fight \nand destroy anything that can threaten my sweet OZena.\nAgenda: I am in love with OZena and I want her to loyally \nserve Henkle once more. I know that imprisonment in the \nhands of the enemy may have made her reluctant to trust us. \nI have to save her, whether she wants it or not.\nGift - Of Steel and Love: Dose is made of pure metal and \ncannot suffer any kind of physical Wound. The only way to \nget him to return to flesh and blood for a few moments is \nto make his heart beat with love. Seeing OZena in danger \nor well disposed towards him will change him back for \none Exchange. Seeing OZena, Dose can’t help but declare \nhis love as he fights, making his infatuation for the young \nassassin clear.\nThe Canine Tigers</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I am in love with OZena and I want her to loyally \nserve Henkle once more. I know that imprisonment in the \nhands of the enemy may have made her reluctant to trust us. \nI have to save her, whether she wants it or not.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5F14HmdVW60IAO1q","name":"The Patients of Wonder","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"TlpInPt87Ew45nlN","name":"The Patients of Wonder - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Patients of Wonder","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are mad and desperate, driven to Wonder \nin the hope of curing our ailments. Madness guides our \nactions and we no longer understand that there is a world \noutside the bedlam.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 174.","positive":"We are mad and desperate, driven to Wonder \nin the hope of curing our ailments. Madness guides our \nactions and we no longer understand that there is a world \noutside the bedlam.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Patients of Wonder","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622931,"modifiedTime":1781557622931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MsbPeOoEe7uAwCvO","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Patients of Wonder","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are mad and desperate, driven to Wonder \nin the hope of curing our ailments. Madness guides our \nactions and we no longer understand that there is a world \noutside the bedlam.\nGift - Why I Am Here: Roll a die to see what problem led \nthem to Wonder.\n1 Violence: The Patient struggles to contain their anger. \nWhen they act violently increase their OL by 1. \n2 Kleptomania: The Patient yearns for any object they \ndeem interesting and will do everything to have it. Once \nper Scene, they can act 2 times consecutively, though the \nadditional Action must be used to attempt to escape and \nhide with the stolen goods.\n3 Abandoned: The Patient was interned at Wonder to \nbe forgotten. Hardened by loneliness, they gain 1 extra \nWound.\n4 Split personality: The Patient changes personality in \nthe face of a specific event, such as a threat. When the new \npersonality acts, its OL becomes Hard 7.\n5 Dementia: The Patient is not fully aware of what is \nhappening around them. They are immune to all attempts \nat intimidation. Increase their OL by 1 when defending \nagainst a violent action.\n6 Illness: The Patient is ill or horribly disfigured. Each \naction against them receives 1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 174.","owner":"The Patients of Wonder","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622931,"modifiedTime":1781557622931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-the-patients-of-wonder-174","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":174,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are mad and desperate, driven to Wonder \nin the hope of curing our ailments. Madness guides our \nactions and we no longer understand that there is a world \noutside the bedlam.\nGift - Why I Am Here: Roll a die to see what problem led \nthem to Wonder.\n1 Violence: The Patient struggles to contain their anger. \nWhen they act violently increase their OL by 1. \n2 Kleptomania: The Patient yearns for any object they \ndeem interesting and will do everything to have it. Once \nper Scene, they can act 2 times consecutively, though the \nadditional Action must be used to attempt to escape and \nhide with the stolen goods.\n3 Abandoned: The Patient was interned at Wonder to \nbe forgotten. Hardened by loneliness, they gain 1 extra \nWound.\n4 Split personality: The Patient changes personality in \nthe face of a specific event, such as a threat. When the new \npersonality acts, its OL becomes Hard 7.\n5 Dementia: The Patient is not fully aware of what is \nhappening around them. They are immune to all attempts \nat intimidation. Increase their OL by 1 when defending \nagainst a violent action.\n6 Illness: The Patient is ill or horribly disfigured. Each \naction against them receives 1 Penalty.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622931,"modifiedTime":1781557622931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5KQLljG0uteZFQDV","name":"Henrich the Father","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"O2COw8xKCBB15YSK","name":"Henrich the Father - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Henrich the Father","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am one of the many people Margareta \nsaved from the miserable life of an outcast. My son Klaus is \neverything to me, which is why I don’t want the village of \nGelb to be suspected of witchcraft.\nKlaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226.","positive":"I am one of the many people Margareta \nsaved from the miserable life of an outcast. My son Klaus is \neverything to me, which is why I don’t want the village of \nGelb to be suspected of witchcraft.\nKlaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Henrich the Father","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LmKd9khrFxspLJJh","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Henrich the Father","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am one of the many people Margareta \nsaved from the miserable life of an outcast. My son Klaus is \neverything to me, which is why I don’t want the village of \nGelb to be suspected of witchcraft.\nKlaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226.","owner":"Henrich the Father","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-henrich-the-father-226","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":226,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am one of the many people Margareta \nsaved from the miserable life of an outcast. My son Klaus is \neverything to me, which is why I don’t want the village of \nGelb to be suspected of witchcraft.\nKlaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"63Pd9STT91uPaJNk","name":"Lizard Automaton","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Eaq3QZ0PyRLhNg9a","name":"Lizard Automaton - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lizard Automaton","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions \nat the same time.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","positive":"I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions \nat the same time.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Lizard Automaton","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OsLD6H2jyOpWLrHA","name":"Gift - Tail","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lizard Automaton","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Automaton always acts twice, once with its \nfront legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both \nits actions on the same target.\nHall of the Mind</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Lizard Automaton","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vaqSto8H8BA8zAI1","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lizard Automaton","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions \nat the same time.\nGift - Tail: The Automaton always acts twice, once with its \nfront legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both \nits actions on the same target.\nHall of the Mind\nDescriptor: A series of rooms painted entirely in white. The \ndoors themselves do not have handles and it takes a careful \nlook to distinguish them from the walls. A large central hall \ngathers all the Patients, lying on rows of beds, asleep in a state \nof trance. The distant ticking of a clock breaks an otherwise \nunnatural silence, creating a hypnotic echo.\nInformation: In the Hall of the Mind, it is possible to \nfind several Patients in a catatonic state, including Alissa \nof Norfolk. Alice Liddell will not seek a confrontation with \nany intruders but will be friendly and willing to listen to the \nunexpected guests. Alice will offer a good tea in which \na powerful sleep drug is mixed.\nThreat - Alice’s special tea</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","owner":"Lizard Automaton","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-lizard-automaton-177","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":177,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions \nat the same time.\nGift - Tail: The Automaton always acts twice, once with its \nfront legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both \nits actions on the same target.\nHall of the Mind\nDescriptor: A series of rooms painted entirely in white. The \ndoors themselves do not have handles and it takes a careful \nlook to distinguish them from the walls. A large central hall \ngathers all the Patients, lying on rows of beds, asleep in a state \nof trance. The distant ticking of a clock breaks an otherwise \nunnatural silence, creating a hypnotic echo.\nInformation: In the Hall of the Mind, it is possible to \nfind several Patients in a catatonic state, including Alissa \nof Norfolk. Alice Liddell will not seek a confrontation with \nany intruders but will be friendly and willing to listen to the \nunexpected guests. Alice will offer a good tea in which \na powerful sleep drug is mixed.\nThreat - Alice’s special tea</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6AHALfZiYzV7veOp","name":"Princess Tuvstarr","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"fvYqVm0zntDey9fW","name":"Princess Tuvstarr - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Princess Tuvstarr","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a pure and innocent soul, who just \nwants a world without suffering.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 193.","positive":"I am a pure and innocent soul, who just \nwants a world without suffering.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Princess Tuvstarr","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623498,"modifiedTime":1781557623498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wj343Oz4WvWaQbWp","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Princess Tuvstarr","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a pure and innocent soul, who just \nwants a world without suffering.\nAgenda: I want to stay forever in my perfect world. I \nhave been here for so long that I have forgotten what my \nlife was like before.\nGift – Creative Will: Tuvstarr has the power to create \nanything she wants in the Dream World. She can make a</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 193.","owner":"Princess Tuvstarr","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623498,"modifiedTime":1781557623498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-princess-tuvstarr-193","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":193,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a pure and innocent soul, who just \nwants a world without suffering.\nAgenda: I want to stay forever in my perfect world. I \nhave been here for so long that I have forgotten what my \nlife was like before.\nGift – Creative Will: Tuvstarr has the power to create \nanything she wants in the Dream World. She can make a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want to stay forever in my perfect world. I \nhave been here for so long that I have forgotten what my \nlife was like before.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623498,"modifiedTime":1781557623498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6eSrOciqJXg5hX0t","name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"c3fZ840sW9P4XzrA","name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>An abomination of flesh and tentacles, obeying \nArthur’s will.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","positive":"An abomination of flesh and tentacles, obeying \nArthur’s will.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KFhkwNLxb2tpFJDy","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: An abomination of flesh and tentacles, obeying \nArthur’s will.\nGift – Flesh Abomination: A Spawn can perform its \naction with a flesh tentacle up to a range of 6 feet, and at the \nend of each Exchange it will grow as indicated in the table. \nIf not engaged in a conflict, the Spawn will grow 1 step per</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-spawn-of-the-god-under-the-mine-212","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":212,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: An abomination of flesh and tentacles, obeying \nArthur’s will.\nGift – Flesh Abomination: A Spawn can perform its \naction with a flesh tentacle up to a range of 6 feet, and at the \nend of each Exchange it will grow as indicated in the table. \nIf not engaged in a conflict, the Spawn will grow 1 step per</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"82MyIbsuhvcs8Cgg","name":"Red-Hood Iskra","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"FEzxY9Q69WAvuH59","name":"Red-Hood Iskra - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I \nhide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made \nwith my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the \nlast gift from my mother.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","positive":"I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I \nhide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made \nwith my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the \nlast gift from my mother.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Bp7eOIjTrQhZcQLp","name":"Gift - Wolf’s Blood","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Iskra is \nmoved by an animalistic fury \nthat allows her to act twice in \nthe course of an Exchange.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ncRf52CnXWtSLjAH","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I \nhide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made \nwith my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the \nlast gift from my mother.\nAgenda: To unleash her animalistic fury \non Elizaveta and anyone who defends \nher. Taking revenge on my mother has \nbecome an obsession for me.\nGift - Wolf’s Blood: Iskra is \nmoved by an animalistic fury \nthat allows her to act twice in \nthe course of an Exchange.\nGift - The Senses of a \nWolf: Iskra’s sense of smell \nhas become infallible. The \nlittle girl will always be able to \nidentify someone if she knows \ntheir scent, ignoring all kinds \nof disguises and even magic.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RmpsD4VKzuhoZabe","name":"Gift - The Senses of a Wolf","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"Recovered legacy source","importSlug":"red-hood-iskra-Gift - The Senses of a Wolf","owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Iskra's sense of smell has become infallible. The little girl will always be able to identify someone if she knows their scent, ignoring all kinds of disguise and even magic.</p>","notes":"Red-Hood Iskra scenario actor gift.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783931098622,"modifiedTime":1783931098622,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-red-hood-iskra-126","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":126,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I hide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made with my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the last gift of my mother.</p><p>Agenda: To unleash her animalistic fury on Elizaveta and anyone who defends her. Taking revenge on my mother has become an obsession for me.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To unleash her animalistic fury on Elizaveta and anyone who defends her. Taking revenge on my mother has become an obsession for me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8et2DnGrdSN8XT3C","name":"Nils the Poor Devil","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"3UFYk3zJ3wdBvsKu","name":"Nils the Poor Devil - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nils the Poor Devil","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an old soldier who lost his legs \nin the war.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","positive":"I am an old soldier who lost his legs \nin the war.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Nils the Poor Devil","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TxGGhULdCaQV8qxx","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nils the Poor Devil","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old soldier who lost his legs \nin the war.\nAgenda: The guilt for what we did to Enar \nhaunts me, I want to find a way to bring him \npeace.\nHans</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","owner":"Nils the Poor Devil","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-nils-the-poor-devil-164","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":164,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old soldier who lost his legs \nin the war.\nAgenda: The guilt for what we did to Enar \nhaunts me, I want to find a way to bring him \npeace.\nHans</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"The guilt for what we did to Enar \nhaunts me, I want to find a way to bring him \npeace.\nHans","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"943mStPd9WOMvYcE","name":"The Hulder","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5DJePHkaIA5kVZU6","name":"The Hulder - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hulder","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an ancient forest spirit. I have eaten so many \nliving things that I have become fat and swollen, and the pieces \nof the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my \nslobbering lips.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 190.","positive":"I am an ancient forest spirit. I have eaten so many \nliving things that I have become fat and swollen, and the pieces \nof the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my \nslobbering lips.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Hulder","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623404,"modifiedTime":1781557623404,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"v0gskAe9U5i63cGu","name":"Gift - Corrupted Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hulder","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Hulder has a feminine form, \nbut her skin is spongy and slimy. Her breath smells of rot. She \ndoesn’t realize what a grotesque monster she has become, as in \nher mind she is still beautiful and seductive. When she suffers \n1 Wound, the Hulder vomits a cloud of foul vapor that reeks \nof rot. All the subjects hit by the cloud suffer 1 Wound in turn. \nThe effect of this Gift can be avoided with a Defense Check.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 190.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Hulder","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623404,"modifiedTime":1781557623404,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"M4tsHOMgubkhRhxY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hulder","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an ancient forest spirit. I have eaten so many \nliving things that I have become fat and swollen, and the pieces \nof the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my \nslobbering lips.\nAgenda: Devour everything I meet.\nGift – Corrupted Spirit: The Hulder has a feminine form, \nbut her skin is spongy and slimy. Her breath smells of rot. She \ndoesn’t realize what a grotesque monster she has become, as in \nher mind she is still beautiful and seductive. When she suffers \n1 Wound, the Hulder vomits a cloud of foul vapor that reeks \nof rot. All the subjects hit by the cloud suffer 1 Wound in turn. \nThe effect of this Gift can be avoided with a Defense Check. \nGift – Swollen with Flesh and Blood: If killed, the Hulder \nwill emit a long, heart-breaking cry that will echo in the \nwoods, and all the dead she has eaten will scream in agony in a</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 190.","owner":"The Hulder","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623404,"modifiedTime":1781557623404,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-the-hulder-190","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":190,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an ancient forest spirit. I have eaten so many \nliving things that I have become fat and swollen, and the pieces \nof the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my \nslobbering lips.\nAgenda: Devour everything I meet.\nGift – Corrupted Spirit: The Hulder has a feminine form, \nbut her skin is spongy and slimy. Her breath smells of rot. She \ndoesn’t realize what a grotesque monster she has become, as in \nher mind she is still beautiful and seductive. When she suffers \n1 Wound, the Hulder vomits a cloud of foul vapor that reeks \nof rot. All the subjects hit by the cloud suffer 1 Wound in turn. \nThe effect of this Gift can be avoided with a Defense Check. \nGift – Swollen with Flesh and Blood: If killed, the Hulder \nwill emit a long, heart-breaking cry that will echo in the \nwoods, and all the dead she has eaten will scream in agony in a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Devour everything I meet.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623404,"modifiedTime":1781557623404,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"BFkM7b0G1BkFToEC","name":"Enar","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"p4YtlbppoEbRaC1P","name":"Enar - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Enar","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an immortal being, the result of all the \nhatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss. I have the \nstrength of five men and my body feels no pain.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","positive":"I am an immortal being, the result of all the \nhatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss. I have the \nstrength of five men and my body feels no pain.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Enar","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fNvsqvaDqGYrXerL","name":"Gift - The Eternal Soldier","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Enar","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Enar’s body is the result of \npowerful magic tainted by hatred. When Enar suffers his \nfinal Wound, his body becomes seawater and soaks into \nthe ground. The following day, Enar completely regenerates \nhimself at the bottom of the sea, where his heart is, the very \nfocus of his existence. Only by recovering the heart and \ndestroying it can Enar be permanently eliminated.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Enar","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"poLwfRSaxSNBJ325","name":"Gift - Rage of the Sea","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Enar","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the magic granted by \nthe Sea Fairy, Enar has gained powers. When he acts, he \ncan always choose an additional effect. 1. Algae Whip: A \nstring of algae stretches from Enar’s body and can perform \na second independent action. 2. Wave: Enar’s body \nbecomes seawater for a few moments, allowing him to slip \naway and cover a distance of 30 feet before regrouping. \n3. Shells: 3 large seashells are shot from Enar’s body in \ndifferent directions, which should be considered 3 attacks</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Enar","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4I2r81jISUb8XfrK","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Enar","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an immortal being, the result of all the \nhatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss. I have the \nstrength of five men and my body feels no pain.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Andersen, but not before I have \neliminated all my former companions / After eliminating \nAndersen and his people, I want to meld with Satu so that \nour bodies and souls are united for eternity.\nGift - The Eternal Soldier: Enar’s body is the result of \npowerful magic tainted by hatred. When Enar suffers his \nfinal Wound, his body becomes seawater and soaks into \nthe ground. The following day, Enar completely regenerates \nhimself at the bottom of the sea, where his heart is, the very \nfocus of his existence. Only by recovering the heart and \ndestroying it can Enar be permanently eliminated. \nGift - Rage of the Sea: Thanks to the magic granted by \nthe Sea Fairy, Enar has gained powers. When he acts, he \ncan always choose an additional effect. 1. Algae Whip: A \nstring of algae stretches from Enar’s body and can perform \na second independent action. 2. Wave: Enar’s body \nbecomes seawater for a few moments, allowing him to slip \naway and cover a distance of 30 feet before regrouping. \n3. Shells: 3 large seashells are shot from Enar’s body in \ndifferent directions, which should be considered 3 attacks</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","owner":"Enar","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-enar-162","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":162,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an immortal being, the result of all the \nhatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss. I have the \nstrength of five men and my body feels no pain.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Andersen, but not before I have \neliminated all my former companions / After eliminating \nAndersen and his people, I want to meld with Satu so that \nour bodies and souls are united for eternity.\nGift - The Eternal Soldier: Enar’s body is the result of \npowerful magic tainted by hatred. When Enar suffers his \nfinal Wound, his body becomes seawater and soaks into \nthe ground. The following day, Enar completely regenerates \nhimself at the bottom of the sea, where his heart is, the very \nfocus of his existence. Only by recovering the heart and \ndestroying it can Enar be permanently eliminated. \nGift - Rage of the Sea: Thanks to the magic granted by \nthe Sea Fairy, Enar has gained powers. When he acts, he \ncan always choose an additional effect. 1. Algae Whip: A \nstring of algae stretches from Enar’s body and can perform \na second independent action. 2. Wave: Enar’s body \nbecomes seawater for a few moments, allowing him to slip \naway and cover a distance of 30 feet before regrouping. \n3. Shells: 3 large seashells are shot from Enar’s body in \ndifferent directions, which should be considered 3 attacks</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Take revenge on Andersen, but not before I have \neliminated all my former companions / After eliminating \nAndersen and his people, I want to meld with Satu so that \nour bodies and souls are united for eternity.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Btz7XLc4f1jmofVA","name":"Margareta the Good Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"wGpakceWbe7aioZb","name":"Margareta the Good Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta the Good Witch","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a capable witch who has devoted her life to \ncaring for the unfortunate. My body is wracked with disease, \nbut that doesn’t make me any less fearsome.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 227.","positive":"I am a capable witch who has devoted her life to \ncaring for the unfortunate. My body is wracked with disease, \nbut that doesn’t make me any less fearsome.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Margareta the Good Witch","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624294,"modifiedTime":1781557624294,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"IShv8JH6N23hdf7x","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta the Good Witch","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a capable witch who has devoted her life to \ncaring for the unfortunate. My body is wracked with disease, \nbut that doesn’t make me any less fearsome.\nAgenda: Keep Gelb and everyone who lives there safe.\nGift - Witch: Margareta can draw on her witch power \nto create a Descriptor to represent the effect of her magic. \nHer abilities are related to manipulating emotions, such as \ninstilling fear or bestowing calm. The Descriptor thus created \nremains for the entire duration of a Scene. Alternatively, \nMargareta can move objects with the power of thought. These \nabilities can be used to hit someone from a distance, knock \nobjects out of someone’s hand, and generally manipulate the \nenvironment.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 227.","owner":"Margareta the Good Witch","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624294,"modifiedTime":1781557624294,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-margareta-the-good-witch-227","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":227,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a capable witch who has devoted her life to \ncaring for the unfortunate. My body is wracked with disease, \nbut that doesn’t make me any less fearsome.\nAgenda: Keep Gelb and everyone who lives there safe.\nGift - Witch: Margareta can draw on her witch power \nto create a Descriptor to represent the effect of her magic. \nHer abilities are related to manipulating emotions, such as \ninstilling fear or bestowing calm. The Descriptor thus created \nremains for the entire duration of a Scene. Alternatively, \nMargareta can move objects with the power of thought. These \nabilities can be used to hit someone from a distance, knock \nobjects out of someone’s hand, and generally manipulate the \nenvironment.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Keep Gelb and everyone who lives there safe.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624294,"modifiedTime":1781557624294,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Cfak53LI1UqEmQJH","name":"Amabile Burromo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"7ajV7A1ga746hMwX","name":"Amabile Burromo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Amabile Burromo","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled business owner \nand I manage my inn without delegating \nanything to anyone. I trust myself only.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","positive":"I am a skilled business owner \nand I manage my inn without delegating \nanything to anyone. I trust myself only.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Amabile Burromo","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"cwE3pteHfw4PR8LS","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Amabile Burromo","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled business owner \nand I manage my inn without delegating \nanything to anyone. I trust myself only.\nAgenda: To make profitable deals, \nwithout worrying about scruples.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","owner":"Amabile Burromo","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-amabile-burromo-137","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":137,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled business owner \nand I manage my inn without delegating \nanything to anyone. I trust myself only.\nAgenda: To make profitable deals, \nwithout worrying about scruples.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To make profitable deals, \nwithout worrying about scruples.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"D3HmPhY5jdaqUYvt","name":"(Opponent Dark Presence)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"DWnIPJzaFxnRNcOA","name":"(Opponent Dark Presence) - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"(Opponent Dark Presence)","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>That of the original NPC.</p>","notes":"One Thousand and One Nightmares - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 198.","positive":"That of the original NPC.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"(Opponent Dark Presence)","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623612,"modifiedTime":1781557623612,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2bHSngfzxoGu139F","name":"Gift - Variable","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"(Opponent Dark Presence)","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Shadow has all the Gifts of the \noriginal NPC.</p>","notes":"One Thousand and One Nightmares - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 198.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"(Opponent Dark Presence)","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623612,"modifiedTime":1781557623612,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HWVcBdogIIJiQcNC","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"(Opponent Dark Presence)","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: That of the original NPC.\nAgenda: Interfering with and impeding the path of the \nHunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their \nmission.\nGift - Variable: The Shadow has all the Gifts of the \noriginal NPC. \nGift - Shadow Body: A Shadow is a darker, sadder \nversion of the original. They can speak and behave like \nthe character they are modelled after, but on a careful \ninspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per \nScene, a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness \nby moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When \nit spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element</p>","notes":"One Thousand and One Nightmares - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 198.","owner":"(Opponent Dark Presence)","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623612,"modifiedTime":1781557623612,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-one-thousand-and-one-nightmares-opponent-dark-presence-198","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","adventureTitle":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":198,"role":"Scenario Actor"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","origin":"Core Book","role":"Scenario Actor","notes":"<p>– (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: That of the original NPC.\nAgenda: Interfering with and impeding the path of the \nHunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their \nmission.\nGift - Variable: The Shadow has all the Gifts of the \noriginal NPC. \nGift - Shadow Body: A Shadow is a darker, sadder \nversion of the original. They can speak and behave like \nthe character they are modelled after, but on a careful \ninspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per \nScene, a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness \nby moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When \nit spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Interfering with and impeding the path of the \nHunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their \nmission.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623612,"modifiedTime":1781557623612,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DWsYtsKilMiq8I2d","name":"Helga the Red Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"iSy9ZLS9bPI3YnKJ","name":"Helga the Red Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helga the Red Witch","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a powerful witch and I use blood to \nperform my spells. Drinking one drop of my blood is enough \nto become my slave.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 236.","positive":"I am a powerful witch and I use blood to \nperform my spells. Drinking one drop of my blood is enough \nto become my slave.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Helga the Red Witch","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624545,"modifiedTime":1781557624545,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"d5ci0tvR0DF44rTQ","name":"Gift - Blood Magic","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helga the Red Witch","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Helga can unleash her powers to \naffect the blood of one or more subjects, inflicting 1 Wound \nor commanding their movements. Whoever has swallowed \nHelga’s blood is totally subject to her will. It is possible to \nresist the effects of Blood Magic with a Defense Check, \nbut this does not eliminate Helga’s magic. Drinking the \nInfusion of Purity renders anyone immune to Blood Magic \nfor the course of a Scene and cancels the crowd control. \nThose under the influence of the Blood Magic have a slight \ncrimson tinge to their eyes.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 236.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Helga the Red Witch","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624545,"modifiedTime":1781557624545,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mMLFY0AsWIpsTaHk","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helga the Red Witch","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful witch and I use blood to \nperform my spells. Drinking one drop of my blood is enough \nto become my slave.\nAgenda: Accumulating power and collecting the four pieces \nof the Compass Rose thanks to the information obtained \nfrom OZena’s sacrifice / I am always willing to make an \nadvantageous deal, even if this leads me to revise my plans. I \nwould do anything to live forever.\nGift - Blood Magic: Helga can unleash her powers to \naffect the blood of one or more subjects, inflicting 1 Wound \nor commanding their movements. Whoever has swallowed \nHelga’s blood is totally subject to her will. It is possible to \nresist the effects of Blood Magic with a Defense Check, \nbut this does not eliminate Helga’s magic. Drinking the \nInfusion of Purity renders anyone immune to Blood Magic \nfor the course of a Scene and cancels the crowd control. \nThose under the influence of the Blood Magic have a slight \ncrimson tinge to their eyes.\nGift - Blood Witch: Helga is made young and immortal \nby blood magic. At the end of each of her actions and if hurt,</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 236.","owner":"Helga the Red Witch","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624545,"modifiedTime":1781557624545,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-helga-the-red-witch-236","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":236,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful witch and I use blood to \nperform my spells. Drinking one drop of my blood is enough \nto become my slave.\nAgenda: Accumulating power and collecting the four pieces \nof the Compass Rose thanks to the information obtained \nfrom OZena’s sacrifice / I am always willing to make an \nadvantageous deal, even if this leads me to revise my plans. I \nwould do anything to live forever.\nGift - Blood Magic: Helga can unleash her powers to \naffect the blood of one or more subjects, inflicting 1 Wound \nor commanding their movements. Whoever has swallowed \nHelga’s blood is totally subject to her will. It is possible to \nresist the effects of Blood Magic with a Defense Check, \nbut this does not eliminate Helga’s magic. Drinking the \nInfusion of Purity renders anyone immune to Blood Magic \nfor the course of a Scene and cancels the crowd control. \nThose under the influence of the Blood Magic have a slight \ncrimson tinge to their eyes.\nGift - Blood Witch: Helga is made young and immortal \nby blood magic. At the end of each of her actions and if hurt,</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Accumulating power and collecting the four pieces \nof the Compass Rose thanks to the information obtained \nfrom OZena’s sacrifice / I am always willing to make an \nadvantageous deal, even if this leads me to revise my plans. I \nwould do anything to live forever.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624545,"modifiedTime":1781557624545,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Detkbj4ut9gjHrSo","name":"Manycorpses","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"BQbR52xfvrQW6BDl","name":"Manycorpses - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Manycorpses","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an abomination created by Helga’s \nexperiments, in which she has united all her lovers into one. \nI hate anyone who still has a normal body and I use my \nincredible power to destroy them.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 234.","positive":"I am an abomination created by Helga’s \nexperiments, in which she has united all her lovers into one. \nI hate anyone who still has a normal body and I use my \nincredible power to destroy them.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Manycorpses","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624482,"modifiedTime":1781557624482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7yDSmKI9gW884NdW","name":"Gift - Aberration","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Manycorpses","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Manycorpses can act twice during an \nExchange. Thanks to its multiple arms it can move on any \nsurface.\nEnd of Scene: After being freed, the greenhouse workers \nreveal that Helga is able to control people’s bodies with her \nblood magic. Something called the Infusion of Purity, a \npotion, can lift the curse. Helga is producing the Infusion \nbecause she plans to sell the antidote to rich and powerful \nnobles after poisoning them with her magical blood. To \ncomplete the Infusion, however, Elderberry is required, \nthough the ingredient does not grow in this area. A strange \ngirl in a green cape has stolen the small stash Helga had \nbrought back from her last trip.\nGo to the THIRD SCENE - The Dolls’ Court.\nTHIRD SCENE – The Dolls’ \nCourt\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You come to a bleak, \ndilapidated village made up of small, ruined houses and \nbrightly colored tents. Men and women in an evident state of \ndistress lie sprawled along the streets. From their tired eyes, \nyou understand that they are exhausted by the incessant work \nHelga magically forces them to do. Suddenly, figures wearing \ngrotesque doll masks appear and head in your direction, \ndrawing their weapons.\nPlace: The dilapidated village of Rot.\nTime: The sun is setting, but time seems to have stopped \nin the small village.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 234.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Manycorpses","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624482,"modifiedTime":1781557624482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ALMYJuMP1hRIfDY8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Manycorpses","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an abomination created by Helga’s \nexperiments, in which she has united all her lovers into one. \nI hate anyone who still has a normal body and I use my \nincredible power to destroy them.\nAgenda: Kill and dismember any human that comes within \nrange.\nGift - Aberration: Manycorpses can act twice during an \nExchange. Thanks to its multiple arms it can move on any \nsurface.\nEnd of Scene: After being freed, the greenhouse workers \nreveal that Helga is able to control people’s bodies with her \nblood magic. Something called the Infusion of Purity, a \npotion, can lift the curse. Helga is producing the Infusion \nbecause she plans to sell the antidote to rich and powerful \nnobles after poisoning them with her magical blood. To \ncomplete the Infusion, however, Elderberry is required, \nthough the ingredient does not grow in this area. A strange \ngirl in a green cape has stolen the small stash Helga had \nbrought back from her last trip.\nGo to the THIRD SCENE - The Dolls’ Court.\nTHIRD SCENE – The Dolls’ \nCourt\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You come to a bleak, \ndilapidated village made up of small, ruined houses and \nbrightly colored tents. Men and women in an evident state of \ndistress lie sprawled along the streets. From their tired eyes, \nyou understand that they are exhausted by the incessant work \nHelga magically forces them to do. Suddenly, figures wearing \ngrotesque doll masks appear and head in your direction, \ndrawing their weapons.\nPlace: The dilapidated village of Rot.\nTime: The sun is setting, but time seems to have stopped \nin the small village.\nInformation:\n ◆ The Porcelain Dolls are the only individuals worth \ntalking to. They will initially have their guard up, but if \nthe Hunters are convincing, they will be brought to the \nPorcelain Princess.\n ◆ The village is just an old, dilapidated logging settlement. \nNot far away, it is possible to see a noble’s mansion \nwhere Helga now resides.\n ◆ No one can come before Helga without the approval of \nthe Porcelain Princess, her favorite.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 234.","owner":"Manycorpses","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624482,"modifiedTime":1781557624482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-manycorpses-234","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":234,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an abomination created by Helga’s \nexperiments, in which she has united all her lovers into one. \nI hate anyone who still has a normal body and I use my \nincredible power to destroy them.\nAgenda: Kill and dismember any human that comes within \nrange.\nGift - Aberration: Manycorpses can act twice during an \nExchange. Thanks to its multiple arms it can move on any \nsurface.\nEnd of Scene: After being freed, the greenhouse workers \nreveal that Helga is able to control people’s bodies with her \nblood magic. Something called the Infusion of Purity, a \npotion, can lift the curse. Helga is producing the Infusion \nbecause she plans to sell the antidote to rich and powerful \nnobles after poisoning them with her magical blood. To \ncomplete the Infusion, however, Elderberry is required, \nthough the ingredient does not grow in this area. A strange \ngirl in a green cape has stolen the small stash Helga had \nbrought back from her last trip.\nGo to the THIRD SCENE - The Dolls’ Court.\nTHIRD SCENE – The Dolls’ \nCourt\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You come to a bleak, \ndilapidated village made up of small, ruined houses and \nbrightly colored tents. Men and women in an evident state of \ndistress lie sprawled along the streets. From their tired eyes, \nyou understand that they are exhausted by the incessant work \nHelga magically forces them to do. Suddenly, figures wearing \ngrotesque doll masks appear and head in your direction, \ndrawing their weapons.\nPlace: The dilapidated village of Rot.\nTime: The sun is setting, but time seems to have stopped \nin the small village.\nInformation:\n ◆ The Porcelain Dolls are the only individuals worth \ntalking to. They will initially have their guard up, but if \nthe Hunters are convincing, they will be brought to the \nPorcelain Princess.\n ◆ The village is just an old, dilapidated logging settlement. \nNot far away, it is possible to see a noble’s mansion \nwhere Helga now resides.\n ◆ No one can come before Helga without the approval of \nthe Porcelain Princess, her favorite.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Kill and dismember any human that comes within \nrange.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624482,"modifiedTime":1781557624482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DpAvVdabWtuttDlW","name":"The God Under the Mine","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"T1fDQhyfDe2jRqiV","name":"The God Under the Mine - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The God Under the Mine","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a creature as old as the world, trapped \nbeneath the bedrock. Millennia of inactivity have made me \ncatatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up. \nOnly pain can stir me even slightly.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","positive":"I am a creature as old as the world, trapped \nbeneath the bedrock. Millennia of inactivity have made me \ncatatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up. \nOnly pain can stir me even slightly.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The God Under the Mine","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"NRcWzz44W5k7lex4","name":"Gift - The Head of the God","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The God Under the Mine","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Only the enormous head of \nthe God emerges from the rock, and pieces of meat can be \nobtained from it. When he suffers 1 Wound, the God emits \na loud grunt that sends everyone flying (a Defense Check \ncan avoid this). As an additional effect of the grunt, the \nGod’s fetid breath taints the air, granting 1 Penalty to the \nnext action of all affected subjects, excluding Arthur. When \nreduced to 0 Wounds, the God falls into a deep sleep to \nfully regenerate in the following Scene.\nSpawn of The God Under the \nMine</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The God Under the Mine","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WrILwwQwACeD1Qzp","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The God Under the Mine","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a creature as old as the world, trapped \nbeneath the bedrock. Millennia of inactivity have made me \ncatatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up. \nOnly pain can stir me even slightly.\nGift - The Head of the God: Only the enormous head of \nthe God emerges from the rock, and pieces of meat can be \nobtained from it. When he suffers 1 Wound, the God emits \na loud grunt that sends everyone flying (a Defense Check \ncan avoid this). As an additional effect of the grunt, the \nGod’s fetid breath taints the air, granting 1 Penalty to the \nnext action of all affected subjects, excluding Arthur. When \nreduced to 0 Wounds, the God falls into a deep sleep to \nfully regenerate in the following Scene.\nSpawn of The God Under the \nMine</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","owner":"The God Under the Mine","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-the-god-under-the-mine-212","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":212,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a creature as old as the world, trapped \nbeneath the bedrock. Millennia of inactivity have made me \ncatatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up. \nOnly pain can stir me even slightly.\nGift - The Head of the God: Only the enormous head of \nthe God emerges from the rock, and pieces of meat can be \nobtained from it. When he suffers 1 Wound, the God emits \na loud grunt that sends everyone flying (a Defense Check \ncan avoid this). As an additional effect of the grunt, the \nGod’s fetid breath taints the air, granting 1 Penalty to the \nnext action of all affected subjects, excluding Arthur. When \nreduced to 0 Wounds, the God falls into a deep sleep to \nfully regenerate in the following Scene.\nSpawn of The God Under the \nMine</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"E0CCV33Xx42RXLZj","name":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"a1ukQAzwrX61MYWD","name":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of \nmy granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow \nme to communicate with the living except through dreams, \nwhispers, and visions.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 125.","positive":"I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of \nmy granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow \nme to communicate with the living except through dreams, \nwhispers, and visions.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621392,"modifiedTime":1781557621392,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8sOWyUG4gYVgCtI3","name":"Gift - Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Anastazia is a spirit and can only be damaged \nby magic. She may appear in a dream to a target, who may \nresist with a Defense Check or accept contact voluntarily. \nThe target suffers 1 Wound from stress but will receive from \nAnastazia a vision of a present or past event with a barely \nwhispered phrase.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 125.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621392,"modifiedTime":1781557621392,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jXH4WZxHDJbfkm6x","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of \nmy granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow \nme to communicate with the living except through dreams, \nwhispers, and visions.\nAgenda: Preventing further harm to Iskra and find a way to \nsave my granddaughter’s soul.\nGift - Spirit: Anastazia is a spirit and can only be damaged \nby magic. She may appear in a dream to a target, who may \nresist with a Defense Check or accept contact voluntarily. \nThe target suffers 1 Wound from stress but will receive from \nAnastazia a vision of a present or past event with a barely \nwhispered phrase.\nGift - Loving Grandmother: Anastazia always follows \nIskra and protects her from danger. Thanks to her strong \nwill, she can interact with the material world by moving \nobjects and manipulating the environment, even inflicting \na Wound on a target. If a subject is likely to help save her \ngranddaughter, Anastazia will simply fill their mind with \nmemories of her.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 125.","owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621392,"modifiedTime":1781557621392,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-anastazia-the-sorrowful-spirit-125","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":125,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of \nmy granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow \nme to communicate with the living except through dreams, \nwhispers, and visions.\nAgenda: Preventing further harm to Iskra and find a way to \nsave my granddaughter’s soul.\nGift - Spirit: Anastazia is a spirit and can only be damaged \nby magic. She may appear in a dream to a target, who may \nresist with a Defense Check or accept contact voluntarily. \nThe target suffers 1 Wound from stress but will receive from \nAnastazia a vision of a present or past event with a barely \nwhispered phrase.\nGift - Loving Grandmother: Anastazia always follows \nIskra and protects her from danger. Thanks to her strong \nwill, she can interact with the material world by moving \nobjects and manipulating the environment, even inflicting \na Wound on a target. If a subject is likely to help save her \ngranddaughter, Anastazia will simply fill their mind with \nmemories of her.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Preventing further harm to Iskra and find a way to \nsave my granddaughter’s soul.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621392,"modifiedTime":1781557621392,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ElolsV3Y4uWwYuCU","name":"Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who Spurns Death","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"SrRcobNcHPZfkxyv","name":"Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who Spurns Death - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who Spurns Death","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow \nme to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 139.","positive":"I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow \nme to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who Spurns Death","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621905,"modifiedTime":1781557621905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XDnhwPucDqNLPHmJ","name":"Gift - Ancient Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who Spurns Death","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Azzurra’s body is immaterial and can only be \ndamaged by magic. Azzurra can interact with the world by evoking the souls \nof the dead, choosing between various effects. 1. Poltergeist: Throw up to \n3 objects at once. The force with which the objects are thrown is such that \nthey can cause a Wound. 2. Cacophony of the Dead: Frighten everyone \nwith the agonized voices of the damned. Anyone who hears the cacophony \nmust pass a Defense Check or lose 2 Soma points. 3. Possession: Take \npossession of a target’s body and cause them to perform a single action, \nalbeit not a self-destructive one. Azzurra must change the spirits’ effect with \neach action and must use all three before she can use an effect again.\nThe Secret Laboratory</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 139.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who Spurns Death","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621905,"modifiedTime":1781557621905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dYHYrz7fLsEe8AYQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who Spurns Death","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow \nme to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will. \nAgenda: To come back to life thanks to Carlo’s power.\nGift - Ancient Spirit: Azzurra’s body is immaterial and can only be \ndamaged by magic. Azzurra can interact with the world by evoking the souls \nof the dead, choosing between various effects. 1. Poltergeist: Throw up to \n3 objects at once. The force with which the objects are thrown is such that \nthey can cause a Wound. 2. Cacophony of the Dead: Frighten everyone \nwith the agonized voices of the damned. Anyone who hears the cacophony \nmust pass a Defense Check or lose 2 Soma points. 3. Possession: Take \npossession of a target’s body and cause them to perform a single action, \nalbeit not a self-destructive one. Azzurra must change the spirits’ effect with \neach action and must use all three before she can use an effect again.\nThe Secret Laboratory\nDescriptor: The cellar of Villa Cilesterino, converted into an alchemical \nlaboratory by Antonio. The smell of wine and mold is unbearable.\nInformation: \n ◆ Antonio continues his research under Azzurra’s guidance. This led him \nto create a magical brazier in which Carlo is to be burned.\n ◆ Nino, the carpenter’s apprentice, is tied to a table, alive but with his legs \nnow ruined by Antonio’s slow flaying. Azzurra wants him kept alive, as \nshe needs innocent blood for the rite.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 139.","owner":"Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who Spurns Death","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621905,"modifiedTime":1781557621905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-azzurra-the-spirit-of-the-witch-who-spurns-death-139","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":139,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow \nme to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will. \nAgenda: To come back to life thanks to Carlo’s power.\nGift - Ancient Spirit: Azzurra’s body is immaterial and can only be \ndamaged by magic. Azzurra can interact with the world by evoking the souls \nof the dead, choosing between various effects. 1. Poltergeist: Throw up to \n3 objects at once. The force with which the objects are thrown is such that \nthey can cause a Wound. 2. Cacophony of the Dead: Frighten everyone \nwith the agonized voices of the damned. Anyone who hears the cacophony \nmust pass a Defense Check or lose 2 Soma points. 3. Possession: Take \npossession of a target’s body and cause them to perform a single action, \nalbeit not a self-destructive one. Azzurra must change the spirits’ effect with \neach action and must use all three before she can use an effect again.\nThe Secret Laboratory\nDescriptor: The cellar of Villa Cilesterino, converted into an alchemical \nlaboratory by Antonio. The smell of wine and mold is unbearable.\nInformation: \n ◆ Antonio continues his research under Azzurra’s guidance. This led him \nto create a magical brazier in which Carlo is to be burned.\n ◆ Nino, the carpenter’s apprentice, is tied to a table, alive but with his legs \nnow ruined by Antonio’s slow flaying. Azzurra wants him kept alive, as \nshe needs innocent blood for the rite.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"To come back to life thanks to Carlo’s power.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621905,"modifiedTime":1781557621905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FQS2dO9SA5cYIOWc","name":"Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"v95tXvsxGrY3uyZI","name":"Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms \nabout doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life \nwithout working so hard.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","positive":"I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms \nabout doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life \nwithout working so hard.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RrMHx8oa7VIHM70J","name":"Gift - Veteran","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Vincent is skilled in taking advantage \nof any situation. When he has the support of at least two \nof his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty \nand Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.\nThe Guards of Gerard Dubois</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PMpGXwATE0dUsgGb","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms \nabout doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life \nwithout working so hard.\nAgenda: I understand how the world works and who \nreally runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the \nbest way to maintain my status.\nGift - Veteran: Vincent is skilled in taking advantage \nof any situation. When he has the support of at least two \nof his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty \nand Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.\nThe Guards of Gerard Dubois</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","owner":"Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-vincent-arn-former-huntsman-and-chief-of-the-guards-122","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":122,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms \nabout doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life \nwithout working so hard.\nAgenda: I understand how the world works and who \nreally runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the \nbest way to maintain my status.\nGift - Veteran: Vincent is skilled in taking advantage \nof any situation. When he has the support of at least two \nof his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty \nand Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.\nThe Guards of Gerard Dubois</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I understand how the world works and who \nreally runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the \nbest way to maintain my status.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"HHmItq1p1RhFzMao","name":"The Pit","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"z5RaTnxhez1ijT4v","name":"The Pit - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pit","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A large, deep pit with strangely smooth walls.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters cross the pit to enter the \nvillage of Smaragd. Go to SECOND SCENE - The Emerald \nVillage.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nEmerald Village\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Once you cross the Pit you \nfind yourself in a small village of houses, built amongst the \ntrees. It only takes a few steps to understand that something \nis wrong. You feel disoriented and it is difficult for you to keep \ntrack of which direction you are moving. The small village \nnow looks like a labyrinth, huge and intricate.\nPlace: The small village of Smaragd which, by a wish \nmade by Henkle, appears as an infinite labyrinth.\nTime: It is impossible to mark the passage of time \nas day and night alternate every minute.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 240.","positive":"A large, deep pit with strangely smooth walls.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters cross the pit to enter the \nvillage of Smaragd. Go to SECOND SCENE - The Emerald \nVillage.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nEmerald Village\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Once you cross the Pit you \nfind yourself in a small village of houses, built amongst the \ntrees. It only takes a few steps to understand that something \nis wrong. You feel disoriented and it is difficult for you to keep \ntrack of which direction you are moving. The small village \nnow looks like a labyrinth, huge and intricate.\nPlace: The small village of Smaragd which, by a wish \nmade by Henkle, appears as an infinite labyrinth.\nTime: It is impossible to mark the passage of time \nas day and night alternate every minute.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Pit","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624653,"modifiedTime":1781557624653,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mmsayvOVDnwN1RQX","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pit","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A large, deep pit with strangely smooth walls.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters cross the pit to enter the \nvillage of Smaragd. Go to SECOND SCENE - The Emerald \nVillage.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nEmerald Village\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Once you cross the Pit you \nfind yourself in a small village of houses, built amongst the \ntrees. It only takes a few steps to understand that something \nis wrong. You feel disoriented and it is difficult for you to keep \ntrack of which direction you are moving. The small village \nnow looks like a labyrinth, huge and intricate.\nPlace: The small village of Smaragd which, by a wish \nmade by Henkle, appears as an infinite labyrinth.\nTime: It is impossible to mark the passage of time \nas day and night alternate every minute.\nInformation: Henkle’s plan is \nto waste the Hunters’ time and \nprevent them from getting to \nthe center of the village. For \nthis he has deployed some \nsubordinates to set up an \nambush. Choose one of the following:\n ◆ Hirnloser will plan an ambush with the help of 4 \nVillagers. He and his men can move freely without \nbeing affected by the Illusory Labyrinth Threat. \n ◆ Lowe will go to meet the Hunters to challenge them \nin the open field, bringing with him 3 Villagers and 3 \nCanine Tigers. \n ◆ Dose will very simply attack the Hunters as soon as \nthey enter the village.\n ◆ 4 Villagers with 4 Canine Tigers\nThreat - Illusory Labyrinth</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 240.","owner":"The Pit","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624653,"modifiedTime":1781557624653,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-pit-240","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":240,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A large, deep pit with strangely smooth walls.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters cross the pit to enter the \nvillage of Smaragd. Go to SECOND SCENE - The Emerald \nVillage.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nEmerald Village\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Once you cross the Pit you \nfind yourself in a small village of houses, built amongst the \ntrees. It only takes a few steps to understand that something \nis wrong. You feel disoriented and it is difficult for you to keep \ntrack of which direction you are moving. The small village \nnow looks like a labyrinth, huge and intricate.\nPlace: The small village of Smaragd which, by a wish \nmade by Henkle, appears as an infinite labyrinth.\nTime: It is impossible to mark the passage of time \nas day and night alternate every minute.\nInformation: Henkle’s plan is \nto waste the Hunters’ time and \nprevent them from getting to \nthe center of the village. For \nthis he has deployed some \nsubordinates to set up an \nambush. Choose one of the following:\n ◆ Hirnloser will plan an ambush with the help of 4 \nVillagers. He and his men can move freely without \nbeing affected by the Illusory Labyrinth Threat. \n ◆ Lowe will go to meet the Hunters to challenge them \nin the open field, bringing with him 3 Villagers and 3 \nCanine Tigers. \n ◆ Dose will very simply attack the Hunters as soon as \nthey enter the village.\n ◆ 4 Villagers with 4 Canine Tigers\nThreat - Illusory Labyrinth</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624653,"modifiedTime":1781557624653,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JMt67EgMsl4dvVUJ","name":"Klaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"jBSFpFwupuP1fZMR","name":"Klaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Klaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a curious child. I \nlove foreigners because they always have \ninteresting stories to tell. I know I have a \ndreadful disease, but I have learned to live \nwith it.\nLowe the Coward \nHenchman</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226.","positive":"I am a curious child. I \nlove foreigners because they always have \ninteresting stories to tell. I know I have a \ndreadful disease, but I have learned to live \nwith it.\nLowe the Coward \nHenchman","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Klaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dKIQOcv1hWWk1baa","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Klaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a curious child. I \nlove foreigners because they always have \ninteresting stories to tell. I know I have a \ndreadful disease, but I have learned to live \nwith it.\nLowe the Coward \nHenchman</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226.","owner":"Klaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-klaus-the-ozenaafflicted-son-226","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":226,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a curious child. I \nlove foreigners because they always have \ninteresting stories to tell. I know I have a \ndreadful disease, but I have learned to live \nwith it.\nLowe the Coward \nHenchman</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JPr8cLMqBrQHzmhB","name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"XarDEFr8OHyOEq6P","name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I became a proud warrior and realized my \nheroic potential. I never back down and set an example for \nmy teammates.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 241.","positive":"I became a proud warrior and realized my \nheroic potential. I never back down and set an example for \nmy teammates.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DXtNFEDukU7qQSUA","name":"Gift - Hero","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Lowe fears nothing and is immune to all forms \nof fear and magical control. After he acts, his allies receive \n+1 to their OL, inspired by their hero’s courage and words.\nHirnloser the Genius</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 241.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3b3Mr4TSam2oSydk","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I became a proud warrior and realized my \nheroic potential. I never back down and set an example for \nmy teammates.\nAgenda: Stop the invaders and protect the village of \nSmaragd, which has elected me as its hero.\nGift - Hero: Lowe fears nothing and is immune to all forms \nof fear and magical control. After he acts, his allies receive \n+1 to their OL, inspired by their hero’s courage and words.\nHirnloser the Genius</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 241.","owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-lowe-the-brave-fighter-241","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":241,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I became a proud warrior and realized my \nheroic potential. I never back down and set an example for \nmy teammates.\nAgenda: Stop the invaders and protect the village of \nSmaragd, which has elected me as its hero.\nGift - Hero: Lowe fears nothing and is immune to all forms \nof fear and magical control. After he acts, his allies receive \n+1 to their OL, inspired by their hero’s courage and words.\nHirnloser the Genius</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Stop the invaders and protect the village of \nSmaragd, which has elected me as its hero.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"K0MVDKEVocgRC3SI","name":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"q41RDhevGL5JMsXu","name":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the youngest of the Pig Heads and, despite \nbelieving in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on \nit. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back \nof my hand.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 209.","positive":"I am the youngest of the Pig Heads and, despite \nbelieving in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on \nit. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back \nof my hand.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623863,"modifiedTime":1781557623863,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0TxjhyOyoLzhCOa9","name":"Gift - Slacker","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Clarence is a master of the art of \ndisappearing when things get tough. In the presence of \neven a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it \nis his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able \nto stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the \norchard, passing the entire following Scene there.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 209.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623863,"modifiedTime":1781557623863,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Gxy4v8zD6uaJmTB1","name":"Gift - Gang Leader","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe \nSlaughterhouse</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 209.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623863,"modifiedTime":1781557623863,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WZj7yovcrBd5hbSg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the youngest of the Pig Heads and, despite \nbelieving in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on \nit. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back \nof my hand.\nAgenda: Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on \nthe Pig Head’s cause in my spare time.\nGift - Slacker: Clarence is a master of the art of \ndisappearing when things get tough. In the presence of \neven a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it \nis his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able \nto stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the \norchard, passing the entire following Scene there. \nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe \nSlaughterhouse\nDescriptor: A huge gray building inside which cattle from \ncoastal pastures are slaughtered. Entry is forbidden to nonworkers.\nWhen the Hunters wander around the slaughterhouse, roll \n1 die to see how far they go without attracting attention, or \npresent the environments in sequence.\n1-2 The outdoor garden: It is more an open-air barn \nthan a garden patch. Bloodstains and excrement suggest \nthat the slaughter starts here. Several signs reading “No \nTrespassing” suggest that the area is very controlled.\n3-4 The slaughterhouse: Composed of a series of large \nspaces, several stairs lead to underground chambers where \nthe meat is preserved. Around ten workers are present day \nand night, all members of the Pig Heads.\n5-6 The salting room: A small room at the back of the \nbuilding, where Frank prepares the meat that will be served \nin the cafeterias throughout the city. During the day Frank \nis always present, intent on hiding the flesh of the God \nwithin freshly butchered beef.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 209.","owner":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623863,"modifiedTime":1781557623863,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-clarence-browne-the-younger-brother-209","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":209,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the youngest of the Pig Heads and, despite \nbelieving in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on \nit. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back \nof my hand.\nAgenda: Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on \nthe Pig Head’s cause in my spare time.\nGift - Slacker: Clarence is a master of the art of \ndisappearing when things get tough. In the presence of \neven a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it \nis his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able \nto stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the \norchard, passing the entire following Scene there. \nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe \nSlaughterhouse\nDescriptor: A huge gray building inside which cattle from \ncoastal pastures are slaughtered. Entry is forbidden to nonworkers.\nWhen the Hunters wander around the slaughterhouse, roll \n1 die to see how far they go without attracting attention, or \npresent the environments in sequence.\n1-2 The outdoor garden: It is more an open-air barn \nthan a garden patch. Bloodstains and excrement suggest \nthat the slaughter starts here. Several signs reading “No \nTrespassing” suggest that the area is very controlled.\n3-4 The slaughterhouse: Composed of a series of large \nspaces, several stairs lead to underground chambers where \nthe meat is preserved. Around ten workers are present day \nand night, all members of the Pig Heads.\n5-6 The salting room: A small room at the back of the \nbuilding, where Frank prepares the meat that will be served \nin the cafeterias throughout the city. During the day Frank \nis always present, intent on hiding the flesh of the God \nwithin freshly butchered beef.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on \nthe Pig Head’s cause in my spare time.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623863,"modifiedTime":1781557623863,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"KWoLr1i1hSqmDhNk","name":"William the Man of Law","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"wDWrLo0TzhXzdnzH","name":"William the Man of Law - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"William the Man of Law","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a prominent lawyer and I know all of \nBardolf ’s secrets. I manage the accounts of both the Factories \nand mine with zealous attention.\nBardolf’s personal \nguard</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 206.","positive":"I am a prominent lawyer and I know all of \nBardolf ’s secrets. I manage the accounts of both the Factories \nand mine with zealous attention.\nBardolf’s personal \nguard","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"William the Man of Law","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623800,"modifiedTime":1781557623800,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"C3DU9ltsDxY1b3oI","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"William the Man of Law","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a prominent lawyer and I know all of \nBardolf ’s secrets. I manage the accounts of both the Factories \nand mine with zealous attention.\nBardolf’s personal \nguard</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 206.","owner":"William the Man of Law","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource