{"_id":"L9r3JRVmEPxUi8wO","name":"Wolfgang the “druid”","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"eBanm21tX0zmGDT3","name":"Wolfgang the “druid” - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Wolfgang the “druid”","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled and renowned pharmacist, and \nthere is no herb or remedy that I am not familiar with.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 233.","positive":"I am a skilled and renowned pharmacist, and \nthere is no herb or remedy that I am not familiar with.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Wolfgang the “druid”","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"j51raFRuI37xzO11","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Wolfgang the “druid”","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled and renowned pharmacist, and \nthere is no herb or remedy that I am not familiar with.\nAgenda: I am enslaved by Helga’s power. My body moves at \nher will and therefore I sprinkle drops of her blood to animate \nthe forest to capture potential intruders.\nEnd of Scene: If captured, Wolfgang will reveal what \nhe knows to the Hunters. In the greenhouse, other poor \npeople like him work incessantly under Helga’s magical \ncontrol. In the village, a strange figure called the Porcelain \nPrincess ensures that no one can harm the witch. During \nthe interrogation, Wolfgang will be seized with sudden \nspasms and drown in his own blood. If Wolfgang has been \neliminated, the Hunters will simply have to choose which \nway to go.\nIf they go to the greenhouse, go to the SECOND SCENE - \nThe Greenhouse.\nIf they go to the Village go to the THIRD SCENE - The \nDoll’s Court.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nGreenhouse\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Following the path you reach \nan old manor house which has been remade as a greenhouse. \nMany men and women dressed in white, with tired and longsuffering expressions, work on small gardens. Strong smells of \nherbs and medicinal infusions fill the air.\nPlace: The greenhouse where the base for the Infusion of \nPurity is produced.\nTime: The sun is setting. \nInformation:\n ◆ Pharmacists are working on a strange potion. Those \nwho are experts in herbs will recognize the plants as \nBurdock, Nettle and Hyssop. \n ◆ If the Hunters approach the greenhouse, Manycorpses \nwill drop from the ceiling to stop the intruders.\n ◆ The Infusion of Purity cannot be completed, as the \nElderberry, which Dorothea took in her fight with \nManycorpses, is missing.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 233.","owner":"Wolfgang the “druid”","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-wolfgang-the-druid-233","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":233,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled and renowned pharmacist, and \nthere is no herb or remedy that I am not familiar with.\nAgenda: I am enslaved by Helga’s power. My body moves at \nher will and therefore I sprinkle drops of her blood to animate \nthe forest to capture potential intruders.\nEnd of Scene: If captured, Wolfgang will reveal what \nhe knows to the Hunters. In the greenhouse, other poor \npeople like him work incessantly under Helga’s magical \ncontrol. In the village, a strange figure called the Porcelain \nPrincess ensures that no one can harm the witch. During \nthe interrogation, Wolfgang will be seized with sudden \nspasms and drown in his own blood. If Wolfgang has been \neliminated, the Hunters will simply have to choose which \nway to go.\nIf they go to the greenhouse, go to the SECOND SCENE - \nThe Greenhouse.\nIf they go to the Village go to the THIRD SCENE - The \nDoll’s Court.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nGreenhouse\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Following the path you reach \nan old manor house which has been remade as a greenhouse. \nMany men and women dressed in white, with tired and longsuffering expressions, work on small gardens. Strong smells of \nherbs and medicinal infusions fill the air.\nPlace: The greenhouse where the base for the Infusion of \nPurity is produced.\nTime: The sun is setting. \nInformation:\n ◆ Pharmacists are working on a strange potion. Those \nwho are experts in herbs will recognize the plants as \nBurdock, Nettle and Hyssop. \n ◆ If the Hunters approach the greenhouse, Manycorpses \nwill drop from the ceiling to stop the intruders.\n ◆ The Infusion of Purity cannot be completed, as the \nElderberry, which Dorothea took in her fight with \nManycorpses, is missing.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"I am enslaved by Helga’s power. My body moves at \nher will and therefore I sprinkle drops of her blood to animate \nthe forest to capture potential intruders.\nEnd of Scene: If captured, Wolfgang will reveal what \nhe knows to the Hunters. In the greenhouse, other poor \npeople like him work incessantly under Helga’s magical \ncontrol. In the village, a strange figure called the Porcelain \nPrincess ensures that no one can harm the witch. During \nthe interrogation, Wolfgang will be seized with sudden \nspasms and drown in his own blood. If Wolfgang has been \neliminated, the Hunters will simply have to choose which \nway to go.\nIf they go to the greenhouse, go to the SECOND SCENE - \nThe Greenhouse.\nIf they go to the Village go to the THIRD SCENE - The \nDoll’s Court.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nGreenhouse\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Following the path you reach \nan old manor house which has been remade as a greenhouse. \nMany men and women dressed in white, with tired and longsuffering expressions, work on small gardens. Strong smells of \nherbs and medicinal infusions fill the air.\nPlace: The greenhouse where the base for the Infusion of \nPurity is produced.\nTime: The sun is setting.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"LXDBK32OYMTajXEQ","name":"Father Adrien","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ZFWbb6a08KGlnVtG","name":"Father Adrien - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Father Adrien","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young priest who chose to take holy \nvows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and \ndistillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 147.","positive":"I am a young priest who chose to take holy \nvows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and \ndistillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Father Adrien","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622202,"modifiedTime":1781557622202,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yloNsrhdekCWeqoy","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Father Adrien","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds) \nDescriptor: I am a young priest who chose to take holy \nvows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and \ndistillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life. \nAgenda: Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling \nand then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new \nworld.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 147.","owner":"Father Adrien","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622202,"modifiedTime":1781557622202,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-father-adrien-147","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":147,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds) \nDescriptor: I am a young priest who chose to take holy \nvows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and \ndistillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life. \nAgenda: Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling \nand then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new \nworld.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling \nand then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new \nworld.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622202,"modifiedTime":1781557622202,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NAiTwOPlc2sHmUsq","name":"Alice’s special tea","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"KSjYBFi4x94Gmd7y","name":"Alice’s special tea - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alice’s special tea","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A delicious tea mixed with a powerful \nsoporific.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","positive":"A delicious tea mixed with a powerful \nsoporific.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Alice’s special tea","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"iGfK99E4F0oTpV4N","name":"Gift - Sleep","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alice’s special tea","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Those who drink the tea and fail their Defense \nCheck will fall into a deep sleep for over eight hours. Only \nsuffering severe pain (equivalent to receiving 1 Wound) or \nthe use of magic can awaken a sleeping subject.\nAlice Liddell The \nDirector</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Alice’s special tea","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QUAz1FAkUpkC5DOP","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alice’s special tea","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A delicious tea mixed with a powerful \nsoporific.\nGift - Sleep: Those who drink the tea and fail their Defense \nCheck will fall into a deep sleep for over eight hours. Only \nsuffering severe pain (equivalent to receiving 1 Wound) or \nthe use of magic can awaken a sleeping subject.\nAlice Liddell The \nDirector</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","owner":"Alice’s special tea","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-alice-s-special-tea-177","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":177,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A delicious tea mixed with a powerful \nsoporific.\nGift - Sleep: Those who drink the tea and fail their Defense \nCheck will fall into a deep sleep for over eight hours. Only \nsuffering severe pain (equivalent to receiving 1 Wound) or \nthe use of magic can awaken a sleeping subject.\nAlice Liddell The \nDirector</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NJO0ISLB2IzpqpCw","name":"Restless spirits","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1mZrVsngrDdMw2ZH","name":"Restless spirits - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Restless spirits","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are restless souls and yearn for the essence \nof the living.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 151.","positive":"We are restless souls and yearn for the essence \nof the living.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Restless spirits","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622310,"modifiedTime":1781557622310,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"r3GaDz2qVqYvA6Ms","name":"Gift - Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Restless spirits","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be \ndamaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy \nand inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers \ncannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by \nnon-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, \nwhen the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and \nrematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are \nhealed, except those inflicted by magical means.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 151.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Restless spirits","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622310,"modifiedTime":1781557622310,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"v3hU1WbtNor7142g","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Restless spirits","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are restless souls and yearn for the essence \nof the living.\nAgenda: We sense Yvonne’s wrath, driving us to prey on the \nliving.\nGift - Spirit: This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be \ndamaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy \nand inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers \ncannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by \nnon-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, \nwhen the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and \nrematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are \nhealed, except those inflicted by magical means. \nInformation: If a Hunter communicates with Spirits \nthrough the Gift Voice of the Spirits, they will be able to \nlearn of Yvonne’s presence.\nThe Cemetery\nDescriptor: The great cemetery of Paris, protected by \nhigh walls and well-maintained thanks to the work of many \ncustodians. Strange noises and a strong smell of death come \nfrom the mass graves.\nInformation: The cemetery is currently under the control \nof Lorenzo Scannapecore, an Italian doctor hired by the city \nof Paris to manage the excessive number of corpses inside \nthe mass graves. Lorenzo has sent the cemetery keepers \naway with the excuse of requiring quiet for his studies. \nHowever, that was only a ruse to secretly host Alizée, a nun \nhe has fallen in love with and whom he keeps safe from the \nsevere judgment of the Church. Lorenzo’s intent is to wait \nuntil the new year to embark with his beloved towards the \nNew World.\n ◆ Speaking with Lorenzo, the Hunters can learn about \nthe dire state of the mass graves of the cemetery, which \nin fact is about to explode due to the excessive number \nof decaying corpses. Lorenzo will appear strangely \nnervous, looking wary. The man fears that the Hunters \nmay discover Alizée hidden among the tombstones.\n ◆ Lorenzo is also a good astrologer and will be able to tell \nthe Hunters about the passage of Morituris and how, \naccording to the legend, this gives power to the spirits.\n ◆ Alizée will observe the Hunters from behind some \ntombstones, trying not to be discovered. However, she \nwill always remain nearby, ready to intervene to help \nher beloved.\n ◆ Alizée will try not to reveal her abilities. When cornered, \nshe may report that the spirits are very agitated, both \ndue to the presence of a very powerful and hateful \nspirit among them, and due to the imminent passage \nof the comet.\n ◆ Strange smells and noises come from the mass graves. \nLorenzo will say that it is the dead bodies generating</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 151.","owner":"Restless spirits","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622310,"modifiedTime":1781557622310,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-restless-spirits-151","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":151,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are restless souls and yearn for the essence \nof the living.\nAgenda: We sense Yvonne’s wrath, driving us to prey on the \nliving.\nGift - Spirit: This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be \ndamaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy \nand inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers \ncannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by \nnon-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, \nwhen the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and \nrematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are \nhealed, except those inflicted by magical means. \nInformation: If a Hunter communicates with Spirits \nthrough the Gift Voice of the Spirits, they will be able to \nlearn of Yvonne’s presence.\nThe Cemetery\nDescriptor: The great cemetery of Paris, protected by \nhigh walls and well-maintained thanks to the work of many \ncustodians. Strange noises and a strong smell of death come \nfrom the mass graves.\nInformation: The cemetery is currently under the control \nof Lorenzo Scannapecore, an Italian doctor hired by the city \nof Paris to manage the excessive number of corpses inside \nthe mass graves. Lorenzo has sent the cemetery keepers \naway with the excuse of requiring quiet for his studies. \nHowever, that was only a ruse to secretly host Alizée, a nun \nhe has fallen in love with and whom he keeps safe from the \nsevere judgment of the Church. Lorenzo’s intent is to wait \nuntil the new year to embark with his beloved towards the \nNew World.\n ◆ Speaking with Lorenzo, the Hunters can learn about \nthe dire state of the mass graves of the cemetery, which \nin fact is about to explode due to the excessive number \nof decaying corpses. Lorenzo will appear strangely \nnervous, looking wary. The man fears that the Hunters \nmay discover Alizée hidden among the tombstones.\n ◆ Lorenzo is also a good astrologer and will be able to tell \nthe Hunters about the passage of Morituris and how, \naccording to the legend, this gives power to the spirits.\n ◆ Alizée will observe the Hunters from behind some \ntombstones, trying not to be discovered. However, she \nwill always remain nearby, ready to intervene to help \nher beloved.\n ◆ Alizée will try not to reveal her abilities. When cornered, \nshe may report that the spirits are very agitated, both \ndue to the presence of a very powerful and hateful \nspirit among them, and due to the imminent passage \nof the comet.\n ◆ Strange smells and noises come from the mass graves. \nLorenzo will say that it is the dead bodies generating</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"We sense Yvonne’s wrath, driving us to prey on the \nliving.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622310,"modifiedTime":1781557622310,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NNKe24tANUDNnihv","name":"The Hammerheads","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"bsin1dmqiVKZmsCW","name":"The Hammerheads - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hammerheads","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We were once a ferocious team of skilled \nmercenaries, but now we are in Helga’s service. We were \ntamed by her magic and therefore we do anything and \neverything for her.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 237.","positive":"We were once a ferocious team of skilled \nmercenaries, but now we are in Helga’s service. We were \ntamed by her magic and therefore we do anything and \neverything for her.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Hammerheads","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624561,"modifiedTime":1781557624561,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ADevsedCdLWOMINv","name":"Gift - Hammerhead Helmet","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hammerheads","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The heavy and distinctive \nHammerhead helmet opens like a flower on the shoulders \nand grants total head and chest protection, making the \nNPC immune to any Wound that can’t get past a thick layer \nof metal. An enemy can aim at the lower parts of the NPC \nto ignore the helmet. However, they receive 1 Penalty for \ntheir Check.\nOZena (Dorothea)\nDorothea’s profile is presented on page \n228, only her Agenda changes.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 237.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Hammerheads","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624561,"modifiedTime":1781557624561,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tX220RHJC1iQ2bf8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hammerheads","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We were once a ferocious team of skilled \nmercenaries, but now we are in Helga’s service. We were \ntamed by her magic and therefore we do anything and \neverything for her.\nGift - Hammerhead Helmet: The heavy and distinctive \nHammerhead helmet opens like a flower on the shoulders \nand grants total head and chest protection, making the \nNPC immune to any Wound that can’t get past a thick layer \nof metal. An enemy can aim at the lower parts of the NPC \nto ignore the helmet. However, they receive 1 Penalty for \ntheir Check.\nOZena (Dorothea)\nDorothea’s profile is presented on page \n228, only her Agenda changes.\nAgenda: Free myself from the prison \nwhere Helga locked me up.\nEnd of Scene: Helga’s threat is \nended, either through combat or by \nconvincing her to let Dorothea go free. \nThe girl surrenders to the Hunters, \nrevealing that everything she did was \nordered by Norman Henkle, a doctor \nwho, like her, comes from another \nworld. Henkle settled in the center of the Black Forest, \nin a village called Smaragd. Henkle’s goal is to gather all \nthe pieces of the Compass Rose to summon the magical \ntornado. Dorothea realizes that Henkle is insane and reveals \nto the Hunters that even though she has been stopped, the \nman will still try to activate the half-reassembled artifact, \ncertainly with devastating results. Only Dorothea knows \nthe location of the village and she is willing to accompany \nthe Hunters, expressing sincere repentance.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are three Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters get the better of Wolfgang: Helga will \nlet him speak for a while so she can observe the Hunters \nclosely and then kill the man by drowning him in his own \nblood.\nWhen the Hunters start to get the better of a conflict \nwith Helga’s minions: the witch will detonate one of her \nminions in each Exchange to cover \nthe Hunters in her blood. Y ou can \ntry to control them later.\nIf Dorothea is saved by the \nHunters: she will stay by their \nside as an ally to take revenge on \nHelga. She will try to kill her even \nif the Hunters intend to negotiate.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 237.","owner":"The Hammerheads","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624561,"modifiedTime":1781557624561,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-hammerheads-237","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":237,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We were once a ferocious team of skilled \nmercenaries, but now we are in Helga’s service. We were \ntamed by her magic and therefore we do anything and \neverything for her.\nGift - Hammerhead Helmet: The heavy and distinctive \nHammerhead helmet opens like a flower on the shoulders \nand grants total head and chest protection, making the \nNPC immune to any Wound that can’t get past a thick layer \nof metal. An enemy can aim at the lower parts of the NPC \nto ignore the helmet. However, they receive 1 Penalty for \ntheir Check.\nOZena (Dorothea)\nDorothea’s profile is presented on page \n228, only her Agenda changes.\nAgenda: Free myself from the prison \nwhere Helga locked me up.\nEnd of Scene: Helga’s threat is \nended, either through combat or by \nconvincing her to let Dorothea go free. \nThe girl surrenders to the Hunters, \nrevealing that everything she did was \nordered by Norman Henkle, a doctor \nwho, like her, comes from another \nworld. Henkle settled in the center of the Black Forest, \nin a village called Smaragd. Henkle’s goal is to gather all \nthe pieces of the Compass Rose to summon the magical \ntornado. Dorothea realizes that Henkle is insane and reveals \nto the Hunters that even though she has been stopped, the \nman will still try to activate the half-reassembled artifact, \ncertainly with devastating results. Only Dorothea knows \nthe location of the village and she is willing to accompany \nthe Hunters, expressing sincere repentance.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are three Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters get the better of Wolfgang: Helga will \nlet him speak for a while so she can observe the Hunters \nclosely and then kill the man by drowning him in his own \nblood.\nWhen the Hunters start to get the better of a conflict \nwith Helga’s minions: the witch will detonate one of her \nminions in each Exchange to cover \nthe Hunters in her blood. Y ou can \ntry to control them later.\nIf Dorothea is saved by the \nHunters: she will stay by their \nside as an ally to take revenge on \nHelga. She will try to kill her even \nif the Hunters intend to negotiate.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Free myself from the prison \nwhere Helga locked me up.\nEnd of Scene: Helga’s threat is \nended, either through combat or by \nconvincing her to let Dorothea go free. \nThe girl surrenders to the Hunters, \nrevealing that everything she did was \nordered by Norman Henkle, a doctor \nwho, like her, comes from another \nworld. Henkle settled in the center of the Black Forest, \nin a village called Smaragd. Henkle’s goal is to gather all \nthe pieces of the Compass Rose to summon the magical \ntornado. Dorothea realizes that Henkle is insane and reveals \nto the Hunters that even though she has been stopped, the \nman will still try to activate the half-reassembled artifact, \ncertainly with devastating results. Only Dorothea knows \nthe location of the village and she is willing to accompany \nthe Hunters, expressing sincere repentance.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are three Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters get the better of Wolfgang: Helga will \nlet him speak for a while so she can observe the Hunters \nclosely and then kill the man by drowning him in his own \nblood.\nWhen the Hunters start to get the better of a conflict \nwith Helga’s minions: the witch will detonate one of her \nminions in each Exchange to cover \nthe Hunters in her blood. Y ou can \ntry to control them later.\nIf Dorothea is saved by the \nHunters: she will stay by their \nside as an ally to take revenge on \nHelga. She will try to kill her even \nif the Hunters intend to negotiate.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624561,"modifiedTime":1781557624561,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NPOMHHgnNpUTx75o","name":"Distrustful Inhabitants","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"n9OVUROtn7gESXy3","name":"Distrustful Inhabitants - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Distrustful Inhabitants","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We don’t want to attract too much attention \nto Sinalunga, so we’re reluctant to talk to foreigners. Nobody \nhere wants to lose what they have gained through years of \nhard work.\nInformation from the townspeople: \nRoll a die or pick from the list.\n ◆ 1-2: 10 people have been found, but 11 went missing. \nNino’s body is still missing. He is Mastro Antonio’s \napprentice carpenter. Antonio is known as Mastro \n“Cherry” Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. \n ◆ 3-4: Villa Cilesterino is haunted by the ghost of the \nold owner, Azzurra. She was burned at the stake for \nwitchcraft.\n ◆ 5-6: The high standard of living in Sinalunga led to the \nopening of Villa Balocchi, a tavern on the edge of town \nwhere one can find company as well as a comfortable \nbed. The tavern is managed by Amabile Burromo and \nis in open competition with the historic town inn, the \nGambero Rosso (meaning “the Red Prawn”).\nThe Old Well\nDescriptor: An old abandoned well in the middle of a \ndilapidated vineyard. A nauseating smell from the bottom of \nthe well reminds anyone who approaches of the horror that \nit hides.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 134.","positive":"We don’t want to attract too much attention \nto Sinalunga, so we’re reluctant to talk to foreigners. Nobody \nhere wants to lose what they have gained through years of \nhard work.\nInformation from the townspeople: \nRoll a die or pick from the list.\n ◆ 1-2: 10 people have been found, but 11 went missing. \nNino’s body is still missing. He is Mastro Antonio’s \napprentice carpenter. Antonio is known as Mastro \n“Cherry” Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. \n ◆ 3-4: Villa Cilesterino is haunted by the ghost of the \nold owner, Azzurra. She was burned at the stake for \nwitchcraft.\n ◆ 5-6: The high standard of living in Sinalunga led to the \nopening of Villa Balocchi, a tavern on the edge of town \nwhere one can find company as well as a comfortable \nbed. The tavern is managed by Amabile Burromo and \nis in open competition with the historic town inn, the \nGambero Rosso (meaning “the Red Prawn”).\nThe Old Well\nDescriptor: An old abandoned well in the middle of a \ndilapidated vineyard. A nauseating smell from the bottom of \nthe well reminds anyone who approaches of the horror that \nit hides.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Distrustful Inhabitants","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621795,"modifiedTime":1781557621795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mMIT8vGmQvYkYgQY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Distrustful Inhabitants","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: We don’t want to attract too much attention \nto Sinalunga, so we’re reluctant to talk to foreigners. Nobody \nhere wants to lose what they have gained through years of \nhard work.\nInformation from the townspeople: \nRoll a die or pick from the list.\n ◆ 1-2: 10 people have been found, but 11 went missing. \nNino’s body is still missing. He is Mastro Antonio’s \napprentice carpenter. Antonio is known as Mastro \n“Cherry” Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. \n ◆ 3-4: Villa Cilesterino is haunted by the ghost of the \nold owner, Azzurra. She was burned at the stake for \nwitchcraft.\n ◆ 5-6: The high standard of living in Sinalunga led to the \nopening of Villa Balocchi, a tavern on the edge of town \nwhere one can find company as well as a comfortable \nbed. The tavern is managed by Amabile Burromo and \nis in open competition with the historic town inn, the \nGambero Rosso (meaning “the Red Prawn”).\nThe Old Well\nDescriptor: An old abandoned well in the middle of a \ndilapidated vineyard. A nauseating smell from the bottom of \nthe well reminds anyone who approaches of the horror that \nit hides.\nInformation: \n ◆ The bodies have already been removed and burned to \navoid infection and disease. \n ◆ When going down into the well, however, there are still \nsome remains and traces of blood. \n ◆ On the bottom, it is possible to find a carpenter’s chisel \nthat Geppetto lost while moving the corpses. \nThe Gambero Rosso Inn\nDescriptor: A small and cozy tavern, full of bottles of good \nwine.\nInformation: \n ◆ Speaking with the innkeeper, a big fat man named \nDuccio, the Hunters will learn that Villa Balocchi is a \nplace steeped in sin, where men and women gamble \nand entertain themselves in shady encounters. \nDuring the evening, Geppetto is at the Gambero Rosso and \nwill not hesitate to play out his little rehearsed spectacle of \nthe worried father for whoever shows up. Geppetto will \ndescribe Carlo as an annoying child with a pair of old, \nelegant shoes that Geppetto gave him for his first day of \nschool.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 134.","owner":"Distrustful Inhabitants","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621795,"modifiedTime":1781557621795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-distrustful-inhabitants-134","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":134,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: We don’t want to attract too much attention \nto Sinalunga, so we’re reluctant to talk to foreigners. Nobody \nhere wants to lose what they have gained through years of \nhard work.\nInformation from the townspeople: \nRoll a die or pick from the list.\n ◆ 1-2: 10 people have been found, but 11 went missing. \nNino’s body is still missing. He is Mastro Antonio’s \napprentice carpenter. Antonio is known as Mastro \n“Cherry” Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. \n ◆ 3-4: Villa Cilesterino is haunted by the ghost of the \nold owner, Azzurra. She was burned at the stake for \nwitchcraft.\n ◆ 5-6: The high standard of living in Sinalunga led to the \nopening of Villa Balocchi, a tavern on the edge of town \nwhere one can find company as well as a comfortable \nbed. The tavern is managed by Amabile Burromo and \nis in open competition with the historic town inn, the \nGambero Rosso (meaning “the Red Prawn”).\nThe Old Well\nDescriptor: An old abandoned well in the middle of a \ndilapidated vineyard. A nauseating smell from the bottom of \nthe well reminds anyone who approaches of the horror that \nit hides.\nInformation: \n ◆ The bodies have already been removed and burned to \navoid infection and disease. \n ◆ When going down into the well, however, there are still \nsome remains and traces of blood. \n ◆ On the bottom, it is possible to find a carpenter’s chisel \nthat Geppetto lost while moving the corpses. \nThe Gambero Rosso Inn\nDescriptor: A small and cozy tavern, full of bottles of good \nwine.\nInformation: \n ◆ Speaking with the innkeeper, a big fat man named \nDuccio, the Hunters will learn that Villa Balocchi is a \nplace steeped in sin, where men and women gamble \nand entertain themselves in shady encounters. \nDuring the evening, Geppetto is at the Gambero Rosso and \nwill not hesitate to play out his little rehearsed spectacle of \nthe worried father for whoever shows up. Geppetto will \ndescribe Carlo as an annoying child with a pair of old, \nelegant shoes that Geppetto gave him for his first day of \nschool.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621795,"modifiedTime":1781557621795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NeL2a4sXOsrPPPON","name":"Elizaveta – The cruel bride","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"sZjTiPIMRAVlDkf9","name":"Elizaveta – The cruel bride - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Elizaveta – The cruel bride","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever \nis needed to get what I want.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","positive":"I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever \nis needed to get what I want.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Elizaveta – The cruel bride","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qL8cfXf0ZNiKDYm5","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Elizaveta – The cruel bride","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever \nis needed to get what I want.\nAgenda: To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have \nearned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter \nIskra.\nVincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of \nthe Guards</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","owner":"Elizaveta – The cruel bride","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-elizaveta-the-cruel-bride-122","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":122,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever \nis needed to get what I want.\nAgenda: To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have \nearned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter \nIskra.\nVincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of \nthe Guards</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have \nearned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter \nIskra.\nVincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of \nthe Guards","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RXBZvznqtw7obEpE","name":"Stallo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"KHHtFh0hZDUhwdm8","name":"Stallo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Stallo","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an old troll and my appetite is \nmatched only by my strength. A bird has made its nest on \nmy head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the \neye, which is incredibly annoying!</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 188.","positive":"I am an old troll and my appetite is \nmatched only by my strength. A bird has made its nest on \nmy head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the \neye, which is incredibly annoying!","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Stallo","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lwWTgFyH39XOF4cv","name":"Gift - Troll","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Stallo","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Stallo possesses enormous strength and \neach Position Check for a physical action attempted \nagainst him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his \nactions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he \nreaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, \nonly to regenerate within minutes. \n5: A saddled warhorse, magnificent and white as fresh \nsnow, is grazing in the tall grass. This mount belonged to \none of the knights who met a dire fate in the search for \nTuvstarr. The steed will be reluctant to be approached, but</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 188.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Stallo","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lKo1A8XEgoeMQ7rd","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Stallo","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old troll and my appetite is \nmatched only by my strength. A bird has made its nest on \nmy head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the \neye, which is incredibly annoying!\nGift – Troll: Stallo possesses enormous strength and \neach Position Check for a physical action attempted \nagainst him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his \nactions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he \nreaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, \nonly to regenerate within minutes. \n5: A saddled warhorse, magnificent and white as fresh \nsnow, is grazing in the tall grass. This mount belonged to \none of the knights who met a dire fate in the search for \nTuvstarr. The steed will be reluctant to be approached, but</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 188.","owner":"Stallo","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-stallo-188","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":188,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old troll and my appetite is \nmatched only by my strength. A bird has made its nest on \nmy head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the \neye, which is incredibly annoying!\nGift – Troll: Stallo possesses enormous strength and \neach Position Check for a physical action attempted \nagainst him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his \nactions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he \nreaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, \nonly to regenerate within minutes. \n5: A saddled warhorse, magnificent and white as fresh \nsnow, is grazing in the tall grass. This mount belonged to \none of the knights who met a dire fate in the search for \nTuvstarr. The steed will be reluctant to be approached, but</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"SBqogICdyx08kVjU","name":"Rabbit Automaton","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"zhhUjBqYo7WTcdVs","name":"Rabbit Automaton - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Rabbit Automaton","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible \njumps and crush everything when landing.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 176.","positive":"I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible \njumps and crush everything when landing.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Rabbit Automaton","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MsIWHvv8amwnR9FC","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Rabbit Automaton","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible \njumps and crush everything when landing.\nGift - Leap: When it acts, the Automaton can free \nitself from any engagement with ease by jumping away. \nIf it lands on a victim, it increases its OL by 1 for the \nattack and if it inflicts 1 Wound, the target will also be \nknocked to the ground.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 176.","owner":"Rabbit Automaton","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-rabbit-automaton-176","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":176,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible \njumps and crush everything when landing.\nGift - Leap: When it acts, the Automaton can free \nitself from any engagement with ease by jumping away. \nIf it lands on a victim, it increases its OL by 1 for the \nattack and if it inflicts 1 Wound, the target will also be \nknocked to the ground.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TOy90f0zyWyUW3rr","name":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"88moMe9fiYLjozXg","name":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as \nthe mastermind of the gang. Living in my natural prison has \ntaught me how to see even in total darkness.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","positive":"I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as \nthe mastermind of the gang. Living in my natural prison has \ntaught me how to see even in total darkness.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"FfWn8LYulhg3r43Q","name":"Gift - The Flesh of The God Under the Mine","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Arthur \ncan tear pieces of flesh from the God’s head to harness its \npowers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes \na Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, \nengaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of \nmeat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BICWp0IaICubAVk1","name":"Gift - Gang Leader","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act \na second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe God Under \nthe Mine</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Q3gNMixeISebzB3E","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as \nthe mastermind of the gang. Living in my natural prison has \ntaught me how to see even in total darkness.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything \nI built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / \nTransforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig \nHeads.\nGift - The Flesh of The God Under the Mine: Arthur \ncan tear pieces of flesh from the God’s head to harness its \npowers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes \na Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, \nengaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of \nmeat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.\nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act \na second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe God Under \nthe Mine</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","owner":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-arthur-browne-the-big-brother-212","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":212,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as \nthe mastermind of the gang. Living in my natural prison has \ntaught me how to see even in total darkness.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything \nI built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / \nTransforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig \nHeads.\nGift - The Flesh of The God Under the Mine: Arthur \ncan tear pieces of flesh from the God’s head to harness its \npowers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes \na Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, \nengaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of \nmeat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.\nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act \na second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe God Under \nthe Mine</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything \nI built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / \nTransforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig \nHeads.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Tk0H4q2QpDyymJZJ","name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"kiJ5YuyaURewvNbm","name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two \nmeters long. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the \ncarcasses of creatures I’ve devoured.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 175.","positive":"I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two \nmeters long. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the \ncarcasses of creatures I’ve devoured.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622955,"modifiedTime":1781557622955,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jPHV4h0JzKNl0r4h","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two \nmeters long. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the \ncarcasses of creatures I’ve devoured.\nGift - Hunter Caterpillar: When a Caterpillar moves, any \nhuman-sized subject in its path risks being overwhelmed. \nWhoever is in the Caterpillar’s way must perform a \nDefense Check in order not to end up knocked down. The \nCaterpillar inflicts 1 Additional Wound against people \nprone on the ground.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 175.","owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622955,"modifiedTime":1781557622955,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-caterpillar-of-the-wonderful-lands-175","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":175,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two \nmeters long. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the \ncarcasses of creatures I’ve devoured.\nGift - Hunter Caterpillar: When a Caterpillar moves, any \nhuman-sized subject in its path risks being overwhelmed. \nWhoever is in the Caterpillar’s way must perform a \nDefense Check in order not to end up knocked down. The \nCaterpillar inflicts 1 Additional Wound against people \nprone on the ground.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622955,"modifiedTime":1781557622955,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"V9IAg6Fwh0wxEi98","name":"Cheshire The Faithful Lynx","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"BIPh40QA0D7dcoWq","name":"Cheshire The Faithful Lynx - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Cheshire The Faithful Lynx","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a snappy and aggressive lynx. I roam the \nhalls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 172.","positive":"I am a snappy and aggressive lynx. I roam the \nhalls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Cheshire The Faithful Lynx","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622892,"modifiedTime":1781557622892,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"afxWxopUtkX8Hja5","name":"Gift - Elusive","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Cheshire The Faithful Lynx","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, \nCheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, \nand move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always \nmove without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to \nattack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the \nconstant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This \nGift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.\nWonderBedlam</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 172.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Cheshire The Faithful Lynx","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622892,"modifiedTime":1781557622892,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qDFZweiJfvPYBz6E","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Cheshire The Faithful Lynx","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a snappy and aggressive lynx. I roam the \nhalls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress.\nGift - Elusive: Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, \nCheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, \nand move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always \nmove without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to \nattack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the \nconstant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This \nGift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.\nWonderBedlam\nDescriptor: I am a building animated by sheer madness \nand no one can attempt to alter me without Alice Liddell’s \npermission.\nGift - Place of Pure Madness: When a subject \nattempts an action or uses a Gift to change Wonder’s insane \nstructure (such as breaking through walls or circumventing \npassageways), the building’s inherent magic activates. \nBefore the action taken is resolved, roll a die to see where \nthe subject will end up being teleported.\n1-2: The Rabbit Hole. \n3-4: The Labyrinth of Doors. \n5-6: The Caterpillars’ Greenhouse.\nThis magical shift causes a side effect that lasts throughout \nthe Scene; roll a die to determine what happens.\n1-2 Shrunk: The subject receives the Descriptor I am half \nthe size I was, all my physical abilities are diminished as well.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 172.","owner":"Cheshire The Faithful Lynx","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622892,"modifiedTime":1781557622892,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-cheshire-the-faithful-lynx-172","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":172,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a snappy and aggressive lynx. I roam the \nhalls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress.\nGift - Elusive: Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, \nCheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, \nand move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always \nmove without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to \nattack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the \nconstant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This \nGift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.\nWonderBedlam\nDescriptor: I am a building animated by sheer madness \nand no one can attempt to alter me without Alice Liddell’s \npermission.\nGift - Place of Pure Madness: When a subject \nattempts an action or uses a Gift to change Wonder’s insane \nstructure (such as breaking through walls or circumventing \npassageways), the building’s inherent magic activates. \nBefore the action taken is resolved, roll a die to see where \nthe subject will end up being teleported.\n1-2: The Rabbit Hole. \n3-4: The Labyrinth of Doors. \n5-6: The Caterpillars’ Greenhouse.\nThis magical shift causes a side effect that lasts throughout \nthe Scene; roll a die to determine what happens.\n1-2 Shrunk: The subject receives the Descriptor I am half \nthe size I was, all my physical abilities are diminished as well.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622892,"modifiedTime":1781557622892,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VCdkr5v1qL50t83H","name":"Marcel the Time-Waster","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"lwbV342cYWFfQLCn","name":"Marcel the Time-Waster - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Marcel the Time-Waster","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I frequently wander the town and may be found \nanywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no \none believed my story because I am too young.\n5 Corinne the Housekeeper</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"I frequently wander the town and may be found \nanywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no \none believed my story because I am too young.\n5 Corinne the Housekeeper","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Marcel the Time-Waster","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AoHatYstbxtUV229","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Marcel the Time-Waster","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I frequently wander the town and may be found \nanywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no \none believed my story because I am too young.\n5 Corinne the Housekeeper</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","owner":"Marcel the Time-Waster","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-marcel-the-time-waster-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I frequently wander the town and may be found \nanywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no \none believed my story because I am too young.\n5 Corinne the Housekeeper</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VdGNzNvjyaIDpV7M","name":"Black Wolves of Greskar’s Pack","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"4oidBWVAHkxd9qV6","name":"Black Wolves of Greskar’s Pack - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Black Wolves of Greskar’s Pack","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are fierce black wolves, we hate \nhumans and obey only our pack leader.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 127.","positive":"We are fierce black wolves, we hate \nhumans and obey only our pack leader.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Black Wolves of Greskar’s Pack","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621429,"modifiedTime":1781557621429,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YqdfRwpgWgwAbZ9b","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Black Wolves of Greskar’s Pack","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are fierce black wolves, we hate \nhumans and obey only our pack leader.\nAgenda: Follow without hesitation every order \nfrom the pack’s alpha.\nGift - The Power of the Pack: Any action \ntaken while being engaged by two or more Wolves \nreceives 1 Penalty.\nStory Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six main Events. As Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.\nIf the raids of the wolves are not stopped in one day: \nmany of Gerard’s soldiers will be eliminated, victims of a much \nmore intense attack than those that have occurred so far, taking \nplace at the gates of the palace. After the furious assault, the \ncity’s defenses will be reduced to a minimum and it will be very \neasy for Iskra to break into the Dubois palace under the cover of \ndarkness.\nIf a Hunter finds Iskra’s pendant in the well: Anastazia \nwill contact them, showing them a vision of Iskra as a child \ndrinking at the Oaks Glade. The spirit of Iskra’s grandmother, \nwhile unable to communicate directly, will try to make the \nHunters understand that Iskra is not a monster.\nIf Elizaveta goes out of town for any reason: Iskra will \nimmediately smell her scent and rush to eliminate her regardless \nof any risk. Confronted with her mother, the little girl will lose all \nrestraint and refuse to listen to reason.\nIf Iskra is captured: the wolf pack led by a furious Greskar \nwill launch a tremendous attack on Durfort. Elizaveta will try to \neliminate her daughter with a powerful poison.\nIf Iskra is killed: Anastazia’s spirit will turn on her murderer, \nsending visions of Elizaveta trying to wash the blood of a dead \nchild from her hands.\nIf someone accuses Elizaveta: Gerard will deny everything \nout of fear and shame, invoking concrete and irrefutable \nevidence. Elizaveta, for her part, will play the role of the victim, \nalways trying to highlight the danger posed by the wolves.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 127.","owner":"Black Wolves of Greskar’s Pack","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621439,"modifiedTime":1781557621439,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-black-wolves-of-greskar-s-pack-127","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":127,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are fierce black wolves, we hate \nhumans and obey only our pack leader.\nAgenda: Follow without hesitation every order \nfrom the pack’s alpha.\nGift - The Power of the Pack: Any action \ntaken while being engaged by two or more Wolves \nreceives 1 Penalty.\nStory Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six main Events. As Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.\nIf the raids of the wolves are not stopped in one day: \nmany of Gerard’s soldiers will be eliminated, victims of a much \nmore intense attack than those that have occurred so far, taking \nplace at the gates of the palace. After the furious assault, the \ncity’s defenses will be reduced to a minimum and it will be very \neasy for Iskra to break into the Dubois palace under the cover of \ndarkness.\nIf a Hunter finds Iskra’s pendant in the well: Anastazia \nwill contact them, showing them a vision of Iskra as a child \ndrinking at the Oaks Glade. The spirit of Iskra’s grandmother, \nwhile unable to communicate directly, will try to make the \nHunters understand that Iskra is not a monster.\nIf Elizaveta goes out of town for any reason: Iskra will \nimmediately smell her scent and rush to eliminate her regardless \nof any risk. Confronted with her mother, the little girl will lose all \nrestraint and refuse to listen to reason.\nIf Iskra is captured: the wolf pack led by a furious Greskar \nwill launch a tremendous attack on Durfort. Elizaveta will try to \neliminate her daughter with a powerful poison.\nIf Iskra is killed: Anastazia’s spirit will turn on her murderer, \nsending visions of Elizaveta trying to wash the blood of a dead \nchild from her hands.\nIf someone accuses Elizaveta: Gerard will deny everything \nout of fear and shame, invoking concrete and irrefutable \nevidence. Elizaveta, for her part, will play the role of the victim, \nalways trying to highlight the danger posed by the wolves.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Follow without hesitation every order \nfrom the pack’s alpha.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621439,"modifiedTime":1781557621439,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"WyN0L7cyRZ5xCRoX","name":"Marionette","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"QZVOsiTIiBr0xQtU","name":"Marionette - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Marionette","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden \nbodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to \nbe destroyed to be free again.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 136.","positive":"We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden \nbodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to \nbe destroyed to be free again.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Marionette","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621843,"modifiedTime":1781557621843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pxUuzxbIX4EXLyuk","name":"Gift - Boundless Rage","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Marionette","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Azzurra’s power animates and \nforces the Marionettes to do evil acts. When a Marionette \nsuffers the last Wound it will immediately spring on the \nenemy with incredible momentum as Azzurra’s power \ncompels them one last time. The Marionette can take a</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 136.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Marionette","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersi