ss Rage: Azzurra’s power animates and \nforces the Marionettes to do evil acts. When a Marionette \nsuffers the last Wound it will immediately spring on the \nenemy with incredible momentum as Azzurra’s power \ncompels them one last time. The Marionette can take a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Attacking every human we meet.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621843,"modifiedTime":1781557621843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"X2gS4rMGqqZOjTkD","name":"Carlo The Living Puppet","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"56ZmqF6tRH3KR0PN","name":"Carlo The Living Puppet - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Carlo The Living Puppet","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The \nlies I tell become reality for a short time.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","positive":"I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The \nlies I tell become reality for a short time.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Carlo The Living Puppet","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"u5l2drU2i5DHp4UL","name":"Gift - Lies","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Carlo The Living Puppet","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life \nby creating a Descriptor that allows him to \nperform incredible feats. All lies must be \ncentered on him. For example: I can walk \nthrough walls or I am invisible to the human \neye. The effects of the lies’ power are literal. \nFor this reason, Carlo would not be able to \ngo through a closed door and he would be \nseen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 \nScene or until a new lie is told.\nLucino - The Good Friend</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Carlo The Living Puppet","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9EhENolSn7XflNJM","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Carlo The Living Puppet","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The \nlies I tell become reality for a short time.\nAgenda: Living a carefree life without responsibility / I don’t \nwant to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but \nI’m always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me. \nGift - Lies: Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life \nby creating a Descriptor that allows him to \nperform incredible feats. All lies must be \ncentered on him. For example: I can walk \nthrough walls or I am invisible to the human \neye. The effects of the lies’ power are literal. \nFor this reason, Carlo would not be able to \ngo through a closed door and he would be \nseen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 \nScene or until a new lie is told.\nLucino - The Good Friend</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","owner":"Carlo The Living Puppet","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-carlo-the-living-puppet-137","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":137,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The \nlies I tell become reality for a short time.\nAgenda: Living a carefree life without responsibility / I don’t \nwant to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but \nI’m always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me. \nGift - Lies: Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life \nby creating a Descriptor that allows him to \nperform incredible feats. All lies must be \ncentered on him. For example: I can walk \nthrough walls or I am invisible to the human \neye. The effects of the lies’ power are literal. \nFor this reason, Carlo would not be able to \ngo through a closed door and he would be \nseen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 \nScene or until a new lie is told.\nLucino - The Good Friend</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Living a carefree life without responsibility / I don’t \nwant to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but \nI’m always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Xqx8QtD5z8u8BLiY","name":"Antonio Ciliegia Gullible Alchemist","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Q6Vhyl8vKDOfg4Up","name":"Antonio Ciliegia Gullible Alchemist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Antonio Ciliegia Gullible Alchemist","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an old alchemist who has never discovered \nanything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck \nis never on my side.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 140.","positive":"I am an old alchemist who has never discovered \nanything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck \nis never on my side.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Antonio Ciliegia Gullible Alchemist","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621931,"modifiedTime":1781557621931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AdL14qrj43fHAf5v","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Antonio Ciliegia Gullible Alchemist","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old alchemist who has never discovered \nanything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck \nis never on my side.\nAgenda: Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to \nalchemy. \nGift - Unlucky Alchemist: Antonio can rely on a series \nof alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides \nin his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or \n6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound \ndue to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the \nsurrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 \nWound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets \nsuffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder: The target \nis knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the \nground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 \nWound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that \nquickly solidifies in the air. The target will be \nparalyzed until the compound is removed. \nThe Glue can take 2 Wounds.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 140.","owner":"Antonio Ciliegia Gullible Alchemist","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621931,"modifiedTime":1781557621931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-antonio-ciliegia-gullible-alchemist-140","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":140,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old alchemist who has never discovered \nanything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck \nis never on my side.\nAgenda: Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to \nalchemy. \nGift - Unlucky Alchemist: Antonio can rely on a series \nof alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides \nin his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or \n6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound \ndue to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the \nsurrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 \nWound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets \nsuffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder: The target \nis knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the \nground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 \nWound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that \nquickly solidifies in the air. The target will be \nparalyzed until the compound is removed. \nThe Glue can take 2 Wounds.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to \nalchemy.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621931,"modifiedTime":1781557621931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Zfuj6tv0FGwMdHmv","name":"Big Black Wolf","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"d2X63EF9fNvZEKoR","name":"Big Black Wolf - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Big Black Wolf","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge, mighty \nwerewolf. I have to constantly prove my \nstrength to stay the alpha of the pack.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","positive":"I am a huge, mighty \nwerewolf. I have to constantly prove my \nstrength to stay the alpha of the pack.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Big Black Wolf","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"A1AthVgqAfHl4FvH","name":"Gift - Big Wolf","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Big Black Wolf","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Greskar is an enormous \nblack wolf, as big as a horse. When he \ngrabs someone with his jaws, in addition \nto inflicting a Wound, he can drag or \nhurl them away as if they were a rag doll. \nOnce per Scene, Geskar’s bite can inflict \n1 additional Wound.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Big Black Wolf","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4ZfkCLpfn4lZ3Uzx","name":"Gift - The Wolf’s Smell","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Big Black Wolf","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Greskar’s \nsense of smell is infallible. The big wolf \nwill always be able to identify someone if \nhe knows their scent, ignoring all kinds \nof disguises and even magic.\nRed-Hood Iskra</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Big Black Wolf","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WQCqIT3Mvl20TdNh","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Big Black Wolf","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge, mighty \nwerewolf. I have to constantly prove my \nstrength to stay the alpha of the pack.\nAgenda: Protect Iskra and devour as \nmany humans as possible.\nGift - Big Wolf: Greskar is an enormous \nblack wolf, as big as a horse. When he \ngrabs someone with his jaws, in addition \nto inflicting a Wound, he can drag or \nhurl them away as if they were a rag doll. \nOnce per Scene, Geskar’s bite can inflict \n1 additional Wound.\nGift - The Wolf’s Smell: Greskar’s \nsense of smell is infallible. The big wolf \nwill always be able to identify someone if \nhe knows their scent, ignoring all kinds \nof disguises and even magic.\nRed-Hood Iskra</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","owner":"Big Black Wolf","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-big-black-wolf-126","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":126,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge, mighty \nwerewolf. I have to constantly prove my \nstrength to stay the alpha of the pack.\nAgenda: Protect Iskra and devour as \nmany humans as possible.\nGift - Big Wolf: Greskar is an enormous \nblack wolf, as big as a horse. When he \ngrabs someone with his jaws, in addition \nto inflicting a Wound, he can drag or \nhurl them away as if they were a rag doll. \nOnce per Scene, Geskar’s bite can inflict \n1 additional Wound.\nGift - The Wolf’s Smell: Greskar’s \nsense of smell is infallible. The big wolf \nwill always be able to identify someone if \nhe knows their scent, ignoring all kinds \nof disguises and even magic.\nRed-Hood Iskra</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect Iskra and devour as \nmany humans as possible.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"a9SyNIvdJu36AmvM","name":"Alissa of Norfolk The Rebel","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"viH27i8R4j6orKRo","name":"Alissa of Norfolk The Rebel - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alissa of Norfolk The Rebel","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I have been physically tested by my stay in \nWonder, but my mind is still strong. My love for Alicia kept \nme in the real world.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 178.","positive":"I have been physically tested by my stay in \nWonder, but my mind is still strong. My love for Alicia kept \nme in the real world.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Alissa of Norfolk The Rebel","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623025,"modifiedTime":1781557623025,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tazHYgsNZUvr2YS3","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alissa of Norfolk The Rebel","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I have been physically tested by my stay in \nWonder, but my mind is still strong. My love for Alicia kept \nme in the real world.\nAgenda: Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a \nfuture with Alicia.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nWhen the Hunters visit the third Cure Room \nwithout first meeting Alicia: they will encounter \nAlicia, who is lost. The young woman will be reluctant to \nreveal her true identity but will give her name and introduce \nherself as a patient.\nOn a regular basis, if the Hunters waste time in the \nEntrance Hall of Wonder: one of the bedlam Patients \nwill walk out of one of the three doors into another. The \nPatient will mumble disjointed words such as “see beyond” \nor “go under” .\nIf the Hunters cause too much havoc in a Cure \nRoom: Alice will take control of Cheshire and order the \nHunters to leave, or try to surprise them by making it clear \nthat they are being watched.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 178.","owner":"Alissa of Norfolk The Rebel","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623025,"modifiedTime":1781557623025,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-alissa-of-norfolk-the-rebel-178","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":178,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I have been physically tested by my stay in \nWonder, but my mind is still strong. My love for Alicia kept \nme in the real world.\nAgenda: Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a \nfuture with Alicia.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nWhen the Hunters visit the third Cure Room \nwithout first meeting Alicia: they will encounter \nAlicia, who is lost. The young woman will be reluctant to \nreveal her true identity but will give her name and introduce \nherself as a patient.\nOn a regular basis, if the Hunters waste time in the \nEntrance Hall of Wonder: one of the bedlam Patients \nwill walk out of one of the three doors into another. The \nPatient will mumble disjointed words such as “see beyond” \nor “go under” .\nIf the Hunters cause too much havoc in a Cure \nRoom: Alice will take control of Cheshire and order the \nHunters to leave, or try to surprise them by making it clear \nthat they are being watched.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a \nfuture with Alicia.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nWhen the Hunters visit the third Cure Room \nwithout first meeting Alicia: they will encounter \nAlicia, who is lost. The young woman will be reluctant to \nreveal her true identity but will give her name and introduce \nherself as a patient.\nOn a regular basis, if the Hunters waste time in the \nEntrance Hall of Wonder: one of the bedlam Patients \nwill walk out of one of the three doors into another. The \nPatient will mumble disjointed words such as “see beyond” \nor “go under” .\nIf the Hunters cause too much havoc in a Cure \nRoom: Alice will take control of Cheshire and order the \nHunters to leave, or try to surprise them by making it clear \nthat they are being watched.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623025,"modifiedTime":1781557623025,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"aHv66BRLRFpTDj6c","name":"Vincenzo Carabiniere","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"n0Scl0VOH76dZ9sW","name":"Vincenzo Carabiniere - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Vincenzo Carabiniere","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my \nbest to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me \naway from battlefields.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 133.","positive":"I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my \nbest to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me \naway from battlefields.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Vincenzo Carabiniere","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621670,"modifiedTime":1781557621670,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9mJQrXsH35LgvHtt","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Vincenzo Carabiniere","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my \nbest to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me \naway from battlefields.\nAgenda: Find out what lies behind the disappearances in \nSinalunga.\nSinalunga\nDescriptor: A small town in the Tuscan hills. Thanks to its \nfamously delicious wine, many in the town manage to have a \ngood standard of living.\nBy wandering around town and talking to the inhabitants, \nthe Hunters can get some information. The fear that \nan intervention by the Grand Duchy could upset life in \nSinalunga means the inhabitants are reluctant to speak to \nanyone other than the authorities. Only Lapo and Cino, \nwho are not particularly bright, won’t hesitate to talk with \nthe Hunters, though only with the promise of a reward.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 133.","owner":"Vincenzo Carabiniere","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621670,"modifiedTime":1781557621670,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-vincenzo-carabiniere-133","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":133,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my \nbest to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me \naway from battlefields.\nAgenda: Find out what lies behind the disappearances in \nSinalunga.\nSinalunga\nDescriptor: A small town in the Tuscan hills. Thanks to its \nfamously delicious wine, many in the town manage to have a \ngood standard of living.\nBy wandering around town and talking to the inhabitants, \nthe Hunters can get some information. The fear that \nan intervention by the Grand Duchy could upset life in \nSinalunga means the inhabitants are reluctant to speak to \nanyone other than the authorities. Only Lapo and Cino, \nwho are not particularly bright, won’t hesitate to talk with \nthe Hunters, though only with the promise of a reward.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Find out what lies behind the disappearances in \nSinalunga.\nSinalunga\nDescriptor: A small town in the Tuscan hills. Thanks to its \nfamously delicious wine, many in the town manage to have a \ngood standard of living.\nBy wandering around town and talking to the inhabitants, \nthe Hunters can get some information. The fear that \nan intervention by the Grand Duchy could upset life in \nSinalunga means the inhabitants are reluctant to speak to \nanyone other than the authorities. Only Lapo and Cino, \nwho are not particularly bright, won’t hesitate to talk with \nthe Hunters, though only with the promise of a reward.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621670,"modifiedTime":1781557621670,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bDXVT7iueVIuEAqR","name":"Alice Liddell The Director","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"3Zvt7fBeVgEdcNG7","name":"Alice Liddell The Director - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alice Liddell The Director","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the director of Wonder and, thanks to the \npower of madness, I can enter people’s minds to heal them.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","positive":"I am the director of Wonder and, thanks to the \npower of madness, I can enter people’s minds to heal them.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Alice Liddell The Director","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7NLiXIDelI6lJH2p","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alice Liddell The Director","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the director of Wonder and, thanks to the \npower of madness, I can enter people’s minds to heal them.\nAgenda: Safeguard what I have built within Wonder and \nall the incredible discoveries that the magic of madness can \ngive to mankind / Solve every problem by transforming it into \na Patient to be treated.\nGift - Alice from Other Worlds: As an action, Alice \ncan attempt to possess the body of a person or animal by \nlooking into their eyes. Hunters can make a Defense Check \nto prevent this. Alice can both act through the body she \ncontrols and continue to use her Gifts and Descriptors. \nThe possession ends when Alice’s body suffers 1 Wound. \nAlice cannot control more than 3 common subjects or a \nsingle Hunter at the same time.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","owner":"Alice Liddell The Director","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-alice-liddell-the-director-177","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":177,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the director of Wonder and, thanks to the \npower of madness, I can enter people’s minds to heal them.\nAgenda: Safeguard what I have built within Wonder and \nall the incredible discoveries that the magic of madness can \ngive to mankind / Solve every problem by transforming it into \na Patient to be treated.\nGift - Alice from Other Worlds: As an action, Alice \ncan attempt to possess the body of a person or animal by \nlooking into their eyes. Hunters can make a Defense Check \nto prevent this. Alice can both act through the body she \ncontrols and continue to use her Gifts and Descriptors. \nThe possession ends when Alice’s body suffers 1 Wound. \nAlice cannot control more than 3 common subjects or a \nsingle Hunter at the same time.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Safeguard what I have built within Wonder and \nall the incredible discoveries that the magic of madness can \ngive to mankind / Solve every problem by transforming it into \na Patient to be treated.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bLThYnpmTlW7L3X1","name":"The Gallant Knight","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"FuH8CS9cY9wOKyav","name":"The Gallant Knight - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gallant Knight","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a respected and experienced knight of the \nkingdom. My skill is only matched by my honor.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 192.","positive":"I am a respected and experienced knight of the \nkingdom. My skill is only matched by my honor.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Gallant Knight","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623467,"modifiedTime":1781557623467,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JmAF4x8n8MQEqfd1","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gallant Knight","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a respected and experienced knight of the \nkingdom. My skill is only matched by my honor.\nAgenda: Respect my knightly duties and serve the young \nPrincess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what’s happening.\nGift - Gallant Knight: The Knight is incredibly skilled, \nbut he would never use his full abilities against anyone \nhe doesn’t consider truly evil. When defending against \nan enemy attack, his mastery increases his OL by 1. The \nKnight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he \ndoesn’t feel it truly deserves death.\nEnd of Scene: After finding out where Tuvstarr is, the \nHunters can proceed to the FIFTH SCENE - The Castle of \nDreams.\nFIFTH SCENE – The Castle of \nDreams\nRead aloud to the Hunters: “ Ahead, you see a castle \nbigger than any other building in the country. The roof shines \nwith gold while the tallest tower is like another sun, shining \never so bright. Looking around you, however, you notice that \neverything seems to be nothing more than a false reflection \nof reality. Farmers at work, animals in the fields, the King \nand Queen themselves you see at the gates of the castle, all do \nnothing but smile and nod. They speak in a low voice and say \ncomforting things like: “Stay here, everything is fine, the lands \nare fresh and full of life. ” You realize that they are nothing \nmore than simple, idealized creations of Tuvstarr’s memories, \nbut full of joy and warmth. ”</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 192.","owner":"The Gallant Knight","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623467,"modifiedTime":1781557623467,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-the-gallant-knight-192","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":192,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a respected and experienced knight of the \nkingdom. My skill is only matched by my honor.\nAgenda: Respect my knightly duties and serve the young \nPrincess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what’s happening.\nGift - Gallant Knight: The Knight is incredibly skilled, \nbut he would never use his full abilities against anyone \nhe doesn’t consider truly evil. When defending against \nan enemy attack, his mastery increases his OL by 1. The \nKnight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he \ndoesn’t feel it truly deserves death.\nEnd of Scene: After finding out where Tuvstarr is, the \nHunters can proceed to the FIFTH SCENE - The Castle of \nDreams.\nFIFTH SCENE – The Castle of \nDreams\nRead aloud to the Hunters: “ Ahead, you see a castle \nbigger than any other building in the country. The roof shines \nwith gold while the tallest tower is like another sun, shining \never so bright. Looking around you, however, you notice that \neverything seems to be nothing more than a false reflection \nof reality. Farmers at work, animals in the fields, the King \nand Queen themselves you see at the gates of the castle, all do \nnothing but smile and nod. They speak in a low voice and say \ncomforting things like: “Stay here, everything is fine, the lands \nare fresh and full of life. ” You realize that they are nothing \nmore than simple, idealized creations of Tuvstarr’s memories, \nbut full of joy and warmth. ”</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Respect my knightly duties and serve the young \nPrincess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what’s happening.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623467,"modifiedTime":1781557623467,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"c9AnvTO9lRCAZx8d","name":"The Pig Heads","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"aVrzsqnEMQoCbZ90","name":"The Pig Heads - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pig Heads","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a band of revolutionaries in the service \nof the three brothers. The God’s flesh gives us power and fills \nus with the anger we need to wage our war.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","positive":"We are a band of revolutionaries in the service \nof the three brothers. The God’s flesh gives us power and fills \nus with the anger we need to wage our war.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Pig Heads","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VgBL0WMpDG7EESmU","name":"Gift - Pigs’ Gang","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pig Heads","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>When they act, each member of the \ngang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes \nthat of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to \ncommunicate with them. Their mutation grants a random \npower, roll 1 die. 1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional \nWound once per Scene; 2. Speed , once per Scene acts \n2 times consecutively; 3. Resistance , +1 Wound; \n4. Abomination , +1 to Opposition Level; 5. Grunt , \nonce per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it \nreceive 1 Penalty on their next action; 6. Out of control , \nthe OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the \nNPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.\nMartha Browne the Mother</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Pig Heads","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"c3rxifHeE9XhdC1J","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pig Heads","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are a band of revolutionaries in the service \nof the three brothers. The God’s flesh gives us power and fills \nus with the anger we need to wage our war.\nGift – Pigs’ Gang: When they act, each member of the \ngang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes \nthat of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to \ncommunicate with them. Their mutation grants a random \npower, roll 1 die. 1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional \nWound once per Scene; 2. Speed , once per Scene acts \n2 times consecutively; 3. Resistance , +1 Wound; \n4. Abomination , +1 to Opposition Level; 5. Grunt , \nonce per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it \nreceive 1 Penalty on their next action; 6. Out of control , \nthe OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the \nNPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.\nMartha Browne the Mother</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","owner":"The Pig Heads","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-the-pig-heads-208","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":208,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are a band of revolutionaries in the service \nof the three brothers. The God’s flesh gives us power and fills \nus with the anger we need to wage our war.\nGift – Pigs’ Gang: When they act, each member of the \ngang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes \nthat of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to \ncommunicate with them. Their mutation grants a random \npower, roll 1 die. 1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional \nWound once per Scene; 2. Speed , once per Scene acts \n2 times consecutively; 3. Resistance , +1 Wound; \n4. Abomination , +1 to Opposition Level; 5. Grunt , \nonce per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it \nreceive 1 Penalty on their next action; 6. Out of control , \nthe OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the \nNPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.\nMartha Browne the Mother</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ciuWB7uIm1FQkvc2","name":"Dose The Tin Man","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"65dAz0vdOBZpWbg3","name":"Dose The Tin Man - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose The Tin Man","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Leprosy has destroyed my appearance, but \nmy body is still that of the Mountain, the name by which \nI performed as a street artist in shows of strength and \nendurance. Under my heavy armor I fear nothing.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 228.","positive":"Leprosy has destroyed my appearance, but \nmy body is still that of the Mountain, the name by which \nI performed as a street artist in shows of strength and \nendurance. Under my heavy armor I fear nothing.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Dose The Tin Man","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624325,"modifiedTime":1781557624325,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PiKiTbYxj4O4R8RI","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose The Tin Man","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: Leprosy has destroyed my appearance, but \nmy body is still that of the Mountain, the name by which \nI performed as a street artist in shows of strength and \nendurance. Under my heavy armor I fear nothing.\nAgenda: I am in love with OZena, disfigured by the disease \njust like me. I am aware that she will never return my feelings \nand that is why the only thing I can do is serve her, even to \nmy death.\nGift - The Tin Man: Dose is completely covered in thick \narmor made of metal and other salvaged materials, such as \na large stove and the hull of a boat. The only unarmored spot \nis a small door in the stove that was once used to remove \nembers, which is located above his heart. It is not possible \nto hurt Dose unless one first finds a way to penetrate his \narmor or uses an attack that can clearly overcome his \ndefenses.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 228.","owner":"Dose The Tin Man","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624325,"modifiedTime":1781557624325,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-dose-the-tin-man-228","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":228,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: Leprosy has destroyed my appearance, but \nmy body is still that of the Mountain, the name by which \nI performed as a street artist in shows of strength and \nendurance. Under my heavy armor I fear nothing.\nAgenda: I am in love with OZena, disfigured by the disease \njust like me. I am aware that she will never return my feelings \nand that is why the only thing I can do is serve her, even to \nmy death.\nGift - The Tin Man: Dose is completely covered in thick \narmor made of metal and other salvaged materials, such as \na large stove and the hull of a boat. The only unarmored spot \nis a small door in the stove that was once used to remove \nembers, which is located above his heart. It is not possible \nto hurt Dose unless one first finds a way to penetrate his \narmor or uses an attack that can clearly overcome his \ndefenses.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I am in love with OZena, disfigured by the disease \njust like me. I am aware that she will never return my feelings \nand that is why the only thing I can do is serve her, even to \nmy death.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624325,"modifiedTime":1781557624325,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dWmQnibLJPNGYWcd","name":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"mUKDq1nGLmWOce71","name":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He \nknew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who \neven married a foreigner!</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He \nknew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who \neven married a foreigner!","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"thKKZBRcBgLqLchP","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He \nknew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who \neven married a foreigner!</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","owner":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-didier-the-grumpy-old-man-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He \nknew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who \neven married a foreigner!</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"eJM3c2QiRAH3qMxU","name":"Fairies (Tuvstarr's Reflection)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"pekLzU4Lq5L7rb93","name":"Fairies - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fairies (Tuvstarr's Reflection)","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are Fairies, spirits of nature \nwho move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 189.","positive":"We are Fairies, spirits of nature \nwho move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Fairies (Tuvstarr's Reflection)","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"j3jPkSZ68E1p1hXf","name":"Gift - Madness","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fairies (Tuvstarr's Reflection)","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Made mad by the light of the crown, the \nFairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more \nFairies can attack together to make a single action with a \nbonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If \nthe action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the \ntarget will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once \nin the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry \nof drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 189.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Fairies (Tuvstarr's Reflection)","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"u2p5ijay1h8QI0E2","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Fairies (Tuvstarr's Reflection)","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are Fairies, spirits of nature \nwho move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans.\nAgenda: Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and \ndance forever wrapped in its sweet light. \nGift – Madness: Made mad by the light of the crown, the \nFairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more \nFairies can attack together to make a single action with a \nbonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If \nthe action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the \ntarget will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once \nin the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry \nof drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 189.","owner":"Fairies (Tuvstarr's Reflection)","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-fairies-189","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":189,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are Fairies, spirits of nature \nwho move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans.\nAgenda: Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and \ndance forever wrapped in its sweet light. \nGift – Madness: Made mad by the light of the crown, the \nFairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more \nFairies can attack together to make a single action with a \nbonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If \nthe action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the \ntarget will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once \nin the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry \nof drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and \ndance forever wrapped in its sweet light.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fvrwTpXt6aGB6xS8","name":"Hatta Carter The Mad Inventor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"TzNNksOac1josXoX","name":"Hatta Carter The Mad Inventor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hatta Carter The Mad Inventor","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my \ntime. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings \nand aggressiveness.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 176.","positive":"I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my \ntime. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings \nand aggressiveness.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Hatta Carter The Mad Inventor","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3sj6hqg4kujXkmyY","name":"Gift - Time Clocks","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hatta Carter The Mad Inventor","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks \nto influence time. 1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases \nhis OL by 2 when defending against a threat. 2. Speed \nUp: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can \nact, immediately stopping anyone’s action regardless of the \nsituation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, \nit can act again thanks to this Gift.\nRabbit Automaton</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 176.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Hatta Carter The Mad Inventor","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nB93Ofr1VtsysnX8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hatta Carter The Mad Inventor","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my \ntime. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings \nand aggressiveness.\nAgenda: I want the company of witty people and not cold \nautomata. I long for the chats I had with Alice.\nGift - Time Clocks: Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks \nto influence time. 1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases \nhis OL by 2 when defending against a threat. 2. Speed \nUp: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can \nact, immediately stopping anyone’s action regardless of the \nsituation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, \nit can act again thanks to this Gift.\nRabbit Automaton</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 176.","owner":"Hatta Carter The Mad Inventor","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-hatta-carter-the-mad-inventor-176","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":176,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my \ntime. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings \nand aggressiveness.\nAgenda: I want the company of witty people and not cold \nautomata. I long for the chats I had with Alice.\nGift - Time Clocks: Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks \nto influence time. 1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases \nhis OL by 2 when defending against a threat. 2. Speed \nUp: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can \nact, immediately stopping anyone’s action regardless of the \nsituation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, \nit can act again thanks to this Gift.\nRabbit Automaton</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want the company of witty people and not cold \nautomata. I long for the chats I had with Alice.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gTiJbKeBtxQ1SPdG","name":"Anne the Little Chatterer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"4f1ahFaT0GS7Y9gP","name":"Anne the Little Chatterer - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anne the Little Chatterer","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her \ninformed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy \nbecause I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.\n2 Nicholas the Huntsman</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her \ninformed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy \nbecause I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.\n2 Nicholas the Huntsman","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Anne the Little Chatterer","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jtrSmWgkHjQ2vTUH","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anne the Little Chatterer","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her \ninformed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy \nbecause I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.\n2 Nicholas the Huntsman</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","owner":"Anne the Little Chatterer","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-anne-the-little-chatterer-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her \ninformed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy \nbecause I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.\n2 Nicholas the Huntsman</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gbesf2SWWOaBwIpe","name":"Porcelain Dolls","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"az6aghVLYpbrzS3q","name":"Porcelain Dolls - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Dolls","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the devoted guards of the Porcelain \nPrincess. Everyone fears us for our martial ability.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 235.","positive":"We are the devoted guards of the Porcelain \nPrincess. Everyone fears us for our martial ability.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Porcelain Dolls","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AE0rYOzRp7LtxlGq","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Dolls","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the devoted guards of the Porcelain \nPrincess. Everyone fears us for our martial ability. \nAgenda: Fulfill every wish of the Porcelain Princess.\nGift - Armed Guard: Each Doll is armed differently. \nRoll 1 die: 1. Spear, the Doll can make exceptional jumps \nand can always keep an enemy at a distance; 2. Double \nknife, 2 attacks per Exchange; 3. Great Blade, once per \nScene inflicts 1 additional Wound; 4. Whip, 9 feet range, \nwhoever fails the Defense Check becomes entangled; 5. \nBlood, the blade of the weapon is soaked in Helga’s blood; \n6. Shield, +1 OL to defend themselves or an ally.\nEnd of Scene: By defeating the Porcelain Princess or \npersuading her away from Helga’s service, the Hunters will \nobtain the key to enter Helga’s palace. When questioned, \nthe Princess will reveal that her lady intends to perform \nan arcane rite during the night that involves sacrificing \nDorothea. Go to SCENE FOUR - The Red Witch of the \nSouth.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 235.","owner":"Porcelain Dolls","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-porcelain-dolls-235","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":235,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the devoted guards of the Porcelain \nPrincess. Everyone fears us for our martial ability. \nAgenda: Fulfill every wish of the Porcelain Princess.\nGift - Armed Guard: Each Doll is armed differently. \nRoll 1 die: 1. Spear, the Doll can make exceptional jumps \nand can always keep an enemy at a distance; 2. Double \nknife, 2 attacks per Exchange; 3. Great Blade, once per \nScene inflicts 1 additional Wound; 4. Whip, 9 feet range, \nwhoever fails the Defense Check becomes entangled; 5. \nBlood, the blade of the weapon is soaked in Helga’s blood; \n6. Shield, +1 OL to defend themselves or an ally.\nEnd of Scene: By defeating the Porcelain Princess or \npersuading her away from Helga’s service, the Hunters will \nobtain the key to enter Helga’s palace. When questioned, \nthe Princess will reveal that her lady intends to perform \nan arcane rite during the night that involves sacrificing \nDorothea. Go to SCENE FOUR - The Red Witch of the \nSouth.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Fulfill every wish of the Porcelain Princess.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gkCmYVYxpNbuxYqo","name":"Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for Revenge","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"CQIJiqS2jtk9oDpH","name":"Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for Revenge - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for Revenge","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 150.","positive":"I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for Revenge","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622287,"modifiedTime":1781557622287,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qC67M1d9hfsArVkx","name":"Gift - Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for Revenge","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Yvonne is in a spirit form and can only \ntruly be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs \nlife energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection \nand barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit \nis harmed by non-magical means, she still will suffer a \nWound. However, when Yvonne has no Wounds left, she \ndisappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all \nher Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical \nmeans. Once per Scene, Yvonne can call 3 Restless Spirits \nto her who will obey her will.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 150.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for Revenge","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622287,"modifiedTime":1781557622287,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZowmQCxK90RWUESG","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for Revenge","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.\nAgenda: Get revenge on Adrien and all those who ignored \nmy death / Set Paris ablaze with the fires of the dead.\nGift - Spirit: Yvonne is in a spirit form and can only \ntruly be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs \nlife energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection \nand barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit \nis harmed by non-magical means, she still will suffer a \nWound. However, when Yvonne has no Wounds left, she \ndisappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all \nher Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical \nmeans. Once per Scene, Yvonne can call 3 Restless Spirits \nto her who will obey her will.\nGift - Soul of Fire: Yvonne can manipulate fire at will. \nThis Gift only affects a fire that is already lit. Manipulating \nfire, for Yvonne, is considered an additional action. The fire \ninflicts 1 Wound and if the Defense Check is an Outcome \nwith a Cost, the target will continue to burn. During the \nfollowing Exchange, if not put out, the fire will inflict \n1 additional Wound. Thanks to her power, Yvonne can \nmultiply the width and size of a flame by up to ten times.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 150.","owner":"Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for Revenge","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622287,"modifiedTime":1781557622287,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-yvonne-the-spirit-who-longs-for-revenge-150","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":150,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.\nAgenda: Get revenge on Adrien and all those who ignored \nmy death / Set Paris ablaze with the fires of the dead.\nGift - Spirit: Yvonne is in a spirit form and can only \ntruly be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs \nlife energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection \nand barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit \nis harmed by non-magical means, she still will suffer a \nWound. However, when Yvonne has no Wounds left, she \ndisappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all \nher Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical \nmeans. Once per Scene, Yvonne can call 3 Restless Spirits \nto her who will obey her will.\nGift - Soul of Fire: Yvonne can manipulate fire at will. \nThis Gift only affects a fire that is already lit. Manipulating \nfire, for Yvonne, is considered an additional action. The fire \ninflicts 1 Wound and if the Defense Check is an Outcome \nwith a Cost, the target will continue to burn. During the \nfollowing Exchange, if not put out, the fire will inflict \n1 additional Wound. Thanks to her power, Yvonne can \nmultiply the width and size of a flame by up to ten times.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Get revenge on Adrien and all those who ignored \nmy death / Set Paris ablaze with the fires of the dead.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622287,"modifiedTime":1781557622287,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hBH7lEuepKz6wOED","name":"A group of faithful Paladins in the service of Saint George","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"PKIobwdbKfdkEUjQ","name":"A group of faithful Paladins in the service of Saint George - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"A group of faithful Paladins in the service of Saint George","source":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in the service of the great Saint \nGeorge himself and his word, for me, is law. Years of training \nhave made me adept at fighting the Broken Tales.\nNote: Each Paladin has a different Downside, indicated in \nthe Paladin Gift.</p>","notes":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 221.","positive":"I am a Paladin in the service of the great Saint \nGeorge himself and his word, for me, is law. Years of training \nhave made me adept at fighting the Broken Tales.\nNote: Each Paladin has a different Downside, indicated in \nthe Paladin Gift.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"A group of faithful Paladins in the service of Saint George","source":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624146,"modifiedTime":1781557624146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sevzcYmdfB3ir7os","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"A group of faithful Paladins in the service of Saint George","source":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a Paladin in the service of the great Saint \nGeorge himself and his word, for me, is law. Years of training \nhave made me adept at fighting the Broken Tales.\nNote: Each Paladin has a different Downside, indicated in \nthe Paladin Gift.\nGift - Paladins: Each Paladin has a name and a dedicated \nGift, and a Downside to add to the standard Descriptor. \nThe Storyteller rolls 1 die to decide which Paladin follows \nSaint George in the Witch Hunt. Saint Geoge has a number \nof Paladins equal to that of the Hunters he hunts.</p>","notes":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 221.","owner":"A group of faithful Paladins in the service of Saint George","source":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624146,"modifiedTime":1781557624146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-a-group-of-faithful-paladins-in-the-service-of-saint-george-221","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","adventureTitle":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":221,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a Paladin in the service of the great Saint \nGeorge himself and his word, for me, is law. Years of training \nhave made me adept at fighting the Broken Tales.\nNote: Each Paladin has a different Downside, indicated in \nthe Paladin Gift.\nGift - Paladins: Each Paladin has a name and a dedicated \nGift, and a Downside to add to the standard Descriptor. \nThe Storyteller rolls 1 die to decide which Paladin follows \nSaint George in the Witch Hunt. Saint Geoge has a number \nof Paladins equal to that of the Hunters he hunts.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624146,"modifiedTime":1781557624146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hT2hmZ0MV65immv8","name":"Edward the Miners’ Chief","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"hhEYCousw6i8WNm2","name":"Edward the Miners’ Chief - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Edward the Miners’ Chief","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn \nhis death. Everyone in the mine does what I say, and I hate \nforeigners who want to poke their nose into my work. I allow \nFrank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died.\nThe Cave of the \nGod Under the \nMine\nDescriptor: A large natural cave, which Arthur has made \ninto a home. You can enter only by descending from a narrow \nwell. In the north wall, the enormous pig head of the God \ngasps and groans as it waits to wake up.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 211.","positive":"I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn \nhis death. Everyone in the mine does what I say, and I hate \nforeigners who want to poke their nose into my work. I allow \nFrank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died.\nThe Cave of the \nGod Under the \nMine\nDescriptor: A large natural cave, which Arthur has made \ninto a home. You can enter only by descending from a narrow \nwell. In the north wall, the enormous pig head of the God \ngasps and groans as it waits to wake up.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Edward the Miners’ Chief","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623910,"modifiedTime":1781557623910,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eGpq0c5BJSNVEPIR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Edward the Miners’ Chief","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn \nhis death. Everyone in the mine does what I say, and I hate \nforeigners who want to poke their nose into my work. I allow \nFrank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died.\nThe Cave of the \nGod Under the \nMine\nDescriptor: A large natural cave, which Arthur has made \ninto a home. You can enter only by descending from a narrow \nwell. In the north wall, the enormous pig head of the God \ngasps and groans as it waits to wake up.\nGift - Arthur’s House: The mastermind behind the Pig \nHeads worked hard to make the Cave an intruder-proof \nhaven. If someone drops from the well, Arthur will be \nalerted (a Position Check can avoid this). At the bottom of \nthe well is a large tub that Arthur can fill with boiling water. \nWhoever arrives through the well suffers 1 Wound if they \nhave no way of avoiding the hot water. Inside the room, \nArthur can turn the lights on and off thanks to a system \nhe has invented, throwing the chamber into either light or \ndarkness. While intruders wander blindly, Arthur can use \nhis knowledge of the place to move freely.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 211.","owner":"Edward the Miners’ Chief","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623910,"modifiedTime":1781557623910,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-edward-the-miners-chief-211","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":211,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn \nhis death. Everyone in the mine does what I say, and I hate \nforeigners who want to poke their nose into my work. I allow \nFrank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died.\nThe Cave of the \nGod Under the \nMine\nDescriptor: A large natural cave, which Arthur has made \ninto a home. You can enter only by descending from a narrow \nwell. In the north wall, the enormous pig head of the God \ngasps and groans as it waits to wake up.\nGift - Arthur’s House: The mastermind behind the Pig \nHeads worked hard to make the Cave an intruder-proof \nhaven. If someone drops from the well, Arthur will be \nalerted (a Position Check can avoid this). At the bottom of \nthe well is a large tub that Arthur can fill with boiling water. \nWhoever arrives through the well suffers 1 Wound if they \nhave no way of avoiding the hot water. Inside the room, \nArthur can turn the lights on and off thanks to a system \nhe has invented, throwing the chamber into either light or \ndarkness. While intruders wander blindly, Arthur can use \nhis knowledge of the place to move freely.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623910,"modifiedTime":1781557623910,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hacLdQzJ1rB6IRER","name":"Emma the Childhood Friend","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"bTdFuNDgMNqK4RpA","name":"Emma the Childhood Friend - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Emma the Childhood Friend","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a childhood friend of Clarence and have \na special relationship with him. He has always promised that \nhe will take me away from this place, but I know that he will \nnever abandon his brothers. I understand that he has a big \nsecret, but tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark.\nThe Orchard\nDescriptor: A large apple orchard which, before the arrival \nof the factories, was one of the main sources of work in the \ncity. Now, however, it is abandoned and represents a home for \nall those who cannot get a job.\nWhen the Hunters roam the orchard, roll 1 die, or present \nthe encounters in sequence.\n1-2 The orchard: The trees have been neglected and on \nthe ground there are still abandoned tools and baskets for \nharvesting apples. A sign next to a tool shed reads “Gift \ncourtesy of the Browne family” .\n3-4 Clarence’s shack: A rickety rundown house with a \nthatched roof. Inside, it is possible to find a rusty key that \nsays “slaughterhouse” and a sketched map of the mines that \nsays “well” . Around the hut there are always 1d6 + 2 Pig \nHeads.\n5-6 Clarence: The youngest of the Browne brothers is \nlying on the ground, visibly drunk, under an apple tree. \nClarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take \nthem off guard.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","positive":"I am a childhood friend of Clarence and have \na special relationship with him. He has always promised that \nhe will take me away from this place, but I know that he will \nnever abandon his brothers. I understand that he has a big \nsecret, but tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark.\nThe Orchard\nDescriptor: A large apple orchard which, before the arrival \nof the factories, was one of the main sources of work in the \ncity. Now, however, it is abandoned and represents a home for \nall those who cannot get a job.\nWhen the Hunters roam the orchard, roll 1 die, or present \nthe encounters in sequence.\n1-2 The orchard: The trees have been neglected and on \nthe ground there are still abandoned tools and baskets for \nharvesting apples. A sign next to a tool shed reads “Gift \ncourtesy of the Browne family” .\n3-4 Clarence’s shack: A rickety rundown house with a \nthatched roof. Inside, it is possible to find a rusty key that \nsays “slaughterhouse” and a sketched map of the mines that \nsays “well” . Around the hut there are always 1d6 + 2 Pig \nHeads.\n5-6 Clarence: The youngest of the Browne brothers is \nlying on the ground, visibly drunk, under an apple tree. \nClarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take \nthem off guard.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Emma the Childhood Friend","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QHqCroREZSXamXRg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Emma the Childhood Friend","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a childhood friend of Clarence and have \na special relationship with him. He has always promised that \nhe will take me away from this place, but I know that he will \nnever abandon his brothers. I understand that he has a big \nsecret, but tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark.\nThe Orchard\nDescriptor: A large apple orchard which, before the arrival \nof the factories, was one of the main sources of work in the \ncity. Now, however, it is abandoned and represents a home for \nall those who cannot get a job.\nWhen the Hunters roam the orchard, roll 1 die, or present \nthe encounters in sequence.\n1-2 The orchard: The trees have been neglected and on \nthe ground there are still abandoned tools and baskets for \nharvesting apples. A sign next to a tool shed reads “Gift \ncourtesy of the Browne family” .\n3-4 Clarence’s shack: A rickety rundown house with a \nthatched roof. Inside, it is possible to find a rusty key that \nsays “slaughterhouse” and a sketched map of the mines that \nsays “well” . Around the hut there are always 1d6 + 2 Pig \nHeads.\n5-6 Clarence: The youngest of the Browne brothers is \nlying on the ground, visibly drunk, under an apple tree. \nClarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take \nthem off guard.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","owner":"Emma the Childhood Friend","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-emma-the-childhood-friend-208","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":208,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a childhood friend of Clarence and have \na special relationship with him. He has always promised that \nhe will take me away from this place, but I know that he will \nnever abandon his brothers. I understand that he has a big \nsecret, but tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark.\nThe Orchard\nDescriptor: A large apple orchard which, before the arrival \nof the factories, was one of the main sources of work in the \ncity. Now, however, it is abandoned and represents a home for \nall those who cannot get a job.\nWhen the Hunters roam the orchard, roll 1 die, or present \nthe encounters in sequence.\n1-2 The orchard: The trees have been neglected and on \nthe ground there are still abandoned tools and baskets for \nharvesting apples. A sign next to a tool shed reads “Gift \ncourtesy of the Browne family” .\n3-4 Clarence’s shack: A rickety rundown house with a \nthatched roof. Inside, it is possible to find a rusty key that \nsays “slaughterhouse” and a sketched map of the mines that \nsays “well” . Around the hut there are always 1d6 + 2 Pig \nHeads.\n5-6 Clarence: The youngest of the Browne brothers is \nlying on the ground, visibly drunk, under an apple tree. \nClarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take \nthem off guard.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hngJhB848FoERbHT","name":"Satu","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"kD9rsTUGhWqpepba","name":"Satu - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Satu","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a former dancer who has lost everything. \nI am but a shadow of my former self.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","positive":"I am a former dancer who has lost everything. \nI am but a shadow of my former self.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Satu","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622625,"modifiedTime":1781557622625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1o0Y4WyArRt6Rp4K","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Satu","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a former dancer who has lost everything. \nI am but a shadow of my former self.\nAgenda: Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep \ngoing.\nErik</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","owner":"Satu","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622625,"modifiedTime":1781557622625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-satu-162","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":162,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a former dancer who has lost everything. \nI am but a shadow of my former self.\nAgenda: Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep \ngoing.\nErik</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep \ngoing.\nErik","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622625,"modifiedTime":1781557622625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"i2RmsiiX8qAFnhL8","name":"Bardolf’s personal guard","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Ls9YOxcjMj7umEiq","name":"Bardolf’s personal guard - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bardolf’s personal guard","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are long-time mercenaries, paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 206.","positive":"We are long-time mercenaries, paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Bardolf’s personal guard","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623800,"modifiedTime":1781557623800,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WzgcOraH21iscXIe","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bardolf’s personal guard","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are long-time mercenaries, paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 206.","owner":"Bardolf’s personal guard","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623800,"modifiedTime":1781557623800,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"c