{"_id":"j5U4JjSkqRDnG7Qe","name":"Martha Browne the Mother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"TGp40gz8iBrHXV2o","name":"Martha Browne the Mother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Martha Browne the Mother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the mother of three brothers, and I am \nso old that I have almost completely lost my sight. My son \nFrank takes care of me, but he doesn’t tell me anything. I \nam convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a \nmother tells me so.\nEmma the Childhood Friend</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","positive":"I am the mother of three brothers, and I am \nso old that I have almost completely lost my sight. My son \nFrank takes care of me, but he doesn’t tell me anything. I \nam convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a \nmother tells me so.\nEmma the Childhood Friend","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Martha Browne the Mother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mAaW8JTzaPhNJgxI","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Martha Browne the Mother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the mother of three brothers, and I am \nso old that I have almost completely lost my sight. My son \nFrank takes care of me, but he doesn’t tell me anything. I \nam convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a \nmother tells me so.\nEmma the Childhood Friend</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","owner":"Martha Browne the Mother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-martha-browne-the-mother-208","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":208,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the mother of three brothers, and I am \nso old that I have almost completely lost my sight. My son \nFrank takes care of me, but he doesn’t tell me anything. I \nam convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a \nmother tells me so.\nEmma the Childhood Friend</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"kpMF0fMVRyAIosq4","name":"The poor people of Paris","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"AbHDvWMw8dKopOIb","name":"The poor people of Paris - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The poor people of Paris","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the poor and desperate who have \nno other home but the catacombs.\nWhen the Hunters interact with the poor, you can \ndecide or roll a die to learn their history and what \ninformation they can give.\n1. Marie lost all her children and her husband to \nthe war. She had grown fond of little Yvonne and \nweeps for the end she met.\n2. Claude is a soldier who lost a leg in the war. \nHe wanted to go into business with the Ravens \nwho live in the east side of the catacombs, but \nthey are all young and arrogant and have \nturned down his offer.\n3. Brigitte is a little girl who lost her parents \nduring the most recent plague. She knew \nYvonne and occasionally went to sell candles \nwith her. She knows that Adrien had taken \nYvonne into his service to do small jobs in the \nsacristy.\n4. Jerome is an old man who has almost \ncompletely lost his sight. In the past, he was \na skilled goldsmith, until his blindness left \nhim without a job. He will say that he heard</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 148.","positive":"We are the poor and desperate who have \nno other home but the catacombs.\nWhen the Hunters interact with the poor, you can \ndecide or roll a die to learn their history and what \ninformation they can give.\n1. Marie lost all her children and her husband to \nthe war. She had grown fond of little Yvonne and \nweeps for the end she met.\n2. Claude is a soldier who lost a leg in the war. \nHe wanted to go into business with the Ravens \nwho live in the east side of the catacombs, but \nthey are all young and arrogant and have \nturned down his offer.\n3. Brigitte is a little girl who lost her parents \nduring the most recent plague. She knew \nYvonne and occasionally went to sell candles \nwith her. She knows that Adrien had taken \nYvonne into his service to do small jobs in the \nsacristy.\n4. Jerome is an old man who has almost \ncompletely lost his sight. In the past, he was \na skilled goldsmith, until his blindness left \nhim without a job. He will say that he heard","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The poor people of Paris","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622234,"modifiedTime":1781557622234,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ThJhEzxxQoZDiOCA","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The poor people of Paris","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the poor and desperate who have \nno other home but the catacombs.\nWhen the Hunters interact with the poor, you can \ndecide or roll a die to learn their history and what \ninformation they can give.\n1. Marie lost all her children and her husband to \nthe war. She had grown fond of little Yvonne and \nweeps for the end she met.\n2. Claude is a soldier who lost a leg in the war. \nHe wanted to go into business with the Ravens \nwho live in the east side of the catacombs, but \nthey are all young and arrogant and have \nturned down his offer.\n3. Brigitte is a little girl who lost her parents \nduring the most recent plague. She knew \nYvonne and occasionally went to sell candles \nwith her. She knows that Adrien had taken \nYvonne into his service to do small jobs in the \nsacristy.\n4. Jerome is an old man who has almost \ncompletely lost his sight. In the past, he was \na skilled goldsmith, until his blindness left \nhim without a job. He will say that he heard</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 148.","owner":"The poor people of Paris","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622234,"modifiedTime":1781557622234,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-the-poor-people-of-paris-148","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":148,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the poor and desperate who have \nno other home but the catacombs.\nWhen the Hunters interact with the poor, you can \ndecide or roll a die to learn their history and what \ninformation they can give.\n1. Marie lost all her children and her husband to \nthe war. She had grown fond of little Yvonne and \nweeps for the end she met.\n2. Claude is a soldier who lost a leg in the war. \nHe wanted to go into business with the Ravens \nwho live in the east side of the catacombs, but \nthey are all young and arrogant and have \nturned down his offer.\n3. Brigitte is a little girl who lost her parents \nduring the most recent plague. She knew \nYvonne and occasionally went to sell candles \nwith her. She knows that Adrien had taken \nYvonne into his service to do small jobs in the \nsacristy.\n4. Jerome is an old man who has almost \ncompletely lost his sight. In the past, he was \na skilled goldsmith, until his blindness left \nhim without a job. He will say that he heard</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622234,"modifiedTime":1781557622234,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"mLo5BPNKWX8NhOvf","name":"The Tunnels","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"tBx4A4GeYZbZVmcd","name":"The Tunnels - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Tunnels","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A dense network of tunnels \nthat all look alike.\nGetting lost in the Tunnels will force \nthe Hunters to waste several hours \nbefore finding the exit.\n4 - The Ravens’ Hideout: This part of \nthe catacombs is only frequented by scoundrels who had \nbusiness with Adrien. A couple of broken bottles of absinthe \nare scattered among some makeshift beds. To those with a \nsensitive sense of smell, the scent of alcohol is still strong. \nAn old dagger and a wooden crucifix are the only other \nnoteworthy details.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 149.","positive":"A dense network of tunnels \nthat all look alike.\nGetting lost in the Tunnels will force \nthe Hunters to waste several hours \nbefore finding the exit.\n4 - The Ravens’ Hideout: This part of \nthe catacombs is only frequented by scoundrels who had \nbusiness with Adrien. A couple of broken bottles of absinthe \nare scattered among some makeshift beds. To those with a \nsensitive sense of smell, the scent of alcohol is still strong. \nAn old dagger and a wooden crucifix are the only other \nnoteworthy details.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Tunnels","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622268,"modifiedTime":1781557622268,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lyNx28RlkFO5ohR8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Tunnels","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A dense network of tunnels \nthat all look alike.\nGetting lost in the Tunnels will force \nthe Hunters to waste several hours \nbefore finding the exit.\n4 - The Ravens’ Hideout: This part of \nthe catacombs is only frequented by scoundrels who had \nbusiness with Adrien. A couple of broken bottles of absinthe \nare scattered among some makeshift beds. To those with a \nsensitive sense of smell, the scent of alcohol is still strong. \nAn old dagger and a wooden crucifix are the only other \nnoteworthy details.\nInformation: If the Hunters arrive here before sunset, they \nwill find Olivier preparing his escape. When night falls, they \nwill find his charred corpse.\nOlivier the Raven on the run</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 149.","owner":"The Tunnels","source":"The Smile in the Darkness","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622268,"modifiedTime":1781557622268,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-the-tunnels-149","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":149,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A dense network of tunnels \nthat all look alike.\nGetting lost in the Tunnels will force \nthe Hunters to waste several hours \nbefore finding the exit.\n4 - The Ravens’ Hideout: This part of \nthe catacombs is only frequented by scoundrels who had \nbusiness with Adrien. A couple of broken bottles of absinthe \nare scattered among some makeshift beds. To those with a \nsensitive sense of smell, the scent of alcohol is still strong. \nAn old dagger and a wooden crucifix are the only other \nnoteworthy details.\nInformation: If the Hunters arrive here before sunset, they \nwill find Olivier preparing his escape. When night falls, they \nwill find his charred corpse.\nOlivier the Raven on the run</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622268,"modifiedTime":1781557622268,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"nm5dwWRqcfXJR0R1","name":"Skutt the Moose","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"mZ4x1TQKS9Ayh2nF","name":"Skutt the Moose - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Skutt the Moose","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a majestic and magnificent moose, \nravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr’s magic which \nkeeps me alive.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 186.","positive":"I am a majestic and magnificent moose, \nravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr’s magic which \nkeeps me alive.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Skutt the Moose","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623290,"modifiedTime":1781557623290,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"57THB9AN4KFSyvjD","name":"Gift - Spectral Presence","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Skutt the Moose","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Skutt cannot truly be \neliminated as long as Tuvstarr’s wish keeps him alive. \nThe moose can move through fog, disappearing and \nreappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one \ncan stop or impede Skutt’s movement. When he suffers \nhis third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the \nfollowing Scene.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 186.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Skutt the Moose","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623290,"modifiedTime":1781557623290,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bD28HWvzuyREpv8Y","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Skutt the Moose","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a majestic and magnificent moose, \nravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr’s magic which \nkeeps me alive.\nAgenda: I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the \nblack pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can’t get in \n/ Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the \nworld rot away.\nGift - Spectral Presence: Skutt cannot truly be \neliminated as long as Tuvstarr’s wish keeps him alive. \nThe moose can move through fog, disappearing and \nreappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one \ncan stop or impede Skutt’s movement. When he suffers \nhis third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the \nfollowing Scene.\nInformation: Skutt is a Main NPC that Hunters can \nencounter in any Scene. He will always appear accompanied \nby a thick fog, stinking of rot, and surrounded by pale \nmoths. From his horns, like a ghostly veil, hangs the torn \nfabric of a knightly cloak, and a spear is half driven into \nhis body.\nIf the Hunters fight: Skutt is not interested in the fight \nbut is still a proud animal, so he will lash out at the enemy, \ncharging with his antlers. \nIf the Hunters talk to Skutt: He can tell how he took \nTuvstarr to the sacred pond, deep in the woods. Whatever \nTuvstarr did by diving into the lake, it wreaked havoc on the</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 186.","owner":"Skutt the Moose","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623291,"modifiedTime":1781557623291,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-skutt-the-moose-186","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":186,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a majestic and magnificent moose, \nravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr’s magic which \nkeeps me alive.\nAgenda: I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the \nblack pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can’t get in \n/ Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the \nworld rot away.\nGift - Spectral Presence: Skutt cannot truly be \neliminated as long as Tuvstarr’s wish keeps him alive. \nThe moose can move through fog, disappearing and \nreappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one \ncan stop or impede Skutt’s movement. When he suffers \nhis third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the \nfollowing Scene.\nInformation: Skutt is a Main NPC that Hunters can \nencounter in any Scene. He will always appear accompanied \nby a thick fog, stinking of rot, and surrounded by pale \nmoths. From his horns, like a ghostly veil, hangs the torn \nfabric of a knightly cloak, and a spear is half driven into \nhis body.\nIf the Hunters fight: Skutt is not interested in the fight \nbut is still a proud animal, so he will lash out at the enemy, \ncharging with his antlers. \nIf the Hunters talk to Skutt: He can tell how he took \nTuvstarr to the sacred pond, deep in the woods. Whatever \nTuvstarr did by diving into the lake, it wreaked havoc on the</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the \nblack pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can’t get in \n/ Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the \nworld rot away.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623291,"modifiedTime":1781557623291,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"o7QQfZR11eFM1Hrn","name":"Erik","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"zU1uSSOcusgVPuG1","name":"Erik - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Erik","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a lively child who can never sit still.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","positive":"I am a lively child who can never sit still.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Erik","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"a3etM74GBUxWAqU7","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Erik","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a lively child who can never sit still. \nAgenda: Understand who Andersen really is, and why he \ntook my mom and me out of the misery we lived in.\nChristian</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","owner":"Erik","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-erik-162","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":162,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a lively child who can never sit still. \nAgenda: Understand who Andersen really is, and why he \ntook my mom and me out of the misery we lived in.\nChristian</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Understand who Andersen really is, and why he \ntook my mom and me out of the misery we lived in.\nChristian","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"pEU3m4b0ZqZh6qEA","name":"Geppetto Gullible Alchemist Apprentice","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"UVOgY6G0CcCGNmOr","name":"Geppetto Gullible Alchemist Apprentice - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Geppetto Gullible Alchemist Apprentice","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a poor man who has always been looking \nfor a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy \nfrom master Antonio.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 135.","positive":"I am a poor man who has always been looking \nfor a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy \nfrom master Antonio.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Geppetto Gullible Alchemist Apprentice","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621827,"modifiedTime":1781557621827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RiDbhlPP3sz9qsU2","name":"Gift - Improvised Alchemist","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Geppetto Gullible Alchemist Apprentice","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Geppetto can rely on \na series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that \nhe hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, \nroll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact \nwith the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty \nfeet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 \nStench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to \nall actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air \nBomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked \nback and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can \nsuffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his \nalchemical concoctions.\nThe Old Carpenter’s Shop</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 135.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Geppetto Gullible Alchemist Apprentice","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621827,"modifiedTime":1781557621827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"EZ2v4CYGVaNB5Khf","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Geppetto Gullible Alchemist Apprentice","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a poor man who has always been looking \nfor a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy \nfrom master Antonio.\nAgenda: Pretend to be Carlo’s father and find him / Obtain \nthe secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy.\nGift - Improvised Alchemist: Geppetto can rely on \na series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that \nhe hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, \nroll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact \nwith the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty \nfeet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 \nStench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to \nall actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air \nBomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked \nback and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can \nsuffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his \nalchemical concoctions.\nThe Old Carpenter’s Shop\nDescriptor: Once the alchemical laboratory of Mastro \nAntonio, the carpenter’s shop was abandoned after the \ndiscovery of the corpses. \nInformation: \n ◆ The place is a normal carpenter’s shop, abandoned for \nsome time. The only element that catches the Hunters’ \nattention is a series of chisels on the wall, with one</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 135.","owner":"Geppetto Gullible Alchemist Apprentice","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621827,"modifiedTime":1781557621827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-geppetto-gullible-alchemist-apprentice-135","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":135,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a poor man who has always been looking \nfor a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy \nfrom master Antonio.\nAgenda: Pretend to be Carlo’s father and find him / Obtain \nthe secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy.\nGift - Improvised Alchemist: Geppetto can rely on \na series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that \nhe hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, \nroll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact \nwith the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty \nfeet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 \nStench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to \nall actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air \nBomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked \nback and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can \nsuffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his \nalchemical concoctions.\nThe Old Carpenter’s Shop\nDescriptor: Once the alchemical laboratory of Mastro \nAntonio, the carpenter’s shop was abandoned after the \ndiscovery of the corpses. \nInformation: \n ◆ The place is a normal carpenter’s shop, abandoned for \nsome time. The only element that catches the Hunters’ \nattention is a series of chisels on the wall, with one</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Pretend to be Carlo’s father and find him / Obtain \nthe secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621827,"modifiedTime":1781557621827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"q91gTXG8nH7JQ89X","name":"The Guards of Gerard Dubois","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"WBdsDzUEWe0fEKT2","name":"The Guards of Gerard Dubois - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Guards of Gerard Dubois","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are duty-bound - as long as we get \npaid.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","positive":"We are duty-bound - as long as we get \npaid.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Guards of Gerard Dubois","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4nZAc0IDW2rQ9W3L","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Guards of Gerard Dubois","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are duty-bound - as long as we get \npaid.\nAgenda: Vincent is the boss. We’ll follow his lead.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","owner":"The Guards of Gerard Dubois","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-