{"_id":"ryp8y4IAJmHJYzmM","name":"Medoro The Old Bear","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"WwsCZFKNtDZegjRg","name":"Medoro The Old Bear - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Medoro The Old Bear","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its \nfur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I am happy to \nserve her. I have retained most of my bestial strength, despite \nmy age.\nThe Villa\nDescriptor: A large manor house, once flamboyant, but \nnow covered in dust and mold.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 138.","positive":"I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its \nfur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I am happy to \nserve her. I have retained most of my bestial strength, despite \nmy age.\nThe Villa\nDescriptor: A large manor house, once flamboyant, but \nnow covered in dust and mold.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Medoro The Old Bear","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621890,"modifiedTime":1781557621890,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"giyc3XeO0t2YNFk8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Medoro The Old Bear","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its \nfur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I am happy to \nserve her. I have retained most of my bestial strength, despite \nmy age.\nThe Villa\nDescriptor: A large manor house, once flamboyant, but \nnow covered in dust and mold. \nInformation: \n ◆ Azzurra is wandering around the Villa and will not \nhesitate to appear and confront intruders.\n ◆ In the dining room, there is a huge painting on the \nnorth wall depicting a whale swallowing an entire \nship. By looking behind the painting, the Hunters can \nactivate the mechanism which opens the secret door to \naccess the Secret Laboratory.\n ◆ The remaining 4 Marionettes covered in human skin \nroam around the Villa, but they only act on Azzurra’s \norders.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 138.","owner":"Medoro The Old Bear","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621890,"modifiedTime":1781557621890,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-medoro-the-old-bear-138","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":138,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its \nfur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I am happy to \nserve her. I have retained most of my bestial strength, despite \nmy age.\nThe Villa\nDescriptor: A large manor house, once flamboyant, but \nnow covered in dust and mold. \nInformation: \n ◆ Azzurra is wandering around the Villa and will not \nhesitate to appear and confront intruders.\n ◆ In the dining room, there is a huge painting on the \nnorth wall depicting a whale swallowing an entire \nship. By looking behind the painting, the Hunters can \nactivate the mechanism which opens the secret door to \naccess the Secret Laboratory.\n ◆ The remaining 4 Marionettes covered in human skin \nroam around the Villa, but they only act on Azzurra’s \norders.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621890,"modifiedTime":1781557621890,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"sLUiuETmHESMEZVo","name":"Lowe the Coward Henchman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"DKyA1asoHpsE0KIP","name":"Lowe the Coward Henchman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward Henchman","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I’m an eternal coward \nwho has been given a monstrous aspect \nby fate. I can adapt to any situation \nand am quick to jump to the winning \nside.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226.","positive":"I’m an eternal coward \nwho has been given a monstrous aspect \nby fate. I can adapt to any situation \nand am quick to jump to the winning \nside.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Lowe the Coward Henchman","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZbkukJf8bpnk7gx9","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward Henchman","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I’m an eternal coward \nwho has been given a monstrous aspect \nby fate. I can adapt to any situation \nand am quick to jump to the winning \nside.\nAgenda: To help Dorothea in her \nmission, with the hope of recovering \nfrom my condition / Save my life, no \nmatter who I have to betray.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226.","owner":"Lowe the Coward Henchman","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-lowe-the-coward-henchman-226","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":226,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I’m an eternal coward \nwho has been given a monstrous aspect \nby fate. I can adapt to any situation \nand am quick to jump to the winning \nside.\nAgenda: To help Dorothea in her \nmission, with the hope of recovering \nfrom my condition / Save my life, no \nmatter who I have to betray.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To help Dorothea in her \nmission, with the hope of recovering \nfrom my condition / Save my life, no \nmatter who I have to betray.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"snbKEa22mAGkuDRa","name":"OZena (Dorothea)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"VdPPhUVHR3e10BP9","name":"OZena (Dorothea) - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"OZena (Dorothea)","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young girl who wants to return to \nher world. The disease that afflicts me has ruined my face \nand with it all the hopes of a normal life. I am willing to do \nanything to heal, which is why I became a witch killer.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 229.","positive":"I am a young girl who wants to return to \nher world. The disease that afflicts me has ruined my face \nand with it all the hopes of a normal life. I am willing to do \nanything to heal, which is why I became a witch killer.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"OZena (Dorothea)","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624341,"modifiedTime":1781557624341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7JaUZZBiI7hHNaY9","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"OZena (Dorothea)","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young girl who wants to return to \nher world. The disease that afflicts me has ruined my face \nand with it all the hopes of a normal life. I am willing to do \nanything to heal, which is why I became a witch killer.\nAgenda: Kill every witch Henkle points out to me and \nretrieve all four pieces of the Compass Rose.\nGift - The Silver Slippers: The wearer of this magical \nartifact can move through folds in space, disappearing and \nreappearing in a flash. Dorothea can move freely up to a \nmaximum distance of thirty feet without anyone preventing \nher, but she must be able to see the point of arrival. Once \nper Scene, Dorothea can take a longer journey and reappear \nin any place she has seen at least once.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 229.","owner":"OZena (Dorothea)","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624341,"modifiedTime":1781557624341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-ozena-dorothea-229","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":229,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young girl who wants to return to \nher world. The disease that afflicts me has ruined my face \nand with it all the hopes of a normal life. I am willing to do \nanything to heal, which is why I became a witch killer.\nAgenda: Kill every witch Henkle points out to me and \nretrieve all four pieces of the Compass Rose.\nGift - The Silver Slippers: The wearer of this magical \nartifact can move through folds in space, disappearing and \nreappearing in a flash. Dorothea can move freely up to a \nmaximum distance of thirty feet without anyone preventing \nher, but she must be able to see the point of arrival. Once \nper Scene, Dorothea can take a longer journey and reappear \nin any place she has seen at least once.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Kill every witch Henkle points out to me and \nretrieve all four pieces of the Compass Rose.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624341,"modifiedTime":1781557624341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"t6XKWn7xYmosypDY","name":"Nicholas the Huntsman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"UCRMs9eq30HszBuM","name":"Nicholas the Huntsman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nicholas the Huntsman","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to \nshow off in front of Baron Gerard.\n3 Genevieve the Chemist</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to \nshow off in front of Baron Gerard.\n3 Genevieve the Chemist","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Nicholas the Huntsman","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dx2t3KLKYynEx2d6","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nicholas the Huntsman","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to \nshow off in front of Baron Gerard.\n3 Genevieve the Chemist</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","owner":"Nicholas the Huntsman","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-nicholas-the-huntsman-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to \nshow off in front of Baron Gerard.\n3 Genevieve the Chemist</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uAa26FLFmPmES1H8","name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"HoBp42ZvW280Sopa","name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Everyone thinks I’m crazy and maybe they’re \nright. I don’t feel any fear and I can see beneath the surface of \nthose who pretend they are normal.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 228.","positive":"Everyone thinks I’m crazy and maybe they’re \nright. I don’t feel any fear and I can see beneath the surface of \nthose who pretend they are normal.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624309,"modifiedTime":1781557624309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nxx7sIfMR9VU5rC4","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: Everyone thinks I’m crazy and maybe they’re \nright. I don’t feel any fear and I can see beneath the surface of \nthose who pretend they are normal.\nAgenda: I follow OZena because I can see past her pain. \nThere is another world, the one where she comes from and \nwhere I want to go too.\nEnd of Scene: Margareta asks the Hunters to save little \nKlaus, offering to reveal all her secrets in exchange for the \nlittle one’s safety. If the Hunters set out to save Klaus go \nto SCENE THREE - In the Swamp . If, on the other hand, \nthey decide to stay in the village or split up, for those who \nremain, go to the FOURTH SCENE - OZena’s Attack.\nTHIRD SCENE – In the Swamp\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You don’t have to go too \nfar into the swamp before you hear little Klaus scream. You \nrun to a small clearing where Hirnloser puts a sickle to the \nchild’s throat. He is near an old, abandoned shed from which \nsuddenly emerges a huge figure covered in grotesque armor \nmade of debris. Hirnloser stares at you, his eyes pools of pure \nmadness. “ And while we dance here in our little puppet show, \nthe real performance unfolds in the village, ” the madman \ncries and smiles maliciously, as you realize that you have \nbeen lured into a trap.\nPlace: A clearing in the swamp twenty minutes’ walk from \nGelb.\nTime: It is late morning and the sun filters through the \ntrees.\nInformation: Hirnloser and Dose want to engage the \nHunters to give Dorothea time to kill Margareta. \n ◆ Hirnloser is insane but he doesn’t really want to kill \nKlaus. It will soon become clear that he uses the child \nas a shield and lever to keep the Hunters busy.\n ◆ If Lowe is present, he will try to surprise the Hunters \nfrom behind but will flee at the slightest sign of danger.\nDose The Tin Man</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 228.","owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624325,"modifiedTime":1781557624325,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-hirnloser-the-scarecrow-228","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":228,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: Everyone thinks I’m crazy and maybe they’re \nright. I don’t feel any fear and I can see beneath the surface of \nthose who pretend they are normal.\nAgenda: I follow OZena because I can see past her pain. \nThere is another world, the one where she comes from and \nwhere I want to go too.\nEnd of Scene: Margareta asks the Hunters to save little \nKlaus, offering to reveal all her secrets in exchange for the \nlittle one’s safety. If the Hunters set out to save Klaus go \nto SCENE THREE - In the Swamp . If, on the other hand, \nthey decide to stay in the village or split up, for those who \nremain, go to the FOURTH SCENE - OZena’s Attack.\nTHIRD SCENE – In the Swamp\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You don’t have to go too \nfar into the swamp before you hear little Klaus scream. You \nrun to a small clearing where Hirnloser puts a sickle to the \nchild’s throat. He is near an old, abandoned shed from which \nsuddenly emerges a huge figure covered in grotesque armor \nmade of debris. Hirnloser stares at you, his eyes pools of pure \nmadness. “ And while we dance here in our little puppet show, \nthe real performance unfolds in the village, ” the madman \ncries and smiles maliciously, as you realize that you have \nbeen lured into a trap.\nPlace: A clearing in the swamp twenty minutes’ walk from \nGelb.\nTime: It is late morning and the sun filters through the \ntrees.\nInformation: Hirnloser and Dose want to engage the \nHunters to give Dorothea time to kill Margareta. \n ◆ Hirnloser is insane but he doesn’t really want to kill \nKlaus. It will soon become clear that he uses the child \nas a shield and lever to keep the Hunters busy.\n ◆ If Lowe is present, he will try to surprise the Hunters \nfrom behind but will flee at the slightest sign of danger.\nDose The Tin Man</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I follow OZena because I can see past her pain. \nThere is another world, the one where she comes from and \nwhere I want to go too.\nEnd of Scene: Margareta asks the Hunters to save little \nKlaus, offering to reveal all her secrets in exchange for the \nlittle one’s safety. If the Hunters set out to save Klaus go \nto SCENE THREE - In the Swamp . If, on the other hand, \nthey decide to stay in the village or split up, for those who \nremain, go to the FOURTH SCENE - OZena’s Attack.\nTHIRD SCENE – In the Swamp\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You don’t have to go too \nfar into the swamp before you hear little Klaus scream. You \nrun to a small clearing where Hirnloser puts a sickle to the \nchild’s throat. He is near an old, abandoned shed from which \nsuddenly emerges a huge figure covered in grotesque armor \nmade of debris. Hirnloser stares at you, his eyes pools of pure \nmadness. “ And while we dance here in our little puppet show, \nthe real performance unfolds in the village, ” the madman \ncries and smiles maliciously, as you realize that you have \nbeen lured into a trap.\nPlace: A clearing in the swamp twenty minutes’ walk from \nGelb.\nTime: It is late morning and the sun filters through the \ntrees.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624325,"modifiedTime":1781557624325,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uJq1AyRkyjQNIM9D","name":"The Villagers of Emerald","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"y1Oknpk77XGUWQdO","name":"The Villagers of Emerald - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Villagers of Emerald","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are poor villagers changed by a wish we \nmade.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 243.","positive":"We are poor villagers changed by a wish we \nmade.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Villagers of Emerald","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624772,"modifiedTime":1781557624772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WxpFgsh2PnLeCFBO","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Villagers of Emerald","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are poor villagers changed by a wish we \nmade. \nAgenda: We hate Henkle for what he did to us, but we serve \nhim in the hope that we can make another wish.\nGift - Careful What you Wish For: Each Villager has \nmade a wish, but it has not had the desired effects. Roll 1 die \nto see what mutation has developed: 1. Wish for Wealth: \nThe NPC spits out gold coins mixed with bile. With a single \naction, they can hit up to 3 targets at a distance of 15 feet; \n2. Wish for Beauty: The NPC warps their body so as \nalways to look beautiful in the eyes of the beholder. When \nthere is more than one subject in view, their body changes \nconstantly. Whoever witnesses the show receives 1 Penalty \non their Checks out of disgust; 3. Wish for Health: The \nNPC’s body regenerates as their hair and body hair grow \nout of proportion. The NPC recovers 1 Wound as soon as it \nloses 1, making them effectively immortal. The effect of the \nWound suffered is applied, so the NPC can be defeated, but \nwill regenerate on its turn to act; 4. Wish for Skill: The \nNPC raises their OL to Medium; 5. The NPC can no longer \nsleep because they are obsessed with the idea of working, \nand will constantly be chattering nonsense; 5. Wish to \nGrow Up: The NPC is a child with a body of a giant while \ntheir head has remained the same as before. They can take \n2 extra Wounds and inflict 1 additional Wound when they \nunleash their strength; 6. Wish for Love: The NPC has \nmerged with the one they love, literally obtaining the desire \nto “become one. ” As a double body the NPC can act twice.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are two Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nWhen Henkle realizes that Dorothea does not have \nthe missing pieces of the Compass Rose with her: \nhe will take off on the balloon as soon as it is ready, and \nthen activate the power of the incomplete Rose.\nIf Dorothea realizes that Henkle is willing to \nabandon her to return to the future: she will do \nanything to reach the man, begging him not to abandon \nher.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 243.","owner":"The Villagers of Emerald","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624772,"modifiedTime":1781557624772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-villagers-of-emerald-243","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":243,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are poor villagers changed by a wish we \nmade. \nAgenda: We hate Henkle for what he did to us, but we serve \nhim in the hope that we can make another wish.\nGift - Careful What you Wish For: Each Villager has \nmade a wish, but it has not had the desired effects. Roll 1 die \nto see what mutation has developed: 1. Wish for Wealth: \nThe NPC spits out gold coins mixed with bile. With a single \naction, they can hit up to 3 targets at a distance of 15 feet; \n2. Wish for Beauty: The NPC warps their body so as \nalways to look beautiful in the eyes of the beholder. When \nthere is more than one subject in view, their body changes \nconstantly. Whoever witnesses the show receives 1 Penalty \non their Checks out of disgust; 3. Wish for Health: The \nNPC’s body regenerates as their hair and body hair grow \nout of proportion. The NPC recovers 1 Wound as soon as it \nloses 1, making them effectively immortal. The effect of the \nWound suffered is applied, so the NPC can be defeated, but \nwill regenerate on its turn to act; 4. Wish for Skill: The \nNPC raises their OL to Medium; 5. The NPC can no longer \nsleep because they are obsessed with the idea of working, \nand will constantly be chattering nonsense; 5. Wish to \nGrow Up: The NPC is a child with a body of a giant while \ntheir head has remained the same as before. They can take \n2 extra Wounds and inflict 1 additional Wound when they \nunleash their strength; 6. Wish for Love: The NPC has \nmerged with the one they love, literally obtaining the desire \nto “become one. ” As a double body the NPC can act twice.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are two Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nWhen Henkle realizes that Dorothea does not have \nthe missing pieces of the Compass Rose with her: \nhe will take off on the balloon as soon as it is ready, and \nthen activate the power of the incomplete Rose.\nIf Dorothea realizes that Henkle is willing to \nabandon her to return to the future: she will do \nanything to reach the man, begging him not to abandon \nher.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"We hate Henkle for what he did to us, but we serve \nhim in the hope that we can make another wish.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624772,"modifiedTime":1781557624772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uKoNmMOCpocsPmyb","name":"The Porcelain Princess","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"bz7efcagQ1FGzXX3","name":"The Porcelain Princess - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Porcelain Princess","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young noble who has fallen from grace. \nMy disfigured face is covered in a beautiful doll mask, and I \nsadistically manage the cult of the Crimson Kiss on behalf of \nmy lady Helga.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 235.","positive":"I am a young noble who has fallen from grace. \nMy disfigured face is covered in a beautiful doll mask, and I \nsadistically manage the cult of the Crimson Kiss on behalf of \nmy lady Helga.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Porcelain Princess","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5pwWmXbBpoman4dg","name":"Gift - Vials","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Porcelain Princess","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Princess always has five or six vials of \nHelga’s blood with her for newcomers to drink. She also has \n1 vial of the Infusion of Purity.\nPorcelain Dolls</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 235.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Porcelain Princess","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7Q5DPhxBZfsycQ7M","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Porcelain Princess","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young noble who has fallen from grace. \nMy disfigured face is covered in a beautiful doll mask, and I \nsadistically manage the cult of the Crimson Kiss on behalf of \nmy lady Helga.\nAgenda: Carry out every order of Helga in the hope that she \nwill heal my face / I would do anything to get my face back.\nGift - Vials: The Princess always has five or six vials of \nHelga’s blood with her for newcomers to drink. She also has \n1 vial of the Infusion of Purity.\nPorcelain Dolls</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 235.","owner":"The Porcelain Princess","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-porcelain-princess-235","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":235,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young noble who has fallen from grace. \nMy disfigured face is covered in a beautiful doll mask, and I \nsadistically manage the cult of the Crimson Kiss on behalf of \nmy lady Helga.\nAgenda: Carry out every order of Helga in the hope that she \nwill heal my face / I would do anything to get my face back.\nGift - Vials: The Princess always has five or six vials of \nHelga’s blood with her for newcomers to drink. She also has \n1 vial of the Infusion of Purity.\nPorcelain Dolls</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Carry out every order of Helga in the hope that she \nwill heal my face / I would do anything to get my face back.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uUr0pwy6QtN1ETZh","name":"Illusory Labyrinth","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"lbMgKJu1UreTeYkl","name":"Illusory Labyrinth - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Illusory Labyrinth","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A maze of trees and houses that change every \nminute, making it impossible to find your way around.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the center of the \nvillage. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Magician’s Fake \nCastle.\nTHIRD SCENE – The \nMagician’s Fake Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Finally in the center of the \nvillage, you find yourself in front of a huge oak that has been \nmolded into the shape of a grotesque castle. Inside the tree, \nyou can see a hot-air balloon made of patched fabric that is \nslowly inflating. You have never seen anything like it, but you \nunderstand it will not be good.\nPlace: Henkle’s workshop house in the center of the \nvillage, where the hot-air balloon is set up.\nTime: The morning sun is high in a cloudless sky.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 240.","positive":"A maze of trees and houses that change every \nminute, making it impossible to find your way around.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the center of the \nvillage. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Magician’s Fake \nCastle.\nTHIRD SCENE – The \nMagician’s Fake Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Finally in the center of the \nvillage, you find yourself in front of a huge oak that has been \nmolded into the shape of a grotesque castle. Inside the tree, \nyou can see a hot-air balloon made of patched fabric that is \nslowly inflating. You have never seen anything like it, but you \nunderstand it will not be good.\nPlace: Henkle’s workshop house in the center of the \nvillage, where the hot-air balloon is set up.\nTime: The morning sun is high in a cloudless sky.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Illusory Labyrinth","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624654,"modifiedTime":1781557624654,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MUxcwX44pBQw8VFS","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Illusory Labyrinth","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A maze of trees and houses that change every \nminute, making it impossible to find your way around.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the center of the \nvillage. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Magician’s Fake \nCastle.\nTHIRD SCENE – The \nMagician’s Fake Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Finally in the center of the \nvillage, you find yourself in front of a huge oak that has been \nmolded into the shape of a grotesque castle. Inside the tree, \nyou can see a hot-air balloon made of patched fabric that is \nslowly inflating. You have never seen anything like it, but you \nunderstand it will not be good.\nPlace: Henkle’s workshop house in the center of the \nvillage, where the hot-air balloon is set up.\nTime: The morning sun is high in a cloudless sky.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 240.","owner":"Illusory Labyrinth","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624654,"modifiedTime":1781557624654,"l