{"_id":"uWsXjWJVk529gk7o","name":"Corinne the Housekeeper","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"aW34FjL9kiAFveR9","name":"Corinne the Housekeeper - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Corinne the Housekeeper","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I know all rumors in the village, partly because \nI start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love \nreceiving gifts.\n6 Didier the Grumpy Old Man</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"I know all rumors in the village, partly because \nI start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love \nreceiving gifts.\n6 Didier the Grumpy Old Man","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Corinne the Housekeeper","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HshPJkFExHuCS3QM","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Corinne the Housekeeper","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I know all rumors in the village, partly because \nI start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love \nreceiving gifts.\n6 Didier the Grumpy Old Man</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","owner":"Corinne the Housekeeper","source":"Red-hood / Iskra","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-corinne-the-housekeeper-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I know all rumors in the village, partly because \nI start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love \nreceiving gifts.\n6 Didier the Grumpy Old Man</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"wMm2moqCTKwmbLPy","name":"Lucino - The Good Friend","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"zuRqzvDGhHFyOOeZ","name":"Lucino - The Good Friend - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lucino - The Good Friend","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a dutiful and studious child \nwho can’t wait to learn a trade to help my family.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","positive":"I am a dutiful and studious child \nwho can’t wait to learn a trade to help my family.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Lucino - The Good Friend","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lWdcK9hDimFJzTX8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lucino - The Good Friend","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a dutiful and studious child \nwho can’t wait to learn a trade to help my family.\nAgenda: Help Carlo become a responsible \nchild / Work to help adults who behave well \nand follow the law.\nVilla Balocchi\nDescriptor: A beautiful and sumptuous inn, recently \nrefurbished.\nInformation: \n ◆ Amabile hosts little Carlo, making him sleep in a small \nback room. \n ◆ The Puppet pays the greedy innkeeper with stones \nwhich he temporarily turns into gold coins with his \npowers. Throwing the coins into a safe in his room, the \ninnkeeper hasn’t yet noticed the Puppet’s trick. \n ◆ During the afternoon and evening, Carlo is at Villa \nBalocchi and can be found playing with Lucino or \npretending to study.\nAmabile Burromo</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","owner":"Lucino - The Good Friend","source":"Of Flesh and Wood","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-lucino-the-good-friend-137","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":137,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a dutiful and studious child \nwho can’t wait to learn a trade to help my family.\nAgenda: Help Carlo become a responsible \nchild / Work to help adults who behave well \nand follow the law.\nVilla Balocchi\nDescriptor: A beautiful and sumptuous inn, recently \nrefurbished.\nInformation: \n ◆ Amabile hosts little Carlo, making him sleep in a small \nback room. \n ◆ The Puppet pays the greedy innkeeper with stones \nwhich he temporarily turns into gold coins with his \npowers. Throwing the coins into a safe in his room, the \ninnkeeper hasn’t yet noticed the Puppet’s trick. \n ◆ During the afternoon and evening, Carlo is at Villa \nBalocchi and can be found playing with Lucino or \npretending to study.\nAmabile Burromo</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Help Carlo become a responsible \nchild / Work to help adults who behave well \nand follow the law.\nVilla Balocchi\nDescriptor: A beautiful and sumptuous inn, recently \nrefurbished.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xCQWGWtOYFrX7YkP","name":"Andersen","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"lnriWGDSrLdXRmPi","name":"Andersen - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Andersen","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills. \nIn addition to being a good leader, I am also a capable fighter.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 161.","positive":"I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills. \nIn addition to being a good leader, I am also a capable fighter.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Andersen","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622594,"modifiedTime":1781557622594,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UP9On97FThkWXgoQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Andersen","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills. \nIn addition to being a good leader, I am also a capable fighter.\nAgenda: Defend my new family from the danger that Enar \nrepresents / Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her \nunderstand that I am now a different man / Prevent anyone \nfrom discovering what I have done.\nGift - Commander: Andersen is skilled at giving orders \nand managing a battle. Up to 3 times per Scene, Andersen \ncan issue an order to an ally who will receive 1 Additional \nSuccess (+1 to OL in the case of an NPC) while executing it.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 161.","owner":"Andersen","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622594,"modifiedTime":1781557622594,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-andersen-161","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":161,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills. \nIn addition to being a good leader, I am also a capable fighter.\nAgenda: Defend my new family from the danger that Enar \nrepresents / Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her \nunderstand that I am now a different man / Prevent anyone \nfrom discovering what I have done.\nGift - Commander: Andersen is skilled at giving orders \nand managing a battle. Up to 3 times per Scene, Andersen \ncan issue an order to an ally who will receive 1 Additional \nSuccess (+1 to OL in the case of an NPC) while executing it.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Defend my new family from the danger that Enar \nrepresents / Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her \nunderstand that I am now a different man / Prevent anyone \nfrom discovering what I have done.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622594,"modifiedTime":1781557622594,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xlTE50GrkIiwUuH8","name":"Makes Wishes Come True","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ukPIIvgZ3XFN4sth","name":"Makes Wishes Come True - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Makes Wishes Come True","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a powerful wizard and what I desire \nbecomes reality. My skill as a barker always charms everyone \nto my side.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","positive":"I am a powerful wizard and what I desire \nbecomes reality. My skill as a barker always charms everyone \nto my side.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Makes Wishes Come True","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"n7mCVcZyFMEepShH","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Makes Wishes Come True","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful wizard and what I desire \nbecomes reality. My skill as a barker always charms everyone \nto my side.\nAgenda: I want to go back to my time alone and become a \ncelebrity thanks to the power of magic.\nGift - Hot-Air Balloon: As soon as it is ready, Henkle will \nboard and release his hot-air balloon into the air to activate \nthe Compass Rose. As indicated by the Scenario, based on \nthe actions of the Hunters this Gift will accumulate Time \nTokens. When the third Time Token is placed, the hot-air \nballoon is ready to go.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","owner":"Makes Wishes Come True","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-makes-wishes-come-true-242","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":242,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful wizard and what I desire \nbecomes reality. My skill as a barker always charms everyone \nto my side.\nAgenda: I want to go back to my time alone and become a \ncelebrity thanks to the power of magic.\nGift - Hot-Air Balloon: As soon as it is ready, Henkle will \nboard and release his hot-air balloon into the air to activate \nthe Compass Rose. As indicated by the Scenario, based on \nthe actions of the Hunters this Gift will accumulate Time \nTokens. When the third Time Token is placed, the hot-air \nballoon is ready to go.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want to go back to my time alone and become a \ncelebrity thanks to the power of magic.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xnCRudOgdBeBRbtu","name":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"0ncUzyadqpKjZRB6","name":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act \nas the strongarm of the gang. I have control over all cultists, \nand the power of The God Under the Mine has given me \nstrength and endurance equal to that of five men.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 210.","positive":"I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act \nas the strongarm of the gang. I have control over all cultists, \nand the power of The God Under the Mine has given me \nstrength and endurance equal to that of five men.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623894,"modifiedTime":1781557623894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"926KjsL5I9hkA9mL","name":"Gift - The Pincer","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Frank replaced his left arm with a \nhome-made mechanical arm with many functions. During \na Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: \n1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; \n2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise \nor lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other \nsubjects with him.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 210.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623894,"modifiedTime":1781557623894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"f3KEPeAT4GiRuz2V","name":"Gift - Gang Leader","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. \nOnce per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a \nsingle action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe Mine</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 210.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623894,"modifiedTime":1781557623894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3f4isSb4QBcvckLm","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act \nas the strongarm of the gang. I have control over all cultists, \nand the power of The God Under the Mine has given me \nstrength and endurance equal to that of five men.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and \nfind a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the \nday of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine \nwith beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to \nadd to the ranks of the gang.\nGift - The Pincer: Frank replaced his left arm with a \nhome-made mechanical arm with many functions. During \na Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: \n1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; \n2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise \nor lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other \nsubjects with him. \nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. \nOnce per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a \nsingle action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe Mine\nDescriptor: A gigantic coal mine where miners work day \nand night. Many areas are abandoned in favor of more \nprofitable veins. \nGift - Maze of Galleries: Whitehaven’s Mine is gigantic \nand without a guide it’s not easy to get to a specific location. \nWith each exploration roll, you can get 1 or more Map \nTokens which represent progress in learning the layout of \nthe mine. Upon reaching 3 Map Tokens, you can go directly \nto the Special result.\nWhen the Hunters explore the mine, roll 1 die or choose \ndirectly based on the narrative.\n1-2 Work zone A: Threading through the tunnels, \ndeafened by the sound of steam engines and digging, the \nHunters encounter a group of miners (2d6 + 6 Minor \nNPCs). If the Hunters do something weird, one of the \nworkers will alert Edward. Exploration will yield 1 Map \nToken.\n3-4 Work zone B: Threading through the tunnels, \ndeafened by the sound of steam engines and digging, the \nHunters encounter a group of miners (2d6 + 6 Minor \nNPCs). If the Hunters do something weird, 1d6 + 6 miners \nwill reveal themselves as Pig Heads and attack. Exploration \nwill yield 2 Map Tokens.\n5-6 Abandoned lodging: In an area close to the collapse, \nrecent traces of passage can be found. The Hunters meet \nFrank and 5 Pig Heads who are going to the well to meet up \nwith Arthur. Exploration will yield 2 Map Tokens.\nSpecial (3 Map Tokens): By moving a heavy stone, \nthe Hunters will find the mouth of the well that leads to \nArthur’s chamber. The shaft is narrow and thirty feet deep,</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 210.","owner":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623894,"modifiedTime":1781557623894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-frank-browne-the-middle-brother-210","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":210,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act \nas the strongarm of the gang. I have control over all cultists, \nand the power of The God Under the Mine has given me \nstrength and endurance equal to that of five men.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and \nfind a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the \nday of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine \nwith beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to \nadd to the ranks of the gang.\nGift - The Pincer: Frank replaced his left arm with a \nhome-made mechanical arm with many functions. During \na Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: \n1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; \n2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise \nor lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other \nsubjects with him. \nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. \nOnce per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a \nsingle action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe Mine\nDescriptor: A gigantic coal mine where miners work day \nand night. Many areas are abandoned in favor of more \nprofitable veins. \nGift - Maze of Galleries: Whitehaven’s Mine is gigantic \nand without a guide it’s not easy to get to a specific location. \nWith each exploration roll, you can get 1 or more Map \nTokens which represent progress in learning the layout of \nthe mine. Upon reaching 3 Map Tokens, you can go directly \nto the Special result.\nWhen the Hunters explore the mine, roll 1 die or choose \ndirectly based on the narrative.\n1-2 Work zone A: Threading through the tunnels, \ndeafened by the sound of steam engines and digging, the \nHunters encounter a group of miners (2d6 + 6 Minor \nNPCs). If the Hunters do something weird, one of the \nworkers will alert Edward. Exploration will yield 1 Map \nToken.\n3-4 Work zone B: Threading through the tunnels, \ndeafened by the sound of steam engines and digging, the \nHunters encounter a group of miners (2d6 + 6 Minor \nNPCs). If the Hunters do something weird, 1d6 + 6 miners \nwill reveal themselves as Pig Heads and attack. Exploration \nwill yield 2 Map Tokens.\n5-6 Abandoned lodging: In an area close to the collapse, \nrecent traces of passage can be found. The Hunters meet \nFrank and 5 Pig Heads who are going to the well to meet up \nwith Arthur. Exploration will yield 2 Map Tokens.\nSpecial (3 Map Tokens): By moving a heavy stone, \nthe Hunters will find the mouth of the well that leads to \nArthur’s chamber. The shaft is narrow and thirty feet deep,</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and \nfind a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the \nday of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine \nwith beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to \nadd to the ranks of the gang.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623894,"modifiedTime":1781557623894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xtzu803xWEfppZjH","name":"Alicia The Young Girl in Love","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"2bgOJRdXDSUj3zF3","name":"Alicia The Young Girl in Love - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alicia The Young Girl in Love","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young rebel from the slums who knows \nhow to get by on her own. Thanks to my tenacity, I can \novercome every obstacle.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 173.","positive":"I am a young rebel from the slums who knows \nhow to get by on her own. Thanks to my tenacity, I can \novercome every obstacle.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Alicia The Young Girl in Love","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yCcek5tomPpaWA1L","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alicia The Young Girl in Love","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young rebel from the slums who knows \nhow to get by on her own. Thanks to my tenacity, I can \novercome every obstacle.\nAgenda: I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run \naway with her to live out our love in peace.\nThreat - The White Rabbit</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 173.","owner":"Alicia The Young Girl in Love","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-alicia-the-young-girl-in-love-173","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":173,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young rebel from the slums who knows \nhow to get by on her own. Thanks to my tenacity, I can \novercome every obstacle.\nAgenda: I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run \naway with her to live out our love in peace.\nThreat - The White Rabbit</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run \naway with her to live out our love in peace.\nThreat - The White Rabbit","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"yBzgI0MrrROY3PFe","name":"The Animated Forest","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"Qh85MQ9iFUTAZI5y","name":"The Animated Forest - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Animated Forest","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We grab and capture all intruders through the \nmagic that animates our branches and roots.\nWolfgang the “druid”</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 233.","positive":"We grab and capture all intruders through the \nmagic that animates our branches and roots.\nWolfgang the “druid”","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Animated Forest","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mL1lh2jL2nTpCFpQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Animated Forest","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: We grab and capture all intruders through the \nmagic that animates our branches and roots.\nWolfgang the “druid”</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 233.","owner":"The Animated Forest","source":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-animated-forest-233","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":233,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: We grab and capture all intruders through the \nmagic that animates our branches and roots.\nWolfgang the “druid”</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"yQx3IMSoVhEMUMbc","name":"Dead Pirates","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"G9A0yi4fgyHjCGOD","name":"Dead Pirates - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dead Pirates","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a lost soul who only \nwishes for revenge on those who are still \nalive. My body is a heap of swollen and \nrotten flesh that moves slowly.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 163.","positive":"I am a lost soul who only \nwishes for revenge on those who are still \nalive. My body is a heap of swollen and \nrotten flesh that moves slowly.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Dead Pirates","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622641,"modifiedTime":1781557622641,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"GqKhbnhOLHrf2UPu","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dead Pirates","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a lost soul who only \nwishes for revenge on those who are still \nalive. My body is a heap of swollen and \nrotten flesh that moves slowly.\nSpecial agenda (James the \nSwordsman): We recognize James \nas the one who killed our captain in \na duel! It is his fault that our ship was \nwrecked, and we will taste his flesh \nfirst!\nGift - Walking Dead: The body \nof the Dead Pirate is rotten and \nputrescent, but it does not stop even if \ndismembered. After suffering his only \nWound, a Dead Pirate can still take his \naction before being eliminated, if he \nhas not already done so in the course \nof the Exchange. If a Dead Pirate acts \nagainst an outnumbered enemy, his \nOpposition Level is increased by 1.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 163.","owner":"Dead Pirates","source":"A Soldier's Duty","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622641,"modifiedTime":1781557622641,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-dead-pirates-163","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":163,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a lost soul who only \nwishes for revenge on those who are still \nalive. My body is a heap of swollen and \nrotten flesh that moves slowly.\nSpecial agenda (James the \nSwordsman): We recognize James \nas the one who killed our captain in \na duel! It is his fault that our ship was \nwrecked, and we will taste his flesh \nfirst!\nGift - Walking Dead: The body \nof the Dead Pirate is rotten and \nputrescent, but it does not stop even if \ndismembered. After suffering his only \nWound, a Dead Pirate can still take his \naction before being eliminated, if he \nhas not already done so in the course \nof the Exchange. If a Dead Pirate acts \nagainst an outnumbered enemy, his \nOpposition Level is increased by 1.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622641,"modifiedTime":1781557622641,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zS1jWu2uamVNfp9k","name":"The swamp where the fairies have","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"1NJb2BJ9qoIClw6c","name":"The swamp where the fairies have - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The swamp where the fairies have","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A marshy swamp with a stone \ntrack as its only path.\nThe water is black, cold, and deep enough to slow a \nHunter who falls into it.\nNote: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter \nSkutt.\n ◆ The Fairies are corrupted by the splendor of the crown \nand will not allow anyone to touch it. It is possible to \ncommunicate with them by interrupting their dance. \nThe Fairies will tell the story of a human princess who \ngifted them with the crown, as bright as a small sun, \nin order to cross the swamp. It is difficult to maintain \na conversation with dreamlike entities, and in a short \ntime they will slip back into their dreams and start \ndancing again.\n ◆ If the Hunters attempt to take the crown, the Fairies \nwill awaken from their trance. Screaming in pain, they \nwill attack the culprits without hesitation. Around the \ncrown there are always twelve fairies.\n ◆ Somehow blocking the light emanating from the \ncrown will awaken the Fairies from the spell. They will \nlook at the cracked moon, screaming in agony as they \nrealize how much the lands around \nthem have been corrupted. Some will \nsuffer so much that they will become \ndew in the grass or a pale reflection in \nthe pond. Others will ask the Hunters \nto do something to save their lands.\nFairies</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 189.","positive":"A marshy swamp with a stone \ntrack as its only path.\nThe water is black, cold, and deep enough to slow a \nHunter who falls into it.\nNote: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter \nSkutt.\n ◆ The Fairies are corrupted by the splendor of the crown \nand will not allow anyone to touch it. It is possible to \ncommunicate with them by interrupting their dance. \nThe Fairies will tell the story of a human princess who \ngifted them with the crown, as bright as a small sun, \nin order to cross the swamp. It is difficult to maintain \na conversation with dreamlike entities, and in a short \ntime they will slip back into their dreams and start \ndancing again.\n ◆ If the Hunters attempt to take the crown, the Fairies \nwill awaken from their trance. Screaming in pain, they \nwill attack the culprits without hesitation. Around the \ncrown there are always twelve fairies.\n ◆ Somehow blocking the light emanating from the \ncrown will awaken the Fairies from the spell. They will \nlook at the cracked moon, screaming in agony as they \nrealize how much the lands around \nthem have been corrupted. Some will \nsuffer so much that they will become \ndew in the grass or a pale reflection in \nthe pond. Others will ask the Hunters \nto do something to save their lands.\nFairies","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The swamp where the fairies have","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Bnjm7M4kzqtQTlmV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The swamp where the fairies have","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A marshy swamp with a stone \ntrack as its only path.\nThe water is black, cold, and deep enough to slow a \nHunter who falls into it.\nNote: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter \nSkutt.\n ◆ The Fairies are corrupted by the splendor of the crown \nand will not allow anyone to touch it. It is possible to \ncommunicate with them by interrupting their dance. \nThe Fairies will tell the story of a human princess who \ngifted them with the crown, as bright as a small sun, \nin order to cross the swamp. It is difficult to maintain \na conversation with dreamlike entities, and in a short \ntime they will slip back into their dreams and start \ndancing again.\n ◆ If the Hunters attempt to take the crown, the Fairies \nwill awaken from their trance. Screaming in pain, they \nwill attack the culprits without hesitation. Around the \ncrown there are always twelve fairies.\n ◆ Somehow blocking the light emanating from the \ncrown will awaken the Fairies from the spell. They will \nlook at the cracked moon, screaming in agony as they \nrealize how much the lands around \nthem have been corrupted. Some will \nsuffer so much that they will become \ndew in the grass or a pale reflection in \nthe pond. Others will ask the Hunters \nto do something to save their lands.\nFairies</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 189.","owner":"The swamp where the fairies have","source":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-the-swamp-where-the-fairies-have-189","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":189,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A marshy swamp with a stone \ntrack as its only path.\nThe water is black, cold, and deep enough to slow a \nHunter who falls into it.\nNote: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter \nSkutt.\n ◆ The Fairies are corrupted by the splendor of the crown \nand will not allow anyone to touch it. It is possible to \ncommunicate with them by interrupting their dance. \nThe Fairies will tell the story of a human princess who \ngifted them with the crown, as bright as a small sun, \nin order to cross the swamp. It is difficult to maintain \na conversation with dreamlike entities, and in a short \ntime they will slip back into their dreams and start \ndancing again.\n ◆ If the Hunters attempt to take the crown, the Fairies \nwill awaken from their trance. Screaming in pain, they \nwill attack the culprits without hesitation. Around the \ncrown there are always twelve fairies.\n ◆ Somehow blocking the light emanating from the \ncrown will awaken the Fairies from the spell. They will \nlook at the cracked moon, screaming in agony as they \nrealize how much the lands around \nthem have been corrupted. Some will \nsuffer so much that they will become \ndew in the grass or a pale reflection in \nthe pond. Others will ask the Hunters \nto do something to save their lands.\nFairies</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
